title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix molasses, syrup, soda and water together for bottom of pie.
Make crumbs with flour, oleo and brown sugar for top part of pie.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for about 25 minutes longer or until done.

title: glazed chicken
directions: Mix preserves, onion soup mix and Russian dressing.
Pour over chicken breasts and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: jack's crunchy crispy cornbread
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Batter will be slightly lumpy.
Add additional milk if desired to reach consistency if batter is too thick.
Pour batter into greased square pan, 8 x 8-inches.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a preheated 400° oven.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix in 9x13 pan and press down.
Bake 350° for 10 minutes. Let cool.

title: gumbolie
directions: Cook rice.
Mix together with peas and tomato juice.
Cook ground beef, onion, pepper, salt and chili powder.
Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: hungarian style cabbage rolls(new year's tradition for good luck)
directions: You will also need toothpicks.

title: oreo delight
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Crush Oreos and mix with one stick melted margarine.
Reserve 3/4 cup cookie mix for topping.
Press remaining cookie mix into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add pudding to milk. Beat in softened cream cheese and whipped topping.
Pour over cookie mix in pan.
Sprinkle reserved cookie mix on top.
Chill.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs and combine with buttermilk. Add remaining ingredients and blend well. Pour in pie shells. Bake 10 minutes at 275°. Bake 50 minutes at 300°.

title: glorified rice
directions: Cook rice; let cool.
Put jello, sugar, water and marshmallows in top of double boiler.
Heat just enough for marshmallows to melt.
Pour into rice, apple and pineapple mixture.
Set in icebox until set, then add Cool Whip.
Mix well.

title: caramels
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients in a large saucepan to soft boil stage. Add butter and evaporated milk quickly. Stir constantly. Heat to 242°, then remove from heat. Add vanilla and stir.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
When cool, cut into squares and wrap in wax paper.

title: pecan pie squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease jelly roll pan.

title: beef skillet fiesta
directions: Brown meat in oil over high heat, leaving meat in coarse chunks.
Add onion; reduce heat to medium and cook until onion is tender (not browned).
Add seasonings, tomatoes, corn and bouillon.
Bring to boil again.
Stir in green pepper and bring to boil.
Stir in rice; remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.

title: vegetable barley soup
directions: Combine all but beans and barley into large pot.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat, then simmer for 1 hour or until carrots are almost tender.
Add barley and cook until barley is done.
Add beans just before serving.

title: sausage breakfast bar
directions: Layer bottom of pan with a can of crescent rolls.
Bake 5 minutes.
Mix cheese, eggs and sausage and layer on top of rolls. Top with other can of rolls.
Cook for 20 more minutes.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Cook peeled potatoes in salted water until tender; drain and add ingredients.
Beat until smooth, light and fluffy.
Cool and cover.
Refrigerate.
Amount needed may be heated in a greased casserole dish at 350° about 30 minutes.
May be kept refrigerated for 2 weeks.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in baking dish that has been sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: carla's christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter in large mixer bowl.
Gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture. Mix well.

title: stir-fried garlic shrimp
directions: Cook and stir garlic in oil in 10-inch nonstick skillet over medium heat for 1 minute.
Add shrimp and stir-fry 1 minute longer.
Stir in mushrooms, scallions and wine.
Stir-fry until shrimp are pink and vegetables are hot, about 2 minutes longer. Serve over rice.

title: potatoes n cheese
directions: Peel and cook potatoes. Add salt and pepper to taste. Drain potatoes and place in baking dish. Mix together soup and milk. Pour on top of potatoes. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: fruit cocktail pie
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Mix whipped cream, Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice and add fruit cocktail and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Chill until set, about 1 hour.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 7 ingredients and mix well, placing in a casserole dish.
Mix brown sugar, flour and 1/3 stick of butter.
Spread over the first mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake 20 minutes, covered.
Remove lid and bake 15 to 20 more minutes.

title: fruit crunchies
directions: Separate biscuits.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Dip biscuits in butter, then into sugar mixture.
Make thumbprint in center of each; fill with jelly.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, until brown.
Frost with thin powdered sugar frosting.

title: carrot ginger soup
directions: Bring to a boil, carrots, onions, ginger and broth.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer for 45 minutes or until carrots are very tender.
Stir in milk and butter.
Cool slightly and puree in a food processor or in 2 batches in blender.
Reheat as needed. Garnish with mint leaves.
Refrigerate up to one week or freeze.

title: leta's dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos.
Mix cream cheese, butter, sugar and
Cool Whip. Mix pudding, milk and vanilla.
Combine the 2 mixes.
Layer crushed cookies, mix, cookies, mix, etc.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix everything together.
Roll into balls and shape as you please.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes or until done.
Makes 4 or 5 dozen cookies.

title: hearty beef and cheese crescent pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In frying pan, brown beef, onion and green pepper.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, beans, garlic and salt.
Simmer while preparing crust.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix thawed hash browns, 1/2 stick margarine, salt, pepper, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1/2 stick margarine with corn flakes and sprinkle on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: preacher cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, cocoa and butter and boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter (let melt).
Stir in oatmeal.
Spoon onto wax paper.
Let harden and enjoy!

title: *koulourakia(twist cookies)
directions: Cream the margarine for 10 minutes. Add oil and continue beating. Add sugar and eggs, one at a time and continue beating. Add dry ingredients (flour and baking powder) gradually. Add orange juice, milk and vanilla. Continue beating to a soft dough.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: To potatoes, add sugar, eggs, salt, margarine and vanilla flavoring.	Mix well and place in a baking dish.

title: orange fluff
directions: Mix dry jello with sour cream.
Fold this into the Cool Whip. Add fruits and chill at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except beans.
Drain beans.
Pour mixture over beans and let stand overnight.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Crush cookies in food processor or purchase them already crushed. Blend margarine, powdered sugar, cream cheese and milk until thoroughly blended in blender. Add 2 small packages of instant pudding. Continue mixing until all ingredients are blended. Fold in 12 ounces Cool Whip.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add dry ingredients and milk along.
Add flavoring.
Bake in greased tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: jesse's favorite zucchini bread
directions: Beat 3 eggs until frothy.
Add oil, vanilla, sugar and zucchini.
Combine dry ingredients.
Beat into wet mixture.
Pour into 2 greased and lightly floured or sugared loaf pans.
Bake 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: old-fashioned molasses nut bread
directions: Mix together the molasses and milk in a large bowl.
In a separate bowl, mix both flours, sugar, baking soda, salt and nuts; stir quickly into liquid, mixing until just blended.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 1/2 x 5 1/4 x 2 3/4-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan before slicing.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: curried chicken breast
directions: Cook chicken breasts in margarine for 5 minutes or until brown, turning once.
Add orange juice, onion, curry and coriander.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until chicken is tender and no longer pink.
Transfer chicken to heated serving platter, cover to keep warm.
Over medium heat, bring pan juices to boiling.
Stir in grapes and jam.
Serve juices and chicken over rice.
Makes 3 servings.

title: doctor bird cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar.
Beat well.
Add oil, vanilla, pineapple and juice; beat again.
Add dry ingredients a little at a time.
Fold in diced bananas last.
If you want to use a 9-inch tube pan or a long cake pan, bake tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350° or long pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook butter and onion in microwave for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add flour, chicken broth and milk.
Heat in saucepan over medium heat. Add Cheddar and Velveeta cheese.
Add broccoli.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Beat all ingredients for 2 minutes.
Pour into large pie pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes in preheated oven.
Knife inserted in middle should come out clean.
It makes its own crust.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix popped corn and peanuts together and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients except soda in microwave in 4-quart dish. Microwave on High 9 to 13 minutes. Stir each 5 minutes.
Mixture should be completely dissolved and 250°.
Quickly add soda. Stir until foamy.
Pour over popped corn and peanuts.
Mix well.
Pour onto cookie sheet or foil to cool.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, cook and stir onion and bacon until bacon is crisp and onion is tender.
Stir in soup and milk; heat through, stirring occasionally.
Stir in clams (with juice), lemon juice and pepper.
Heat through.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Place broccoli in buttered 12 x 8 x 2 1/2-inch casserole. Lay cooked chicken pieces on top of broccoli. Mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice. Pour over mixture. Sprinkle grated cheese over casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and cheese is melted.

title: brownie nut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a baking pan, 8 x 8-inch. Measure all ingredients into large mixer bowl.
Blend 1 minute on low speed, then beat on high speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into pan. Bake 40 to 50 minutes until done.

title: punch slush
directions: Put bananas in blender.
Bring sugar and water to boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add to juices and bananas.
Put into 6 (1 quart) containers.
Freeze.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill several hours before using.

title: mock chow mein
directions: Put into covered dish.
Open large can chow mein noodles. Stir in few of the noodles; add rest to top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: boiled custard
directions: Scald milk in double boiler.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add to milk.
Cook about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Temper well-beaten eggs with some of the hot milk, then add to rest of milk, stirring well.
Cook 2 or 3 more minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Strain and cool.
You may also want to temper the sugar and flour with a small amount of hot milk.
Serve with nutmeg sprinkled on the top.

title: guacamole
directions: Beat avocados, onion, peppers, lemon juice, salt and pepper until creamy.
Fold in tomato.
Cover and refrigerate.
Stir before serving.
Makes 2 cups.

title: mulled cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and bring slowly to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes. Strain before serving.

title: parmesan baked potatoes
directions: Pour butter into 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan.
Sprinkle cheese over butter.
Place potatoes, cut side down, over cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 400°, for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: caribbean salad(note:  this is a dessert)
directions: Slice bananas.
Sprinkle juice of limes and grated rind on bananas.
Add remaining ingredients and well drained fruit.
Mix lightly, but thoroughly.
Freeze.
(I use a Bundt pan; we enjoy this when served with pound cake.)

title: spicy bean toss
directions: In large skillet, stir-fry Italian beans, peppers and onions in margarine until crisp-tender.
Add garbanzo beans, olives and Italian seasoning; mix lightly.
Reduce heat to low.
Add process cheese spread and milk; stir until process cheese spread is melted.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: pecan pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add milk or water and egg yolks and stir well.
Spray saucepan with Pam, then pour mixture in pan and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened. Remove from heat and add margarine and vanilla.
Beat until margarine is melted.
In an oblong dish, put a layer of wafers, then a layer of pudding.
Then sprinkle a layer of chopped pecans. Repeat this again with a layer of each.
In a medium bowl, pour egg whites and 1/4 teaspoon soda.
Beat until fluffy and will stand in a peak.
Add 6 tablespoons sugar and beat a little. Spread over pudding.
Put in oven and brown meringue.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Mix and let rise 1 hour.
Make stiff dough.
Put in icebox and make rolls when ready.
Roll out and cut with round cutter.
Brush melted butter on this.
Fold as you would half moon pie.
Put on cookie sheet and let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Cook until brown.
Brush with melted butter.
Put back in oven for about 1 minute.

title: tortellini salad with pesto dressing
directions: Mix all salad ingredients together.
Pour Pesto Dressing over salad.

title: orange pineapple chicken stir-fry(lo-fat)
directions: Preheat heavy frypan or wok about 3 minutes on medium-high heat.
Spray with nonstick corn oil cooking spray. Add chicken strips and garlic; stir-fry about 3 minutes.
Increase heat to high and add onion and snow peas. Stir-fry about 3 minutes. Add salt, pepper, ginger and pineapple.
Continue to stir-fry about 3 minutes more.

title: prune cake - orange
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs. Beat thoroughly. Add prunes and mix well. Add soda to buttermilk. Add flour and milk alternately. Bake in a well-greased, floured tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes. While cake is still hot in pan, pour mixture of juice of 2 oranges, 2 teaspoons grated orange rind and 2 cups confectioners sugar over the cake and let stand until cake has absorbed it. This cake stays moist for days.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix milk and Cool Whip. Add pineapple (drained), lemon juice and pecans.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: almost guilt-free brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and spray an 8 or 9-inch square pan with cooking spray.

title: pudding cake
directions: Tear the cake into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare the pudding and pour over the cake while the pudding is thin.
Spread the pie filling over the
pudding.
Let stand several hours.
Spread the Cool Whip over the pie filling and serve. It freezes well and will keep for some time frozen.

title: shrimp in beer(crock-pot cooking)
directions: Wash shrimp in cold water, drain.
Place in crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Cover and cook on high setting for 2 hours or until shrimp turn pink, if desired.
Turn to low setting until serving time, up to 2 hours.
Yields 4 to 6 servings, 2 1/2 quarts.

title: ernest's baked steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge steak with the dry ingredients.
Pound the flour into the steak well on both sides; keep adding flour as needed.
Brown in a hot skillet on both sides and bake at 325° until tender, approximately 2 hours.
Add about 1 cup water during cooking and a little flour to make gravy while baking.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Onion may be added if so desired.
Add milk to the consistency desired for vegetables or chips.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling in 13 x 9 x 2 pan. Place crushed pineapple evenly over filling. Mix together cake mix and margarine until crumbly.
Sprinkle over fruit. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in oleo.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: hearty beef stew
directions: Put cubes in Dutch oven with cover.
Pour beef broth over meat.
Fill can with water and add to pot along with salt, pepper, thyme and bay leaf.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Add veggies and cook on stove top until tender.

title: race day biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450 degrees.
Thoroughly cut shortening into flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in just enough milk until dough leaves side of bowl and forms a ball.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface.
Knead 10 times.
Roll or pat dough into 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with floured 2 1/2 inch cutter.
Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10-12 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield about 8 biscuits.

title: crispy chewy cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking powder, salt and soda. Cream butter. Gradually blend in sugars, beating well after each addition. Add egg and vanilla. Blend well. Add flour mixture and blend well. Stir in cereal. Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Cool. Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: no name cookies
directions: Cream butter, oil, sugars and extracts.
Stir in eggs, one at a time, then beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Chill dough.
Roll dough into walnut size pieces; flatten with glass dipped in granulated sugar.
Bake on ungreased pan at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Drain corn and put in bottom of 2 quart casserole.
Add pepper.
Saute
onion in small amount of melted oleo.
Stir in soup,
sour
cream	and grated cheese.
Pour this mixture over corn in
casserole.
Pour rest of melted oleo over this layer. Crush
Ritz
crackers fine (I crumb in the blender).
Sprinkle over melted oleo.
Bake in slow 300° oven for 45 minutes.

title: lazy day lasagne
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
In greased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish, make layers in order half each of noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese slices and spaghetti sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Wash and scrub potatoes.
Cut lengthwise into halves or quarters.
Combine ingredients; dip each half or quarter into mixture.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Spoon remaining mixture over potatoes and sprinkle with fine bread crumbs.

title: cauliflower cheese casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower according to package directions; drain. Place in 1-quart baking dish that has been sprayed with nonstick spray.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place eggs, cottage cheese, onion flakes, salt and pepper in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Pour over cauliflower.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes until set and lightly browned.
Makes 2 servings.
Each serving equals 2 protein and 2 vegetable exchanges.

title: cheese cake
directions: Make crust with vanilla wafers and butter.

title: mint tingle
directions: Combine the water and sugar and bring to a boil while stirring constantly.
Remove from the heat and cool.
Then add the lemon juice and mint extract, next enough green food coloring to tint a very delicate green.
Before serving, add the ginger ale and serve with or without chopped ice.
Makes 5 cups before adding ice. Serve and enjoy.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets until fork-tender. Peel, then shred into a large bowl.
Stir in sour cream, onions, 1 cup cheese, salt and pepper. Turn into a greased casserole dish. Top with the 1/2 cup cheese and paprika.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° for about 40 minutes or until heated thoroughly. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: jewish brownies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, eggs, cocoa, flour, salt and nuts.
Bake in greased pan (11 x 16-inch) at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: onion rings
directions: Separate onions into rings.
Once done, set aside.
In a bowl, combine egg, milk, the 3 tablespoons oil, flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Beat just until well moistened.
Using a fork, dip onion rings into batter; drain off excess batter.
Add to deep hot fat (375°).
Fry onion rings in a single layer, stirring once with a fork to separate rings.
Once onions are golden brown, about 2 to 3 minutes, remove from fat and drain, using a paper towel.
Sprinkle with salt and serve.

title: buster bars
directions: Crush cookies and add oleo.
Pat in pan and freeze for 1 hour. Soften ice cream.
Put on top of crust and freeze.
Mix chocolate chips, oleo, powdered sugar and evaporated milk.
Boil 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Let cool thoroughly and put on top of ice cream; sprinkle with chopped walnuts if desired.
Freeze 2 hours.

title: almond punch
directions: Combine
all ingredients except ginger ale.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add
ginger ale just before serving.
May freeze and serve slushy.
Makes
a dull yellow color.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Soften and mix ice cream and Cool Whip.
Crumble Oreos and add to ice cream mixture.
Freeze in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sausage roll-ups
directions: Separate and flatten crescent rolls.
In microwave or in saucepan, melt butter or margarine.
Add parsley flakes to suit your taste.
Brush crescent rolls with butter mixture.
Sprinkle each crescent roll with Parmesan cheese.
Carefully roll one sausage in each crescent roll, starting at the side end of the crescent roll.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake according to crescent roll directions until rolls are lightly browned. Remove from baking sheet and cut each roll into 4 pieces.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: 7-up jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O gelatin in water.
Beat in cream cheese with electric mixer.
Slowly add 7-Up and vanilla.
Let thicken; add drained pineapple and pecans. Chill in 1-quart mold.

title: western perfection salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cold water, vinegar and salt.
Chill.
When gelatin becomes thick and syrupy, add remaining ingredients.
Turn into 1-quart shallow pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut in squares and serve on a bed of lettuce with mayonnaise.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
This is very good.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken and onion in plenty of salted water.
Boil until the chicken is very tender. Remove the meat from the bones and cut into bite size pieces.
Save the broth to cook spaghetti. Make a sauce by mixing soups, cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat until the cheese melts. Cook spaghetti in broth.
Place in a baking dish a layer of spaghetti, a layer of chicken and a layer of sauce.
Repeat until all the ingredients are used. Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and top is browned.

title: steak and zucchini supper
directions: Cut steak into thin strips.
Stir-fry in hot oil in skillet. Add gravy, sauce mix and water; mix well.
Cook, covered, over low heat for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add zucchini.
Cook for 10 minutes or until zucchini is tender-crisp, stirring occasionally.
Serve over hot cooked rice or noodles.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken in bottom of casserole.
Pour drained peas over chicken.
Mix soup and broth together and pour on top.
Mix biscuit mix, margarine and buttermilk.
Pour over other ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: butter pecan dessert
directions: Mix flour, melted oleo and 1/2 cup ground nuts well and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: funny face pancakes
directions: Beat ingredients with a wire whisk or hand beater until smooth.
For each pancake, pour 1/4 cup onto griddle or frypan. (Grease pan, if necessary.)
Cook until edges are dry.
Flip with spatula and cook until golden.
Use banana slices, grapes, raisins, blueberries, and any other fruit to decorate with.

title: ornamental cookie frosting
directions: Sift powdered sugar and cream of tartar through very fine sifter.
Add egg white with mixer at high speed.
Beat mixture so stiff that a knife drawn through it leaves a clean path.
Work quickly to ice cookies before frosting stiffens and dries.

title: spaghetti marinara
directions: *Can substitute canned tomatoes with 3 pounds ripe plum (Roma) tomatoes, peeled, seeded and chopped.

title: shamrock frosting
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Chill until slightly thickened, then blend in whipped topping.
Makes 4 cups or enough for tops of 24 cupcakes or for two 9-inch layers.
Store in refrigerator.

title: porcupines
directions: In large pan, melt butter and sugar, then quickly add beaten eggs, stirring constantly. Add dates. Cook on medium. Add vanilla and salt. Cook until it slightly comes to a bubbly mix and until dates make mixture darker. Remove from heat. Add Rice Krispies and walnuts. Let cool enough to handle and roll in coconut. Keep refrigerated.

title: diana's sweet potato pie
directions: Peel and boil potatoes; drain.
Mash them with mixer, adding butter while they are hot.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well (consistency should be loose).
Rinse beaters to remove strings.
Strain mix into a clean bowl to remove lumps.
Fill pie shell and bake at 425° (hot) for 55 to 60 minutes.
Center may look soft but it will set later.
Yields 3 pies.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides in a skillet; set aside.
Place rice in greased casserole and place chops on top of rice.
On the top of each pork chop add pork chop drippings, onion slices, tomatoes and green pepper rings.
Season with salt and pepper. Pour tomato juice over all.
Sprinkle with basil.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Reserve 2 tablespoons flour.
Wash blueberries and drain well. Combine with reserved flour.
Grease 12 muffin pans.
Combine rest of flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Combine egg, milk and melted shortening and stir swiftly into dry ingredients.
Add floured blueberries; mix well.
Spoon into muffin pans.
Bake for 25 minutes or until browned.
Serve hot.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All, corn and beans; mix with celery soup, sour cream and grated cheese.
Pour in casserole dish.
Crumble crackers and mix with melted margarine.
Pour on top of casserole. Bake in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese and sausage balls
directions: Cook and drain sausage. Trim crusts from bread and roll flat. Mix cheese and butter together. Spread on both sides of each bread slice. Roll a sausage in each slice. Bake on greased baking sheet at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes. Slice into bite-sized pieces.

title: kellogg's rice krispie treats
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat. Add Rice Krispies.
Stir until well coated.

title: reuben chicken
directions: Place breasts in casserole dish.
Squeeze sauerkraut and place some on each breast.
Put slice of Swiss cheese on top; spread Thousand Island dressing over all.
Cover and bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain well. Mix drained meat, drained Veg-All and soup together (may use cream of chicken).
Place in greased casserole dish.
Top with 1 can of biscuits.
Cook at 350° until biscuits are brown.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Molasses may be used instead of syrup.
Cook sugar and vinegar in a heavy saucepan over moderate high heat.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Then cook, uncovered, without stirring until a drop forms a hard ball when put into cold water.
Remove from heat and mix in butter and vanilla.
Pour over the popcorn and stir quickly until well mixed.
With buttered hands, shape into balls.
Cool on waxed paper.
Serves 24.

title: easy cranberry-orange muffins
directions: For coconut topping, in a bowl stir together the 1/3 cup biscuit mix and the 2 tablespoons sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Add the coconut, tossing with crumb mixture to coat. Set aside.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine milk, 1/2 cup butter, sugar and salt in a saucepan. Heat until butter melts.
Cool to 105° to 115°.
Add yeast, stirring until dissolved.
Place flour in a large bowl.
Add milk mixture and stir until well blended.
Cover and let rise in warm place (85°) free from drafts, about 1 hour and 20 minutes or until doubled in bulk.
Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Dip each in melted butter.
Layer balls of dough in a 10-inch one-piece tube pan or Bundt pan.
Cover and let rise about 45 minutes or until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Yields one 10-inch loaf.

title: bourbon slushes
directions: Let tea bags steep in boiling water until strong.
Add sugar while tea is warm, stirring until dissolved.
Add orange juice, lemonade, bourbon and water, mixing until dissolved.
Pour into individual plastic glasses and freeze.

title: homemade yeast
directions: Make a thin batter of flour and lukewarm water; let it stand in a warm place until it ferments and is full of bubbles.
Two cups of this liquid yeast is equal to one cup of old yeast.
Yeast is good when foamy and full of beads, has a brisk pungent odor and has snap and vim; it is bad when it has an acid odor, is watery and has a thin film on top.

title: old fashioned gingerbread
directions: Beat well and add 1 cup very hot water. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken chalupas
directions: Cook and cut up chicken into bite size pieces. Saute onion and celery in a little butter. Blend soups, broth, green chiles, onion and celery.
Pour half of the soup mixture into large baking dish. Put half of the chicken on top of the soup mixture and all of the tortillas, torn in pieces.
Layer remaining chicken and soup. Bake at 350° until bubbly. Top with cheese and melt.

title: onion bread
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in soup mix.
Blend well. Stir in sugar and margarine.
Mix until margarine melts.
Cool to lukewarm. Sprinkle yeast over warm water.
When dissolved, add yeast mixture, egg and 2 cups flour to the lukewarm milk mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Add remaining flour to make a stiff batter.
Cover tightly and chill at least 2 hours.
Cut dough in half.
Flatten and press into 2 well-greased 9-inch round pans.
Brush with melted margarine.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled in size, about 45 minutes.
Bake at 375° for about 35 minutes. Remove from pans and cool on racks.
Brush again with melted margarine while still hot.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs; add sugar, corn syrup, melted margarine and pecans.
Pour into unbaked shell. Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Firm when cool.

title: summer punch
directions: Mix frozen juice with water as directed on cans.
Cut sherbet in two-inch squares and add to fruit juices.
Chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes on high in large bowl.
Gradually add sugar, beating constantly.
Add pumpkin, lemon juice and dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour into greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: apple roll
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Roll into ball and chill.
Bring next 4 ingredients to a boil and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Roll dough into large circle.
Sprinkle with apples, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll into jelly roll.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch slices.
Put in pan and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine ingredients and store in refrigerator.

title: pecan rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine hot milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 cup flour; beat well. Beat in yeast and egg.
Gradually add remaining flour to form a soft dough, beating well.
Brush top lightly with soft shortening. Cover and let rise in warm place until double (1 1/2 to 2 hours). Punch down; turn out on lightly floured surface and divide dough in half.
Roll each piece in 12 x 8-inch rectangle, about 3/8-inch thick.

title: glazed graham cookies
directions: Place graham crackers on a cookie sheet sprayed with food release.
Melt butter and margarine together slowly.
Add sugar. Bring to boil and boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour mixture quickly over graham crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 10 minutes at 325°.
Remove from pan immediately with spatula. Place on waxed paper.

title: chinese cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumbers; slice thinly.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over cucumbers.
Stir carefully; chill.
Makes 6 servings. Preparation Time:

title: purple cooked cabbage
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain off fat.
Add cabbage, pinch of red pepper and salt to taste.
Add garlic and potatoes.
Add 1/2 cup water and cook over low heat.
When potatoes are done, serve.

title: fruit dip
directions: Makes 2 cups.
Dip apple, oranges, bananas, grapes, strawberries, etc.

title: bacon-leek soup
directions: Cut slices of bacon into bits and place in stewpot.
Saute until almost done.
In the meantime, clean and cut up leeks, including the green part.
Add to bacon.
Saute until limp.
Add mushrooms and cook for 5 minutes.
Then add water and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour in rectangular pan.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken.
Debone.
Cut in small pieces.
Crumble chips in baking pan.
Mix cream of chicken soup and Ro-Tel in saucepan. Add chicken and heat.
Pour over chips.
Top with cheese.
Heat in oven until cheese melts.

title: cranberry-tangerine conserve
directions: Remove peel from tangerines; scrape off excess white membrane. Cut and peel into very thin strips.
Reserve 3/4 cup strips.

title: fake apple slices (zucchini)
directions: Mix together with fork.
Reserve 1/2 c. mix for later use. Press remaining mix into 9x13 pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes and cool.

title: chocolate bonbons
directions: Melt chocolate chips with peanut butter over hot (not boiling) water.
Remove from water.
Add remaining ingredients; mix until well coated.
Spoon into tiny 1/2 ounce paper cups or drop by heaping teaspoon onto waxed paper lined cookie sheets.
Chill until set.

title: sauce leon
directions: Saute garlic and onions, then add sausage meat and wine and simmer five minutes.
Add tomatoes and cook 20 minutes.
Add all other items and simmer slowly for 5 minutes longer; serve on cooked pasta.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: In bowl, combine milk, sugar, eggs, vanilla, salt and nutmeg. Beat well to blend.
Sprinkle coconut into pastry shell.
Pour egg mixture over coconut.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Can be served with whipped cream.

title: orange delight
directions: Bring pineapple to a boil, juice and all.
Add jello, cool. When cool, add orange juice and ginger ale.
Chill until partially set.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into mold.
Let set until firm.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: quick pie
directions: Mix together and pour into graham cracker crust.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 2 pies.

title: potato soup
directions: Put all ingredients in pot and barely cover with water. Cook until desired texture is reached. Thicken with cornstarch if needed.

title: pumpkin cobbler
directions: Sprinkle dry cake mix over pumpkin mixture and drizzle melted margarine over top.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons oleo until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients except crescents.
Mix.
Separate crescents into 4 rectangles.
Firmly press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup mixture onto the center of each.
Pull the 4 corners to center and twist slightly.
Brush with the rest of the oleo.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apricot ball cookies
directions: Grind or cut up finely apricots.
Mix with coconut and milk. Mix chopped nuts into mixture.
shape in 1-inch balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Do not bake.
Let stand 2 hours or until firm.

title: nina bemus' favorite chicken spaghetti
directions: Stew hen with salt, pepper and a stalk of celery until tender. Cool and remove bones; cut into bite size.
Cook peppers, celery and onions in a small amount of broth until tender.
Add chili powder, soup, mushrooms and pimentos.
Cook spaghetti as directed on box.
Mix chicken, vegetables and spaghetti together.
Pour into large casserole.
Cover with grated cheese and bake at 350° until mixture bubbles.

title: fruit dip
directions: Sift confectioners sugar.
Heat marshmallow cream in microwave 30 seconds.
Let cream cheese get to room temperature. Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and refrigerate until used.

title: borscht
directions: Cook chicken or beef until almost done.
Add all the vegetables.
Just before serving, add the cream.

title: 2 hour buns
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add boiling water.
Beat well. Add eggs.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix salt with 6 cups flour.
Mix well.
Knead in about 2 more cups of flour.
Put in large greased bowl.
Let raise 1 hour.
Shape into buns and let raise 1 hour.
Bake at 350° about 15 to 20 minutes until lightly browned.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats.
Beat butter and add sugars, vanilla and eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Add to oat mixture.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Bake 50-55 minutes at 350°.

title: calico beans and burger
directions: Brown bacon, then ground beef and onion in bacon drippings. Mix browned meats and remaining ingredients with one can each of: lima, kidney, Northern and pork and beans.
Pour into 3-quart casserole and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in prebaked deep dish pie shell.
Sprinkle chips on top or you can mix in with other ingredients.

title: cocoa brownies
directions: Soften margarine; combine in order listed.
Pour into greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Can be frosted or nuts omitted.

title: maple pecan shortbreads
directions: For shortbreads, preheat oven to 350°.
Generously butter a 9-inch square baking dish.
Cream butter and sugar in processor until light and fluffy.
Add flour and process until blended; do not form a ball.
Pat into bottom of prepared dish.
Bake until shortbread is light brown, about 25 minutes.

title: strawberry frosted
directions: Crush the berries in a blender.
Add sugar and chill.
Add milk and ice cream.
Stir until ice cream is partially melted. Pour into glasses and top each serving with whipped cream.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Fry, salt, drain and break tortillas into small pieces or use Doritos.
Grate cheese (reserve 1/2 cup cheese for topping).
Mix green chili, cheese, soup, tomato sauce and tortillas or Doritos with ground beef and onions. Put in casserole dish and top with 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tropical fruit freeze
directions: Put thawed orange juice into 48-ounce Tupperware container. Add pineapple juice and stir.
Banana is pureed with 1 tablespoon of lemon juice in blender.
Add to orange juice mixture.
Seal container and freeze several hours until slushy.
Stir in ginger ale when ready to serve.
Yields eight 6-ounce servings.

title: cherry treat
directions: Melt butter in baking
dish.
In
bowl,
combine
flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and milk;
stir
until
smooth.
Pour over
melted butter in baking dish.
Layer
cherries over batter. Add 1/2 cup sugar to cherry juice and pour over mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In a saucepan, stir together ingredients.
Stirring frequently, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and boil gently for 15 minutes to thicken.
Makes 2 cups.

title: peach butter
directions: Scald, peel and chop peaches.
Place in large kettle.
Add only enough water to prevent sticking.
Cool until soft, stirring frequently.
Press through sieve, measuring 2-quarts of pulp. Cook about 30 minutes or until thick, stirring often.
Place into hot jars.
Process for 10 minutes in hot water bath.

title: death by chocolate cake
directions: Pour oil in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover bottom.
Add cake mix, eggs and water.
Stir in pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Take cake from oven and let sit for 10 minutes.
Punch holes in cake with end of wooden spoon.
Pour fudge topping into holes and over cake.
(I heated mine in microwave so it would pour easier.)
Cool completely. Frost with Cool Whip and garnish with nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: beverly's bundt bread
directions: Pour melted butter into bundt pan and roll around sides.
Place the three crescent rolls as they come out of container around bottom of bundt pan.
This makes a quick and easy breakfast bread.

title: amish dressing
directions: Brown bread in butter in skillet, turn often.
Beat eggs, add milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix it all together.
Put 1/4 cup butter in baking dish or pan, brown it.
Then pour dressing in. Bake it at 350° to 375° until done.

title: linguine salad
directions: Cook and cool the linguine.
Cut chicken breasts into small pieces.
Add remaining ingredients.
I also like to add ripe olives, sliced, for added contrast.
This salad is good even without meat.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine soups and broth; boil, then pour over chicken.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple delight torte
directions: Mix and press in a 9 x 13 pan. Bake just a little and cool.

title: ham and cheese appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes, at 350°.
Cut into rectangles, about 2 x 1 1/2-inches.
Makes 36 appetizers.

title: jodi's favorite heart-smart zucchini bread
directions: Using low speed of electric mixer, combine egg, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
In separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Gradually add to zucchini mixture; blend evenly. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans (use safflower margarine to grease pans).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: buttermilk pies
directions: Beat eggs.
Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Melt butter and add with eggs to dry mixture, beating slightly.
Add buttermilk and continue to beat.
Add vanilla and blend.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until firm in center.

title: meat and cheese loaf
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Mix well.
Press into greased pan and bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fluffy meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, mix together all ingredients.
Press into shallow loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: honey dinner rolls
directions: In a large bowl, combine together flour and yeast, then set aside.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; slice in thirds and arrange in a lightly greased
x
x
2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt. Pour
corn	syrup and butter evenly over potatoes and sprinkle with
pecans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Arrange marshmallows over
potatoes.
Bake
an additional 10 or 12 minutes or until marshmallows are lightly browned.
Yields 10 servings.

title: christy's sausage
directions: Melt together in saucepan, then add sausage.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: great gazpacho
directions: Chop vegetables into tiny pieces.
Add spices, salt and pepper and tomato juice.
Dice avocado and add to soup.
Stir well and chill.

title: microwave baked beans
directions: Get more juice from lemons and limes.
Heat fruit 20 to 30 seconds on High.
Cut and squeeze out the juice.

title: spinach layered salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and Miracle Whip; set aside.
Layer ingredients with mayonnaise and Miracle Whip mixture between layers.
Should be able to get 2 layers with mayo mixture on top, then cover with cheese.
(I have cheese thick enough so plastic wrap doesn't stick to mayo mixture.)
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight or at least all day.

title: martian cookies
directions: *Be sure to shred zucchini so you have thin and long green pieces.

title: tahitian punch
directions: Use Tupperware jello mold to freeze pineapple juice.
Put the frozen mold in bottom of punch bowl and pour remaining beverages on top.
Makes a very refreshing punch for summer picnics.

title: easy lemon (or lime) pie
directions: Mix together, pour into crust.
Refrigerate until set. Delicious summer treat!

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook pasta al dente.
While pasta cooks, heat butter and add flour; cook for few minutes, stirring.
Add salt and pepper. Bring to boil and simmer until thickens; stir in cream, chicken and cheese.
Heat butter and lemon juice in skillet.
Saute mushrooms until juice cooks off.
Drain pasta; combine with cream mixture and place 1/2 in shallow baking dish.
Spread mushrooms over; reserve some for garnish.
Top with remainder.
Sprinkle with cheese and mushrooms.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes, until light brown.

title: microwave chocolate cake
directions: Grease round micro-proof baking dish, 6 1/4 x 2 1/2-inches or 8 x 1 1/2-inches; line bottom with plastic wrap.
In small microwaveproof bowl combine cocoa and 1/3 cup water; microwave on High (full power) 40 to 50 seconds or until very hot and slightly thickened.
In medium bowl combine flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add oil, remaining 1/3 cup hot water, egg, vanilla and chocolate mixture; beat until batter is smooth and well blended.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes * without turning until cake beings to pull away from side (some moist spots may remain but will disappear on standing).
Let stand 5 minutes; invert onto serving plate.
Peel off plastic wrap; cool.
Frost.
Yields about 8 servings.

title: mound cake
directions: Bake cake in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool and slice in half.

title: california casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease 12x8x2 (2 qt.) pan.
In hot butter in large skillet, saute onions until golden, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in hot rice, sour cream, cottage cheese, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Layer 1/2 rice mixture, then 1/2 chilies.
Sprinkle with cheese and then repeat.
Bake, uncovered 25-30 minutes until bubbly and hot.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 8.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel apples; remove cores.
Slice apples in thin slices; put in lightly greased pie pan.
In a bowl, mix oats, sugar and flour. Add margarine; stir until you have a crumbly mixture.
Put mixture on top of apples; spread to cover apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: gumdrop bars
directions: Mix gumdrops and nuts; set aside.
Beat eggs until light; add sugar, flour, salt and flavoring.
Gradually add gumdrops and nuts. Spread into 11 x 16-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry angel dessert
directions: Break the cake up in about 1-inch pieces into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix the cooled (if cooked) pudding and sour cream together, then pour over cake pieces.
Spread the cherry pie filling over the pudding and chill.

title: maryland sparkler
directions: Pour thawed juice into large pitcher, stirring constantly, until dissolved.
Add chilled ginger ale and mix thoroughly.

title: bob's chili
directions: Brown meat and drain off all fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Good on hamburgers and hot dogs.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt.
Cream the sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Add sour cream and half the flour mixture; blend.
Add rest of flour; blend by hand.
Chill.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: creole jambalaya
directions: Melt shortening in heavy saucepan over medium heat or 350° on controlled surface heat. Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients except rice.
Bring to a boil.
Press rice into liquid.
Cover and simmer at 200° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: country meatball ragout
directions: Mix thoroughly beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion, salt and dash of pepper; shape firmly into 24 meatballs.
In large saucepan, brown meatballs in 2 tablespoons shortening; pour off fat.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.
Gradually blend 1/2 cup water into 1/4 cup flour until smooth; slowly stir into stew. Cook, stirring until thickened.
Remove bay leaf.
Makes about 8 1/2 cups.

title: shrimp fettucine
directions: Saute onions, peppers, celery and green onions in margarine until soft.
Add flour, parsley and shrimp and let cook about 15 minutes.
Add jalapeno relish, Velveeta and half and half.
Cook fettucine until tender.
Drain and mix in shrimp mixture.

title: oven pork chops
directions: Dip pork chops in beaten egg, then in crumbs to coat it.
Fry quickly in heated Pam coated skillet just to brown slightly.
Place in greased roaster pan and spread Parmesan cheese on each pork chop.
Salt and pepper; pour pizza sauce over all the chops.
Bake at 350° covered loosely with foil for 40 minutes, then spread Mozzarella on each chop.
Bake another 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: betty's pound cake
directions: Beat butter and margarine until blended.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time until well blended.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Add flour alternating with milk and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper; coat meat in seasoned flour. Brown in hot shortening in Dutch oven.
Add soup, water, onion and basil.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Add potatoes, carrots and water (or grape juice).
Cover and bake 1 hour longer or until tender.
Makes 2 or 3 servings.
Can be doubled.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: In a saucepan, combine all the ingredients and cook on medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Marinate meat (beef, chicken or pork) overnight in refrigerator.
When cooking chicken or pork, the meat must be dipped repeatedly in the sauce to keep from burning.

title: frito pie
directions: Mix beans and tomatoes together.
Layer bottom of casserole pan with Fritos, meat, then bean mix, then shredded Cheddar cheese.
Keep layering until you run out.
Top layer with finely crushed Fritos and cheese.
Bake in oven about 20 minutes at 350° until cheese melts.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients until well blended.
Makes 3/4 cup. Can be used as a dip for vegetables.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion in water until tender.
Drain well.
Mix together sour cream, soup and grated carrot.
Mix with squash and onion.
Melt oleo and add croutons.
Layer in a 2-quart casserole dish, starting with squash and ending with croutons.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken ciullo appetizers
directions: Spray a baking pan with Pam.
Arrange the wings in the pan. Sprinkle the wings with the poultry seasoning, celery salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Put a pat of butter on each piece of chicken. Grate a generous layer of Romano on top and sprinkle with parsley. Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Baste them every 20 minutes. Don't turn them.

title: pecan pie
directions: Stir all ingredients in a bowl.
Then put in shells.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Make a well and add the egg, butter, juice and water.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in cranberries, nuts and orange peel.
Bake in greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan at 350° for about 1 hour or until bread tests done.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan to a wire rack.
Recipe doubles well.

title: orange roughy with tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop and seed tomato.
In ovenproof skillet, over medium heat, saute onion and garlic in margarine until soft, about 5 minutes.
Stir in tomato and seasonings.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Place fish in skillet; cover with sauce. Pour wine over fish.
Cover and bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until fish flakes with fork.
Remove fish to heated platter.
Reduce sauce on top of range to 1/3 cup.
Stir in tomato paste and pour over fish.
Serve with lemon wedges.

title: scrooge mcduck's blueberry buckle(for kids to make)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart baking dish with butter.
Put the corn flakes on a piece of waxed paper and crush them into little pieces.
Wash the blueberries and put them in a medium saucepan.
Add the sugar, water and lemon juice.
Cover and cook for 5 minutes over low heat.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix the cake mix, 1 stick butter and 1 egg together to make crust.
Mix confectioners sugar, cream cheese, 3 eggs and vanilla together.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, or until done.
Once it is brown on top and crust is brown, it's ready.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat and drain; add next 6 ingredients and simmer for 45 minutes.
Mix Ricotta cheese, egg, salt, pepper, parsley and Parmesan cheese.
Cook noodles per package.
In a dish, layer noodles, cheese mix, sauce and Mozzarella cheese; cook at 375° until bubbly.
You can use low-fat ingredients; still real good.

title: tuna-cashew crunch casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle remaining noodles on top.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: foolproof beef and broccoli
directions: Slice beef across grain into very thin strips.
Freeze 1 hour before slicing.
In skillet over medium-high heat, in hot oil, cook beef and garlic until beef is browned. Add onion.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring often. Stir in soup, water and soy sauce.
Heat to boiling. Add broccoli.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serve over noodles.

title: lois jane's broccoli and rice
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Combine sauteed vegetables, rice, broccoli, cheese, milk and soup in well buttered baking dish. Salt and pepper to taste.
Top with bacon crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Cool on pan before removing.

title: banana bars
directions: Cream together butter and sugar. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes in an ungreased jelly roll pan.

title: skillet chicken with fruit
directions: In a large, nonstick skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Add chicken and brown for about 6 minutes per side.
Remove chicken, season lightly with salt and pepper.
Add 1/3 cup water to skillet and stir to loosen and dissolve any browned bits.
Stir in dried fruit, lemon juice and thyme.
Place chicken over the fruit and baste with sauce.
Arrange lemon slices over chicken.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 30 minutes or until chicken is cooked through and fruit is tender.
Remove lemon slices and place around edge of serving platter.
Transfer chicken and fruit to platter. Add 1/3 c. water to broth in skillet and bring to boil, 1 minute. Pour over chicken and serve.
Serves 6.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Put vegetables in large bowl.
Pour dressing over vegetables, stirring to coat.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Keeps well for 1 week.
Serves 10 to 12.
tags: Wish-Bone olive oil Classic red wine vinaigrette dressing

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Slit chilies, remove seeds and rinse.
Place thick slice of cheese in chilies.
Place in a buttered dish.
Do not layer.
Mix eggs, milk and flour.
Pour over chilies.
Add grated cheese on top.
Bake 55 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy horseradish dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring until well blended.
Cover and chill for at least 3 hours.
Serve with veggies.
Yields 2 cups.

title: strawberry nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 3 greased and floured 8-inch pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon into pie shell.
Chill before serving.

title: mud slide pie
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, butter and water.
Put in pan and bake about 15 minutes.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Place cherries in a large bowl. Sprinkle with sugar, tapioca, lemon rind and salt.
Toss lightly to mix.
Let stand while making pastry.

title: excellent pie crust(single crust)
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar together.
Cut in shortening.
Add water.
When all flour is moist, form into a ball.
Roll out about 1 1/2 inches larger than pan.
Put in pan and flute edges.
Take a fork and punch holes in the bottom and around the sides of the crust (this keeps it flat).
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes or until the crust is as brown as you want it.

title: pineapple cream cheese cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed.
To prepare cream cheese frosting, drain the pineapple juices.
Mix together cream cheese, Cool Whip, sugar and crushed pineapple with hand mixer until smooth.
Spread frosting on cooled cake.
Sprinkle with pecan pieces.
Place pineapple slices on top of frosted cake with a cherry in the middle of each slice.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: flying brooms
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy.
Gradually add brown sugar, beating until blended.
Add flour and salt, beating until blended.
Stir in vanilla.
Shape dough into 16 (1
1/4 inch) balls.

title: mom romig's scalloped oysters
directions: Stir butter into crumbs.
Alternate layer of oysters and crumbs, ending with crumbs.
Pour mix of liquor, milk and butter over layers before last layer of crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broiled stuffed clams
directions: Saute the onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons of the melted butter or margarine 3 minutes.
Add the well-scrubbed clams and the wine, cover the pan and simmer 5 to 10 minutes, or until clams are opened.
Remove the clams from the pan and remove the clams from the shells.
Chop the clams or put them through a meat grinder.
Rinse the shells in cold, running water.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Boil celery, onion, sugar, salt, vinegar and corn oil.
Pour over drained vegetables.
Store overnight.

title: lime-yogurt salad
directions: Drain pears, reserving 1/2 cup syrup; slice pears.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Measure 1 cup gelatin; blend in yogurt and pour into 8-inch square pan.
Chill until set but not firm. Add measured syrup to remaining gelatin and chill until slightly thickened.
Arrange pear slices on gelatin-yogurt layer and top with clear gelatin.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Cut into squares.
Garnish, if desired.
Makes 9 servings.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta until done.
Drain and rinse.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add potato salad dressing.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage; stir to crumble and drain.
Spread bread with margarine and cut in cubes.
Place bread in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Sprinkle sausage on cubes of bread and top with cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour on top.
Chill at least eight hours before baking.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage and cheese thoroughly.
Sift flour a small amount at a time, mixing thoroughly until blended, with sausage and cheese mixture.
Roll into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes or until bottom of balls are brown at 400°.

title: bud's burgers
directions: Fry burgers on medium heat 6 to 8 minutes (semi-done); pour off grease except for small amount and remove burgers.
Cook onions for 2 to 3 minutes in grease; add Karo, A.1. sauce and Hellmann's Dijonnaise mustard and mix until liquid.
Put burgers back in and let simmer for about 5 minutes.
Put burgers on buns and top with remaining juices for open-face sandwiches or top with favorite burger fixings and sauce.
Enjoy.

title: rum cake
directions: Boil for 2 minutes or more.
Pour over cake and let stand for 15 minutes.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Place dill seed, garlic and hot peppers in bottom of jar. Pack cucumbers on top of spices.
Then heat water, vinegar and salt; pour hot solution over cucumbers.
Seal and pressure five minutes.

title: hot rolls
directions: Heat milk until warm.
Dissolve yeast, sugar and salt in milk. Melt butter.
Add 1/2 cup to mixture, then add flour to make stiff dough. Put dough on a floured board and roll out and cut in rolls.
Put in a greased pan.
Grease top of rolls with butter. Set in warm place and let rise.
Put in oven and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
When brown, take out and brush top of rolls with butter.

title: zucchini italiano
directions: Cut ends from zucchini; do not pare.
Cook in boiling salted water for 5 minutes.
Halve lengthwise.
Remove pulp with spoon; reserve shells.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and onions until tender.
Add chili sauce, catsup and sweet relish.
Simmer for a while.
Serves approximately 8 to 10.

title: chicken-cheese soup
directions: Slice and saute carrots, onion and celery in butter until tender.
Chop in blender with flour.
Heat milk and broth while cutting cheese in small chunks; drop into milk mixture.
Cook until melted.
Add vegetables and chicken.
Cook over low heat 1 hour.

title: baked clams
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in butter until light brown; add clams.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Combine seasonings and white sauce; add clam mixture.
Pour into greased casserole; sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: green onion fern garnish
directions: Heat oil and onion in large pot on medium-high heat; saut until colored and softened slightly, 2 to 3 minutes. Add celery and carrot and cook until almost tender. Pour into a large bowl. Put half the chicken in pot; saut both sides until lightly browned, 4 to 5 minutes. Add cooked chicken to vegetable bowl and saut remaining chicken. Return vegetables and chicken to pot; cover. Cook on low until chicken releases juices, about 20 minutes. Increase heat to high; add water, salt and bay leaves and simmer, then cover and barely simmer until the stock is rich and flavorful, about 30 minutes. Strain stock and discard solids. Cool and place in container in fridge until cold and all fat rises to the top and sets. Skim fat off. Stock will keep up to 2 days in fridge and 6 months in freezer. Makes about 2 quarts.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together and then add all the rest of them.
Bake at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine brown sugar, flour, corn syrup, eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in margarine and pecans.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes or until center of pie is puffed and golden brown. Cool.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: harvest pumpkin muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine dry ingredients.
In medium bowl, whisk eggs, pumpkin, margarine and peel.
Stir in walnuts and raisins. Pour pumpkin mixture into dry ingredients.
Stir just until mixed. Spoon batter into 12 greased muffin cups.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Add boiling water until clear and thick, stirring constantly.
Add a drop or two of red food coloring to give a rosy tint.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Stir fresh whole strawberries into mixture.
Pour into large baked pie shell.
Chill several hours.

title: breaded cauliflower
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just until blended.
Dip cauliflower into batter.
Fry in deep, hot oil at 375° until golden.
Drain on paper towel.

title: hot sauce
directions: Cook onion and garlic over medium heat, stirring constantly, until tender. Add tomato and remaining ingredients. Cook until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally, serve warm.
Yields 1-1/2 cups.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Put flour and sugar into mixing bowl and mix thoroughly.
In saucepan, mix margarine, shortening, unsweetened chocolate, water and salt.
Bring to boil.
Cook 1 minute and add to flour-sugar mixture.
Beat well.
Add eggs, soda (dissolved in buttermilk) and vanilla.
Beat until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: yeast bread (rolls)
directions: Sift dry ingredients, then add Crisco, then add warm yeast water while kneading a long time.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Cream together butter and powdered sugar.
Add flour gradually.
Roll dough into small balls and dip in powdered sugar. Place on non-greased cookie sheet and crisscross with a fork. Bake in 300° oven until slightly brown.
The dough may also be pressed into a shortbread mold.

title: sweet and sour salad dressing
directions: Combine sugar, salt, mustard, onion and half the vinegar. Gradually add salad oil, beating constantly and vigorously.
Beat in remaining vinegar.
Add celery seed.
Continue to beat until mixture thickens.

title: amish starter and friendship bread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Proceed to day 1.

title: peach pie
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into unbaked pastry shell; dot with butter and cover with top crust.
Flute edges.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes.

title: breakfast brunch
directions: Place 6 slices of bread butter side down in buttered 9x13 pan.
Cover with sausage.
Add cheese.
Place remaining 6 slices of bread butter side up over cheese.
Beat remaining four ingredients and pour over bread.
Refrigerate 12 hours.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheesecake
directions: Melt butter; add to cracker crumbs and sugar.
Use mixture to line bottom of spring-form pan (mash down with back of a fork).

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients raw.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: best strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix all and beat for 4 minutes on medium speed. Pour into a 12 x 18 inch pan that has been greased and floured. Tap to remove all air bubbles. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes. Cut into 25 to 28 pieces.

title: sangria
directions: Juice the first 3 fruits.
Combine juice, sugar and liqueur in 3-quart pitcher until sugar is dissolved. Add red wine and fruit slices. Cover and refrigerate for 4 hours.
Just before serving, mix in club soda and pour over ice in wine glasses.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Mix sour cream, onion and soup together for your sauce . Layer in casserole bowl:
corn, beans, cheese and sauce on top. Sprinkle crumbled crackers on top of sauce.
Dribble melted margarine over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic; drain.
Add picante sauce, spinach, tomato sauce, tomatoes, pepper, lime juice and salt. Simmer uncovered 15 minutes.
Arrange 6 tortillas on bottom and up sides of greased 13 x 9-inch dish.
Top with 1/2 of meat mixture. Layer remaining tortillas, overlapping if necessary.
Spread sour cream over tortillas.
Top with remaining meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with shredded cheeses.

title: dressing
directions: Mix everything together.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a pie plate, 9 x 1 1/4 inches.
Place all ingredients in blender; blend on high speed for 15 seconds.
Pour into a pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and a knife inserted in center comes out clean (50 to 55 minutes).

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream
together
butter,
Crisco and sugar until fluffy. Add cocoa.
Add
eggs,	one
at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir soda, sour cream and sweet milk together.
Stir salt into flour.
Add
milk
mixture and flour to batter alternately beating well
after
each addition.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Pour into greased
and floured 10-inch tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Cool in pan 5 minutes. Turn out to cool.

title: jello cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream oleo, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Add the sifted dry ingredients and mix thoroughly. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until done.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix ingredients and shape into round mounds on serving dish. Garnish with chili sauce.

title: bean bake
directions: Brown hamburger and bacon in skillet.
Add onion and cook slightly.
Mix rest of ingredients, except tomatoes, in Dutch oven.
Pour tomatoes over the top.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Fry the sausage or beef to medium.
Remove grease and add spaghetti sauce.
Remove from heat.
While the meat cooks, combine Ricotta, spinach and eggs in a food processor and process until spinach is not larger than 1/2-inch leaves.

title: doctor birds cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together slightly; set aside.
Mix all dry ingredients:
flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and sugar.
Add egg mixture.
Add the bananas to the dry ingredients along with the oil, vanilla and crushed pineapple with juice.
Stir mixture, do not beat.
Pour into a greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Set aside to cool on a rack without removing from the pan.

title: scripture cake
directions: Follow Solomon's prescription for making a good boy by Proverbs 23:14.
Bake at 350° until tests done.

title: thimble cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat egg yolks and vanilla.
With a wooden spoon, gradually work in flour until blended.
Chill if necessary.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place 1 1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press hole in the center, using a floured sewing thimble and fill with jam.
Bake at 325° until brown on bottom, but not on the top, about 25 minutes.
Store in tightly covered tin box.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple in large bowl; mix well.
Add other ingredients to pudding mix and chill.
Will keep in refrigerator several days.

title: lemon sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in dry ingredients, then lemon and mix well.
Chill 2 hours.
Shape into 1 1/4-inch balls and roll in additional sugar.
Bake on greased baking sheets, 2-inches apart for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onions in oil or margarine, then add water and bouillon cubes and bring to a boil.
Add the fine noodles and cook until the noodles are nearly done, then add the broccoli and cook 5 more minutes.
Then add the milk and the cheese.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Scald milk and cream in top of double boiler.
Combine the flour, cornstarch, sugar and salt; mix them together thoroughly. Add to the scalded milk.
Cook until mixture becomes thick and smooth, then cook 15 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Stir a small amount of the mixture into the beaten egg yolks.
Pour egg mixture back into the double boiler and cook a few minutes longer. Cool and add vanilla.
Slice 2 bananas thin and arrange in the bottom of the baked pie shell.
Pour the cooled cream filling over them.
Top with your favorite meringue made with the 2 egg whites. Brown in oven.
Cool, refrigerate and serve.

title: mary bowden's oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.

Combine oleo, sugars and pudding mix in a large mixer bowl. Beat until smooth and creamy. Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in oats and raisins. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased baking sheet.

title: crabmeat salad
directions: In a mixing bowl combine all ingredients except lettuce and tomatoes.
Serve on lettuce with cherry tomatoes as garnish, chilled.
Serve with hot, crusty French bread.

title: hamburger goulash
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet and drain.
Chop onion and pepper and cook in with hamburger until tender; drain.
Add tomatoes, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Add corn.
Simmer 15 minutes.
May add 1 tablespoon sugar at the
last if you want it sweet.

title: beef and broccoli casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add salt, garlic powder, pepper and mushrooms.
Stir.
Cook broccoli and drain well; add to meat mixture along with soup and sour cream.
Place in greased cooking dish with a lid; top with cheese and cover.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: holiday ham balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes approximately 7 dozen.

title: deviled cheese sandwich
directions: Combine cheese and chopped vegetables.
Add eggs, seasonings and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Spread on bread or crackers.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Combine cooking oil and sugar and beat until smooth; add egg yolks and beat well.
Add hot water and beat; sift together dry ingredients.
Stir in sweet potatoes, nuts and vanilla; beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Sift dry ingredients together 3 times.
With a large fork, mix cheese with flour mixture.
Melt margarine.
Add water slowly, then blend with cheese mixture.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix lemon juice with the cherry pie filling and pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread 3/4 of a box of dry yellow cake mix on top of cherry pie filling.

title: microwave hacienda dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, salsa and salt until well blended.
Spread cream cheese mixture in pie plate or bowl.
Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes or until heated.
Stir every 2 minutes.
Makes 2 cups.

title: spider cookies
directions: Combine margarine, 10x sugar and peanut butter.
Roll mixture into small balls.
Place 2 small balls on a graham cracker half square.
Break 1 stick pretzel in half and use these on 1 ball on graham cracker for legs.
Use 6 halves total.
Use mini chips for eyes and nose.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
While the oven is heating, melt butter or margarine in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan in the oven.
Cover the melted butter with the graham cracker crumbs and press into a crust.
Sprinkle the chocolate chips, coconut and walnuts over the crust.
Pour the condensed milk over the top.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until slightly brown.
Cool completely before cutting into bars.
Refrigerate to keep the bars firm.

title: schrafft's hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter, chocolate and sugar over hot water in a double boiler.
Add other ingredients.
Let cook for 2 hours.
Just before serving, add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Makes 1 pint.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Put all ingredients in cooker.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: ranch style mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in tightly covered jar.
Makes 1/2 cup.

title: mud hen bars
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg plus 2 egg yolks. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Combine all the above ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Spread in a 9x13 pan.
Sprinkle over batter nuts, chips and marshmallows.
Beat 2 egg whites stiff and fold in brown sugar.
Spread over top of cake and Bake at 300 degrees for 30-40 minutes.

title: sourdough flapjacks
directions: Place one package yeast in a deep bowl.
Add one cup water and stir to dissolve yeast.
Add enough flour to make mixture stiffer than waffle batter.
Cover bowl and let stand overnight.
The next morning, stir in 1/4 teaspoon baking soda, 3/4 teaspoons salt and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Add 1 or 2 eggs.
One egg for heavy batter or 2 eggs for thinner batter.
Cook on griddle pan just like pancakes.

title: magalene chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and cornstarch together.
Add milk, egg yolks, vanilla and butter; cook on low heat, stirring until thick and smooth.
Put in baked pie shell.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Add all ingredients and bake until when inserted with knife comes out clean.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and cook until done.

title: 5 hour pot roast
directions: Place roast on large double layer of foil.
Pour soups on top. Salt and pepper.
Close tight.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding mix and pineapple together.
Add Cool Whip, marshmallows and pecans.
Mix well and refrigerate for 2 hours or longer.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; put in casserole, buttered with other 1/2 stick butter.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: squash and apple casserole
directions: Pare squash.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds and stringy portions.
Cut crosswise into 1/4-inch slices.
Place slices in a medium saucepan.
Cover with water.
Cook covered over medium heat 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain and place on paper towels.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: night cookies
directions: Turn oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Add sugar slowly to egg whites.
Stir in food coloring and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Put in oven, close oven door and turn oven off immediately, as soon as you shut the door.
Leave overnight in oven.
Store in tin to keep airtight.
Eat.
Do not open oven door for anything until morning.

title: cheesy barbecued potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in shallow, greased baking dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes; uncover and bake 15 minutes.
Everyone loves these potatoes!

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well and shape into loaf pan.

title: cherry dump pudding
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and 1/2 cup sugar into bowl. Add shortening, milk and vanilla.
Beat with spoon or mixer.
Pour into greased 6 x 10-inch pan.
Cover with drained cherries and sprinkle with 1/4 or 1/2 cup sugar.
Heat the drained juice and pour the hot liquid over the cherries.
Bake at 375° about 40 minutes.
Serve warm with plain whipped cream or ice cream.

title: lemon tea bread
directions: Cream butter and 1 cup sugar well.
Add eggs.
Beat.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Beat well. Add grated rind and nuts.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done in center. Mix lemon juice with remaining sugar.
Spoon over bread as soon as it comes from oven.
Let juice run down sides.
Cool.

title: raisin-cinnamon bread
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine 2 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Heat milk, water and butter until very warm (120° to 130°); butter does not need to melt.
Add to flour mixture.
Add egg.
Beat at low speed until moistened; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, add raisins and enough remaining flour to make a firm dough.
Knead on well floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased pot, turning to grease top.
