Cover; let rise in warm place for 40 minutes (20 minutes for quick rise yeast).

title: twinkie cake
directions: Cut Twinkies in half and place in oblong pan, cream side up. Fit in closely any way they will fit.
Mix sour cream and vanilla pudding together (following instructions on box).
Spread over Twinkies.
Mix together flour, 1 cup water and sugar; heat until thick.
Let cool and add jello and strawberries (cut in half) and pour over Twinkies.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Put Cool Whip on top.

title: mock steak(serves 10 people)
directions: Mix meat, flour and seasonings by hand.
Shape into long loaf pan or individual rounds.
Wrap in foil and place in refrigerator 2 to 3 hours or overnight.
When ready to cook the loaf, prepare heavy-duty skillet with 3 tablespoons melted shortening.
Slice meat 1/2-inch thick and shape into steak like pieces.
Brown in skillet on both sides.
Remove slices to a large baking dish. Prepare sauce by mixing onion soup mix, mushroom soup and 2 cans of water.
Pour over meat; cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Serves 10 people.

title: icebox cookies
directions: It may not take that amount of flour so go carefully, mixing well.
Make into 3 rolls. Wrap wax paper around each and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° about 10 minutes. Watch.
Can refrigerate rolls of dough up to 1 month.

title: ham casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter. Stir in flour and 2 cups of the milk and cook until thickened. Add soup and ham, and heat thoroughly. Pour into greased medium-sized casserole.

title: macaroni salad with boiled dressing
directions: Prepare Dressing:
In medium saucepan, mix eggs with sugar and dried mustard.
Add vinegar and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
When mixture starts to boil, remove from heat and allow to cool.

title: easy barbecued chicken
directions: Brown chicken breast in skillet over medium heat.
Add barbecue sauce and simmer over low heat for 45 minutes or until tender. Serves 4.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugar.
Add egg and rest of ingredients. Make into small balls.
Flatten and place a half almond in center. Bake until lightly browned at 350° (approximately 15 minutes, depending upon your oven).

title: rich pastry
directions: Cut shortening into flour, salt and sugar.
Beat yolk and lemon juice. Add milk.
Add to pastry.
Roll into ball.
Chill. Makes two 8-inch crusts.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake at 350° uncovered 30 to 40 minutes.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream butter, eggs and sugar.
Add flour and fold in buttermilk last.
Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: orange-pineapple bread
directions: Put in well-greased pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: beet gelatin salad
directions: Drain canned beets.
Heat liquid.
Dissolve jello in juice. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour in ingredients. Mix thoroughly.
Pour in oiled mold and chill until firm.

title: squash patties
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and drop by tablespoonful into hot oil in a frying pan.
Flatten each patty and cook until golden brown.
Turn carefully.
Serves 4.

title: peach melba ice cream dessert
directions: Thaw raspberries and strain through smallest hole strainer so no seeds are in remainder of juice and pulp.
In medium saucepan, combine raspberries, jelly and cornstarch.
Cook over medium heat for 45 minutes, letting mixture boil and stirring constantly. Remove and cool.
Place peach half in dessert dish (you may need to slice small sliver of rounded side of peach half so it will not tip).
Dip ice cream balls ahead on cooled tray to be ready to use.
Spoon an ice cream ball on peach half just before ready to serve.
Spoon cooled berry sauce over ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: oven stew
directions: Layer ingredients in a roaster, casserole dish or baking pan in order listed.
DO NOT MIX.
Cover tightly and bake at 250° for 5 hours.
DO NOT OPEN oven during baking time.
Note:
If desired, remove cover and continue baking 5-10 minutes at 400°-450° to thicken and lightly brown surface vegetables.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Use 3 to 4 pound fryer or broiler, cut up.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, seasoned salt and flour.
Fry in hot fat (oil) until brown on all sides.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Cover tightly and cook over low heat until chicken is tender.
Add more water if necessary during cooking.

title: friendship cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. You may use two loaf pans instead of a Bundt pan.
Do not use an angel food pan! Cake may be frozen.
You may need to lower temperature during the last half of baking.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon until crisp. Remove and saut onion, then return the bacon and add all other ingredients together. Bake in 2 1/2-quart dish at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lime-pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice and cold water.
Place in freezer for 15 to 30 minutes, or until mixture is partially set.
Beat in sour cream.
Fold in bananas, pineapple and walnuts.
Chill until set.

title: cheesy spinach pinwheels
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Unroll dough into 2 long rectangles. Press perforations to seal.
Spread rectangles with cream cheese to within 1/4 inch of edges; top with spinach leaves.
Starting at shortest side, roll up each rectangle.
Press edges to seal.
Cut each roll into 8 slices.
Place cut side down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 18 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm.
Makes 16 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease 2 loaf pans.
Mix all ingredients above. Fill each loaf pan 1/2 full. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: In a small saucepan, melt butter and garlic together.
Wash potatoes and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Put potatoes in a baking dish.
Pour butter and garlic over potatoes.
Sprinkle parsley over top of potatoes.
Bake at 350°, uncovered.
Stir frequently. Can add more butter if potatoes become too dry.
Cook until golden brown and tender.

title: chewy brownie cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat shortening, brown sugar, water and vanilla on medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir together flour, cocoa, salt and baking soda.
Gradually add to sugar mixture, beating on low speed.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 7 to 9 minutes.
Cool on a piece of foil.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Flour and season chicken.
Brown as fried chicken.
Blend together cream of chicken soup and milk.
Pour over fried chicken. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Roll biscuits in sugar and cinnamon.
Line in Bundt pan.
Add leftover sugar and cinnamon on top and top with pecans and coconut.
Melt butter and brown sugar.
Pour over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter in pot; add flour and stir until smooth.
Add salt and pepper; add milk and stir continuously until mixture boils and thickens.
Layer half potatoes and onions and pour half of milk mixture over this.
Layer remaining potatoes and pour remaining mixture over.
Bake 30 minutes covered, then 30 minutes uncovered in 350° oven.

title: scalloped cabbage and eggs
directions: Place layers of cabbage and eggs in a casserole dish, seasoned with salt and pepper and dot with butter.
Make cream sauce using butter (melted); dissolve flour in butter and add milk and blend. Add salt and pepper and cook until thick, stirring constantly. Pour over cabbage and eggs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: layered pudding delight
directions: Line 9-inch square pan with graham crackers, breaking crackers if necessary.
Prepare pudding mix with milk as directed on package.
Let stand 4 to 5 minutes.

title: margaret's chocolate pie
directions: Mix the egg, sugar and flour together and then add the melted chocolate and margarine.
When mixed, add milk and stir until well blended.
Pour mixture in pie shell and add nuts on top; do not stir.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: tijuana pie
directions: Brown meat and add taco seasoning.
Put all canned stuff in saucepan and heat (grease crock-pot).
Start with layer of 1/3 Doritos, 1/3 meat, mix 1/3 sauce and 1/3 cheese.
Continue layers and end with cheese on top.
Put crock-pot on low until cheese is melted.
You may want to add Ranch style beans or whole kernel corn.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Break bread in small pieces and saute in margarine.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Layer ingredients in order given.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lemon broiled chicken
directions: Rub chicken pieces on all sides with cut surface of lemon, squeezing lemon halves to release juice.
Place chicken pieces skin-side down on broiler pan.
Combine salt with paprika and pepper.
Brush chicken with half of melted margarine; sprinkle with half of seasoning mixture.
Broil about 6 inches from heat, 15 to 20 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Turn chicken; brush with remaining margarine and sprinkle with remaining seasoning. Continue broiling 10 to 15 minutes or until chicken is tender.
For a special flavor, sprinkle chicken with sugar 3 minutes before end of broiling time.

title: munchies
directions: Mix together well lemon pepper, dill weed, dressing mix and popcorn oil.
Stir in until well coated crackers.
These are usually smaller than brand name crackers.
Place in airtight container and let stand for 24 hours before serving.

title: homemade bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in small amount of warm water.
Next, add the oil, sugar and salt.
Add the egg and beat with mixer until light. Add the cups of warm water and the flour, 1 to 2 cups at a time. Mix with mixer until dough gets too stiff, then mix with wooden spoon.
Cover and let rise.
Work down and roll it out on a board. Place in pans.
Can be put in refrigerator overnight or let rise and bake at 350°.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: In a large skillet, saute onions and celery in margarine over medium heat.
Cook until vegetables are clear.
Arrange turkey in a layer over onions and celery.
Cover with spaghetti.

title: creamy horseradish dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring vigorously with a spoon until blended.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours.
Serve with vegetables.
Yield:
2 cups.

title: pecan salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Garnish with maraschino cherries.

title: ham glaze
directions: Mix to make a paste.
Put on ham last half hour of baking.

title: baked vegetable omelet
directions: Layer pepper cheese, broccoli, tomatoes and Cheddar in an ungreased 8-inch square baking dish.
Beat together remaining ingredients until smooth; pour over cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until egg mixture is set.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: Mix cream of mushroom soup, onion soup mix and 1/2 can water. Put chicken breast in casserole dish and pour mixture over, coating completely.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for one hour or until tender.

title: elegant chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in shallow 2 to 3-quart casserole. Place 2 slices cheese on each breast.
Stir soup and wine together and spoon evenly over chicken.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: egg casserole
directions: Combine mayonnaise, soup and milk.
Layer eggs and mixture in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with bacon and cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes (covered).
Serve over toasted English muffins.

title: baked stuffed tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash tomatoes, but do not peel.
Cut slice from top of each; scoop out centers and lightly salt insides.
Mix tomato pulp, bacon, celery, onion, bread crumbs, salt and half of cheese.
Fill tomato cavities with mixture. Cover with remaining cheese.
Dot with butter.
Place in greased muffin cups or baking dish.
Bake about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread blueberry pie filling in bottom of dish.
Then add pineapple; add sugar.
Pour dry cake mix over this.
Slice sticks of margarine; place on top of this.
Add pecans and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: strawberry banana torte
directions: Slice cake crosswise into 5 equal layers.
Place 1/4 cup cold water in blender.
Add gelatin and let stand a moment.
Add boiling water; cover and run on low speed until dissolved.
Add cottage cheese, sugar, 1 cup of strawberries and banana; blend on high until smooth.
Fold into whipped cream.
Chill 30 minutes or until mixture starts to thicken.
Spread about 1/2 cup of mixture on each layer, including top of cake.
Chill.
To serve, garnish top of cake and plate with whole berries and banana slices that have been dipped in lemon juice.
Serves 10.

title: microwave caramel corn(paul's favorite)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except soda and popcorn, in a 2-quart bowl.
Bring to a boil in microwave, then cook on High power for 2 minutes.
Remove and stir in soda.
Pour syrup over popped corn in large brown grocery bag; twist shut and shake well.
Cook in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Take out and shake well and cook for another 1 1/2 minutes on High power.
Shake well and dump out on greased cookie sheet.
Keep moving while cooling so will be loose kernels.
Great caramel corn!

title: butter twist sesame cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat after each.
Add baking powder, soda and flavorings.
Add flour and milk.
Knead dough and keep adding flour until dough is fairly stiff.
Knead well and shape as desired.
Brush with egg wash; sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: rice and broccoli
directions: Cook rice and broccoli by directions; drain broccoli.
Melt butter in pan.
Add soup, cheese, garlic, milk, almonds and onions.
In baking dish, mix rice and broccoli, then add other mixture on top and mix in.
You may add ham, chicken or tuna, also green pepper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fish with beer-cheese sauce
directions: Thaw
fish if frozen.
Measure thickness of fish.
In a lightly
greased
x
6 x 2-inch baking dish, arrange fish. (For
fillets,
tuck
under
thin
edges.) Bake in a 450° oven until
fish flakes with a fork.
(Allow 4 to 6 minutes per 1/2 inch thickness of fish.)

title: cherokee casserole
directions: Brown the meat and add onions.
Cook over medium heat until the onion is tender.
Stir in the seasonings, tomatoes, soup, rice and half of the olives.
Simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon into a baking dish and top with cheese strips.
Broil until the cheese is melted and decorate the casserole with the remaining olive slices.
Black olives may be substituted for the green olives.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and press firmly into a loaf dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour basting occasionally.
Drain off excess grease and spread 1/2 cup catsup on top.
Put bake in hot oven for 10 minutes.
(Oven turned off after cooking is hot enough.)

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: turkey salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise with lemon juice, sea salt, marjoram and cayenne.
Mix turkey with dressing and arrange on a large platter with ripe olives and tomato slices.

title: sweet pickle peaches
directions: Cook fruit and sugar until tender; remove from syrup and put vinegar and spices and cook down.
Then add peaches again and boil until hot through, then put in jars and seal.

title: ruby punch
directions: Mix juices and chill.
Add soda water just before serving. Makes 20 servings.

title: fresh apple cake(makes 1 cake)
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, water, oil and vanilla together.
Mix flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon together.
Mix wet and dry ingredients together.
Fold in apples, nuts and raisins.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: banana milkshake
directions: Put all ingredients in mixer.
Blend for 5 minutes.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Empty 2 cans pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix all over pie filling.
Slice butter and bake at 350° until lightly brown (30 to 35 minutes).

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus tips, saving 1/4 cup of the juice.
In a saucepan combine butter, flour, juice and milk.
Cook on low heat until thickened.
In a baking dish, layer 1 cup of asparagus, 1/2 of the sauce and desired amount of cheese.
Repeat layering.
Top with crumbled potato chips.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: crunch bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in large greased pan. Cookie sheet is okay!
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
I check them at 25 minutes.
I don't like them too brown.

title: corn-and-potato casserole
directions: Brown onion, hamburger and garlic; set aside.
Place potato tots in 13 x 9-inch baking dish; top with hamburger mixture, then corn.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: croghan style bologna
directions: Mix all ingredients; let stand in refrigerator 24 hours.
Mix again and mold into round rolls.
Bake at 300° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes on a rack in a shallow pan.

title: pancake mix
directions: Combine and store in cool dry place. Stir before mixing up the following recipe:

title: country fare barbecue glaze
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer covered for 30 minutes.

title: quich
directions: Mix all the ingredients; refrigerate overnight. Next morning, pour over 1 pound cooked sausage or ham. Bake in cake pan 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in lemonade and add 6 cups cold water.
Add cranberry juice.
Put in container and freeze.
Two hours before serving, let thaw until mushy.
Add ginger ale and serve.
Serves 24 to 30 people.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in a mixing bowl.
Add melted butter and beaten eggs and stir with a whisk or fork until well blended.
Stir in buttermilk, vanilla and lemon juice and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and dust with cinnamon or nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until filling is set and lightly browned.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Bake in bread pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: corn light bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake for 40 minutes in a 450° oven.

title: creamed corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in order given and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until top is golden brown in greased 2-quart casserole dish.

title: super pound cake
directions: Cream butter until light.
Cream in sugar and beat until fluffy.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Beat in 1 cup flour, then add extracts and ginger ale alternately until all used.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans (9 x 5-inch) or one 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in preheated 275° oven for about one hour and 45 minutes. (Baking time will be longer for the 10-inch pan.) Test for doneness with a toothpick.
Let cool in pan.

title: father's chili(a quick meal)
directions: Brown and drain ground chuck; add soup (blend soup in blender before adding to meat) and remaining ingredients.
Simmer at least 20 minutes or longer.
Stir often.
Cooked macaroni may be added. Leave cover ajar to thicken.

title: sparkling pineapple ham
directions: Slice ham 1/4 inch thick.
Place slices in a casserole dish, arrange 1/2 pineapple slice between every 2 pieces of ham alternately.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Mix together the soup mix, preserves and Russian dressing.
Let chicken pieces (of your choice) stand in marinade overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350°.
Time varies according to what chicken pieces are used.

title: monkey bread
directions: Use a small Bundt cake pan.
Butter it.
Melt butter; add raisins, cinnamon, sugar and nuts.	Split biscuits; spread halves with butter and cinnamon mixture.
Stand biscuit halves on edge in pan; fill pan in this way.	Put extra on top.
Put in room temperature oven.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Pour glaze on top; serve hot.

title: 3 step cheesecake
directions: Step 1:
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs and mix well.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix white vinegar, sugar and salad oil together in saucepan. Boil 2 minutes and cool.
Mix all remaining ingredients together with sauce.
Chill thoroughly or overnight.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix together 1/2 cup Mandarin orange syrup and 1 1/2 cups of orange juice.
Bring to a boil and pour into Jell-O.
Beat into Jell-O mixture, 1 pint of orange sherbet.
Pour into mold until almost firm, then add Mandarin oranges.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Combine 1st three ingredients; mix until smooth.
Stir in cranberry sauce; add next three ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: pasta al pesto
directions: Place basil, nuts, garlic clove, salt and pepper in a blender and puree. Add cheese and oil; blend for 1 minute. Serve warm over hot spaghetti. Serves 4 and can be frozen.

title: tomato pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in oil.
Add onions.
Add stewed tomatoes and water.
Add soy sauce and bouillon cube.
Cover pan; simmer meat for 45 minutes.
Use leftover tomatoes for side dish.

title: carrot souffle pudding
directions: Cream Spry, add brown sugar and cream together.
Beat in egg yolks.
Add mashed carrots.
Mix in all dry ingredients; add water, lemon juice and vanilla.
Fold beaten egg whites in last. Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Set casserole in a pan of water, bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, test with knife.
Can be frozen and reheated.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix well and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Will be brown.

title: two egg cake
directions: Mix well.
Heat oven to 350°.
Will make 3 layer cake.
Top with favorite frosting.

title: pistachio cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except pistachios.
Blend well.
Form into a ball.
Place pistachios on waxed paper and roll ball in nuts until well covered.
Wrap tightly in plastic wrap and refrigerate for 2 hours or until firm.
Yields 1 cheese ball or 2 cups cheese spread.

title: aunt eliza's corn pudding
directions: Combine
cornstarch
with egg, sugar, cinnamon and milk. Blend in creamed corn.
Pour all in baking dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and
top with pats of butter.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour until firm at 325°.
A delightful main dish!

title: corn squash casserole
directions: Wash and slice squash; cook in 1/2 cup water on medium heat until tender.
Beat egg and add milk; spread about 1/3 cup corn in bottom of greased casserole dish.
Add layer of 1/3 of squash. Sprinkle on part of crumbs, season and add few dots of butter and few spoons of egg mixture.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Pour remaining liquid over all.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.
You can add onions and Cheddar cheese also.

title: easy punch for large group
directions: Heat 1 quart water and sugar together until sugar dissolves. Set aside to cool.
To sugar mixture add pineapple juice and real lemon, then finish filling gallon jug with water to make a gallon. Refrigerate.
When ready to serve pour base into large container. Add 8 cups water and ginger ale.
This will make 3 gallons of punch per gallon of base.
Serve immediately over ice.
Very light colored so can be colored easily.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients, except stick of butter and nuts.
After mixed, place stick of butter on top.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes; stir until smooth, then stir in nuts.
Put in wax papered dish.
Chill in fridge for 1 hour, or place in freezer for 20 minutes.
Take out and slice.

title: coconut pie
directions: To prepare pie crusts:
Cook crusts for half cooking time. Sprinkle crusts with coconut before pouring custard in.
Also, after custard has been poured in, sprinkle with more coconut.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix well.
Cover in casserole dish.
Let cure in refrigerator for 3 days.
When ready to bake, divide into 3 equal long, tubular rolls.
Place on rack in baking casserole pan.
Cover for up to 8 hours to prevent drying.
Bake at 150° for 12 hours.
Turn over after 6 hours.
When done, let cool and wrap in foil.
Keep in refrigerator.
Slice when ready to serve.

title: kale soup
directions: Wash kale and snip leaves, cutting diagonally into wide slices (makes 6 to 7 cups lightly packed).
Wash, peel and chop potatoes. Prick and blanch sausage for 5 to 10 minutes to release fat. Drain and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Saute onions, carrots and garlic in oil and butter until softened.
Add potatoes and broth and simmer, partially covered, until potatoes are cooked.
Mash potatoes against side of pot.
Stir in tomatoes and kidney beans. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Add kale and sausage and cook another 5 to 10 minutes.
Season to taste.

title: helen's egg pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and nutmeg.
Add beaten eggs and oleo. Add hot milk and vanilla.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into small, greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Shred dried beef in blender.
Add to softened cream cheese and horseradish.
Form into a ball.
Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Split Twinkies.
Put half in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding according to directions on package.
Pour half on Twinkies, then add half of crushed candy bars.
Then add remaining Twinkies and vanilla pudding.
Spread Cool Whip on top and remaining crushed candy bars.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: easy pizza pasta
directions: Cook pasta until done.
Brown sausage.
Mix spaghetti sauce, pasta, pepperoni and optional veggies; mix well.
Place 1/2 in cake pan.
Spread cottage cheese over that; top with other half of pasta mixture.
Top off with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake until heated through.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cream, margarine and syrup in heavy cooker. Boil to soft-ball stage, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add vanilla, peanut butter, marshmallow cream and nuts, if desired. Pour into well buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Stir and cook sugar, syrup, water and butter until sugar is dissolved.
Continue to cook without stirring until it forms a hard ball in cold water.
Add vanilla.
Pour over warm popcorn; mix well.
Butter hands to make balls.
Makes 12.

title: new york steak with pepper corn sauce
directions: Rub 1/2 teaspoon black pepper on both sides of each steak. Season steaks with salt, melt butter in heavy skillet over high heat.
Add steaks and cook to desired doneness, about 3 minutes per side for medium rare.
Transfer steaks to plates. Tent with foil to keep warm.

title: dill bread
directions: Measure out half a bag of self-rising flour into large mixing bowl. Add warm water, a cup at a time, until you get where your mixture does not stick to your fingers. Pinch off dinner roll size dough, then flatten on a flour covered surface. You may use a rolling pin if so desired. Fry in 1 inch of hot shortening, preferably in an iron skillet. Fry until golden brown, flipping over, so both sides are even.
Set aside on a paper towel to drain. Top with honey or powdered sugar if desired.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and celery; drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce. Simmer 5 minutes.
Cook macaroni 10 minutes.
Add; pour into Corning Ware dish and top with cheese.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken in water (salted if desired) and let cool in broth.
Remove meat from bone.
Cook spaghetti in broth and drain; reserving liquid.
Mix chicken, spaghetti, peppers, onions and cheese.
Stir well.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms and peas.
If mixture seems dry, reserved liquid may be added.
Divide into casserole dishes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or freeze.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Use coarse blade on grinder.
Combine all vegetables in large bowl; sprinkle with salt.
Cover with cold water.
Let stand 4 hours.
Drain thoroughly in colander; press out all excess liquid.

title: baked ham
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Place ham in baking dish.
Make holes in ham with a fork.
Pour 6 oz. of Coca-Cola, brown sugar, and 1/2 c. water over top of ham.
Bake 40 minutes.
Pour remaining 6 oz. Coca-Cola and 1/2 c. water over ham.
Return to oven and bake an additional 40 minutes.

title: real french chocolate
directions: Melt chocolate, corn syrup, water and vanilla in top of double boiler.
Cool.
Beat cream while adding cooled chocolate, until cream mounds.
Refrigerate.

title: vegetable strata
directions: In greased 13 x 9-inch greased dish, arrange vegetables, then bread and ham.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and melted margarine; press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix powdered sugar, softened margarine and eggs together until fluffy. Spread over crust. Spread pineapple over filling; arrange banana slices over pineapple. Spread whipped topping over bananas. Top with chopped nuts; garnish with cherries.

title: easy chocolate pudding
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add milk and cook until it thickens and bubbles, 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.

title: macaroni dill salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain and cool.
In a large bowl, combine macaroni, chopped eggs, onions, chopped pickles and olives.
In a separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients, blending well.
Pour over macaroni mixture.
Mix.
Cover and chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, salt and nuts.
Shape into logs and about 1-inch in diameter.
Wrap in wax paper and chill overnight in refrigerator.
Heat oven to 375°. Slice cookies about 1/4-inch thick.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Add water, sour cream, eggs, chocolate and vanilla; mix until well blended. Pour into two 8-inch round pans (lightly greased).
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
Use icing of your choice.

title: quick easy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together, put into an ungreased loaf pan. Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Serves four.

title: sweet potato
directions: Place pineapple around casserole dish.
Place sweet potatoes in center of dish.
Make sauce with brown sugar, pineapple juice and oleo.
Bring to a boil and pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle marshmallows over top of dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Sprinkle ingredients with salt. Let set about 5 to 10 minutes; drain. Put in large pot and add sugar. Bring to a boil; cook for 4 or 5 minutes. Add vinegar and continue to cook over low heat until thick. Pack in clean jars and seal. Makes 2 to 3 pints.

title: cinnamon flop
directions: Mix all ingredients together, dust flour on top of batter. Then dot with brown sugar and butter.
Put in a greased 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Put peanut butter, oatmeal, coconut and nuts in a separate bowl. Bring first 6 ingredients to a bowl, then take off heat and mix into dry ingredients. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper and let set up.

title: mexican corn
directions: In bowl, combine corn, Bisquick mix, egg, butter, sugar and milk and mix well.
Turn one-half of batter mix into well-greased 8 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Cover with chilies then cheese slices on top of chilies.
Spread remaining batter on top.
Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: sugar-free cocoa press cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, egg and vanilla in large bowl.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, cocoa and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Fill cookie press with dough.
Press cookies onto a cool, ungreased cookie sheet (or drop by spoonfuls).
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes or until set.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: chili
directions: Mix all ingredients into large soup pot, except tomatoes. Cover ingredients with water.
Puree tomatoes in blender.
Add to mixture.
Simmer on low heat for 2 hours.

title: flavorful beef roast
directions: Place the roast on
large sheet of aluminum foil.
Sprinkle the onion soup over the roast.
Pour the mushroom soup on top, covering the entire roast.
Cover with the foil.
Bake at 325° for 3 1/2 hours.

title: corn - southern style
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Turn into well buttered pudding dish.
Bake until firm in a slow oven and serve hot.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook and debone chicken; cut into small pieces and set aside. In the chicken broth, cook spaghetti until there is very little broth left.
Saute onion and celery until soft.
Add chicken, spaghetti and onion/celery mix together with tomatoes, olives, seasonings and soup.
Chop cheese into pieces and mix into spaghetti mixture.
Bake or freeze until needed.
Bake in 350° oven about 35 or 40 minutes until the casserole is really bubbly hot and all the cheese has melted.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheese straws
directions: Sift flour, pepper and baking powder.
Cut in cheese and oleo; add water and mix well.
Put in cookie press using star plate. Form straws.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Let cool before adding to cake mix.
Add eggs, oil, 3/4 cup strawberries and flour.
Mix well and pour into 3 prepared cake pans (9-inch pans) and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: moist oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Cover raisins with water and cook until tender.
Add soda to 9 tablespoons of raisin liquid.
Sift dry ingredients.
Alternate dry ingredients with raisin liquid mixture; add to sugar and shortening.
Mix well.
Add raisins.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter and bake approximately 45 minutes. If mixture is too dry, add water or chicken broth.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate, peanut butter and butter in microwave for 1 minute.
Mix together and pour over cereal.
Pour sugar over mix and put lid over bowl; shake.

title: rancho sausage supper
directions: In a large skillet, fry sausage and drain.
Add onions and green pepper.
Cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, sour cream, macaroni, chili powder, salt and sugar.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring frequently until macaroni is done.
Serve hot.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring often, adding Parmesan cheese as desired.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Mix water and salt in saucepan and bring to boil.
Stir in cornmeal and cook, stirring continually to prevent lumps, for one minute.
Remove from heat.
Add butter or margarine and beat well. Stir in eggs, then milk, beating well after each addition.
Pour into a hot greased 12-inch square baking dish.
Bake in 425° preheated oven for 25 minutes.
(This is soooo good and is even better if eaten straight out of the oven.)

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread.
Dig out center of bread and tear into bite-size pieces.
Pour dip into center of hollowed-out loaf and place bread pieces around bread loaf.

title: sinfully rich cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool slightly. Make large holes all over (handle of wooden spoon works well). Pour condensed milk over the warm cake, not hot.
Pour ice cream topping over warm cake; cool.
Spread Cool Whip over cake.
Break candy bars into small bits; sprinkle over top and serve.
Freeze. Skor bars break up easier.

title: key lime cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth, use hand mixer.
Pour into lightly greased pan, 2 x 8 x 8-inch or 1 x 13 x 9-inch.
Bake about 40 minutes at 325°.

title: delicious pork chops in gravy
directions: Rub chops with salt and pepper.
Place in heated skillet with tight fitting lid. Melt enough butter to keep chops from sticking. Combine soup and water.
Pour over chops.
Re-cover.
Reduce heat to very low and cook slowly for 1 hour. Serves 4.

title: solyanka
directions: Approximately 1 1/4 hours preparation time, including baking.

title: white chocolate pretzels
directions: Melt almond bark in microwave for 1 minute and if needed melt at 30 second intervals until melted.
Dip pretzels in almond bark; lay on wax paper.
Decorate if desired.

title: easy cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa and baking soda.
Add salad dressing and water.
Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: rice pilaf
directions: In large nonstick frying pan, heat oil.
Brown garlic and onion.
Add rice and cinnamon stick; stir.
Add celery, carrots and garbanzos; keep stirring.
Add basil, sesame seed, salt and pepper.
Keep stirring, until celery and carrots are soft.

title: corned beef spread
directions: Mash corned beef and mix with cream cheese and other ingredients.
Serve on bread or crackers.

title: prune whip
directions: Cook prunes until tender, remove pits.
Add sugar and egg whites, beaten stiff. Put in a shallow baking dish and bake in a moderate oven until light brown.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and cocoa together; gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens and boils; boil 1 minute.
Remove from
heat.
Gradually stir 1/2 of hot mixture into beaten egg yolks.
Return all to saucepan.
Boil one minute more, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, add butter and vanilla.
Pour immediately into nine-inch baked pie shell. Spread meringue over hot filling, sealing to edges of crust.
Bake at 400° about 8 to 10 minutes.
Use meringue recipe with lemon pie.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans and parsley.
Form into a ball.
Roll ball in crushed pecans and dried parsley flakes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook beans; drain and place in buttered casserole.
Add tuna chunks and soup diluted with milk.
Top with dressing and dot with butter.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: southern bell alcoholic punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except 7-Up.
Do not dilute frozen juices. Add 7-Up last.
Makes 1 full punch bowl.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Break eggs over apples; add sugar, cinnamon, oil, raisins and nuts. Mix. Sift flour, salt and soda into apple mixture and mix well. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and water; mix well.
Mix together baking soda, salt and flour; blend well.
Add nuts, vanilla and chips.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: hickory smoked barbecue chicken
directions: Combine liquid smoke and water in a shallow dish.
Add chicken and marinate for 15 minutes, turn chicken and marinate other side for 15 minutes.
Remove chicken from marinade.
Drain and place in baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, in 325°
oven for 45 to 50 minutes. Dip or brush chicken with barbecue sauce.
Bake in 350°
oven for 15 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat eggs and margarine.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350° until done in center.
Mixture will appear soupy before baking.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix together apples, 1/3 cup sugar, cinnamon, salt and melted butter.
Place in greased 8-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar and flour.
Cut in 1/3 cup butter until crumbly. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done. Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: fruit cocktail
directions: Any one fruit may be used for a cocktail, or a mixture of two or more.

title: cranberry sparkler punch
directions: Mix well.
Chill and serve.
Add ice ring or crushed ice. Serves about 10.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: Mix spices into cottage cheese.
Layer in a casserole lightly oiled the noodles, cottage cheese, spinach, tomatoes, onion and cottage cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 325°F. for about 30 minutes.

title: smoky crescents(makes 24)
directions: Cut sausage links in half, making 24 short links.
Unroll crescent dough and spread it out flat.
Cut the 8 triangles lengthwise into 3 triangles each.
This will give you 24 long, thin triangles of dough.

title: cheesy milano lasagna rolls
directions: Mix cheeses, spinach, shrimp and crab together.
Season with salt and pepper.
Lay noodles out on work surface.
Spread even layer of filling on each; roll up.
Place in 9 x 11-inch baking pan.
Pour sauce over.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Yields 12 servings.

title: boiled cake
directions: Boil together for 5 minutes the raisins, sugar, water and Crisco.
Add eggs, salt, baking soda and flour.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: country club punch
directions: Boil the sugar and water together for 8 minutes.
Add the tea, then chill.
Add oranges, lemons, grape juice and pineapple. Place in refrigerator to mellow for about 2 hours.
Before serving, add 2 quarts of ginger ale and ice cubes.
For small parties this recipe can be divided into thirds.
If served in a punch bowl, add quarter slices of oranges and lemons and one small bottle of maraschino cherries.
Serves about 50.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and chop the frozen spinach; drain well.
Add Parmesan cheese, stuffing mix, butter and eggs.
Mix and shape into balls. Put on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hill billy casserole
directions: Cook noodles and brown hamburger.
Layer in casserole dish all ingredients, ending with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: seafood dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: cherry berry coffeecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Generously grease jelly roll pan or 2 (9-inch) square pans. Blend sugar, butter, shortening, baking powder, vanilla, almond extract and eggs in large mixing bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly. Beat 3 minutes on high speed. Stir in flour. Spread 2/3 of batter in jelly roll pan or 1/3 in each square pan. Spread pie filling over batter; sprinkle lemon rind over cherries. Drop remaining batter by tablespoonfuls onto pie filling. Bake about 45 minutes. Drizzle with glaze.

title: watergate salad
directions: Chop
up cherries and drain pineapple.
In a large bowl, mix together Cool Whip, pistachio pudding, marshmallows, coconut, cherries and 1/2 cup pecans.
After mixing together all of the ingredients, sprinkle remaining pecans on top and garnish with a whole cherry.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes before serving.

title: green tomato bread
directions: Beat eggs well.
Then add oil, sugar, salt, vanilla and green tomatoes.
Sift dry ingredients and add gradually to green tomato mixture.
Add raisins and nutmeats.
Stir.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: easy frozen dessert
directions: Mix and freeze in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: quick ham skillet dinner
directions: Stuff into maw and fasten all openings.
Place in oven roaster with small amount of water in bottom.
Roast at 350° for 2 hours. When top side has browned, turn over and brown other side.
Slice to serve.

title: spinach phyllo pizza
directions: Cook spinach covered with water for 3 to 4 minutes, until wilted.
Rinse in cold water and drain.
Heat oven to 400°. Brush baking sheet with butter; put 1 sheet of phyllo on baking sheet and cover with butter.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon Parmesan; cover with next sheet of phyllo.
Press together and repeat, ending with phyllo sheet.
Bake for 5 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: In bowl tear spinach leaves in bite size pieces, combine rest of veggies.
Mix dressing per instructions on package.
Toss dressing in salad.
Before serving squeeze some fresh lemon over salad.

title: chew bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° in 13 x 9-inch pan for 35 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Saute the ground beef until you remove the reddish out of it. Drain. Add the rice, tomato paste and seasoning. Trim core of center of cabbage. Insert whole head in boiling water for wilting to make leaves come out one by one and easy to roll.
Drain and separate leaves. Cut off coarse ribs, enough to roll easily.
Put about 1 tablespoon in half of a large leaf or use large leaf and put about 2 tablespoons.
Line boiler with 2 or 3 leaves or some of the coarse ribs that have been taken off to prevent scorching. Lay cabbage rolls evenly, layer after layer.

Add about 4 cups water mixed with a small can of tomato sauce and salt as desired. Add enough water to cover cabbage rolls and cook, covered, at medium heat until it boils, then you finish cooking on low heat until done.
It's best to cover cabbage rolls with foil paper so that they will stay down.
It usually takes about 45 minutes or so. Check occasionally to see if done.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender, do not overcook.
Rinse and carefully mix with remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill before serving.

title: shrimp and spinach linguine
directions: Place sausage in medium skillet; add water, cover and simmer until water has evaporated.
Remove cover and brown sausage on all sides.

title: broccoli slaw
directions: Cut up green onions and mix with broccoli slaw. Crush up Ramen noodles. Mix with sunflower seeds and almonds. Separately mix oil, sugar, vinegar and Ramen noodles seasoning. Shake. When ready to serve, mix everything together.

title: venison goulash
directions: Brown meat in oil; stir constantly.
Add 1 cup wine and stir well.
Add onions, Tabasco, spices and seasonings.
Cook slowly, adding remaining wine.
May add water or stock juice.
Keep tightly covered and cook 4 to 5 hours, adding mushrooms last 1/2 hour.

title: chocolate pudding fudge
directions: Combine pudding mix, sugar, brown sugar and milk.
Blend well and cook over low heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Continue cooking without stirring to a full boil.
Boil 3 minutes. Remove from heat and add 3 tablespoons butter.
Beat at once until thickened, about 12 minutes.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5-inch pan and chill.

title: naomi's revel bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch pan. Cream the 1 cup margarine and sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs; beat until light.
Blend in vanilla.
Combine flour and baking soda. Stir into creamed mixture.
Blend in oats.
Spread 3/4 of oat mixture evenly in prepared pan.
Combine chocolate chips, milk and 2 tablespoons margarine in small heavy saucepan.
Stir over low heat until chocolate is melted.
Pour chocolate mixture evenly over mixture in pan.
Dot with remaining oat mixture.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are browned and center feels firm.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Cut into 2 x 1 1/2-inch bars.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: german sweet chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate with butter over low heat, stirring until blended.
Remove from heat.
Gradually blend in milk.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt thoroughly.
Beat eggs and vanilla into dry mixture.
Gradually blend in chocolate mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Combine nuts and coconut; sprinkle over filling.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until puffed and brown.
Filling will be soft but will set while cooling.
Cool at least 4 hours.

title: sweet and sour beef stew
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, brown meat in hot oil; drain excess oil and add remaining ingredients, except cold water and cornstarch. Cover and cook in low heated oven until meat is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Blend cold water with cornstarch; add to stew.
Cook and stir until thick.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown beef and onion together; drain well.
Add cooked bacon. Add all beans.
Mix together brown sugar, granulated sugar, catsup, salt, dry mustard and vinegar.
Mix all ingredients together, gently and thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or cook in crock-pot slowly for hours.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix together zucchini, onion, biscuit mix, eggs, oil, cheese, marjoram, parsley, salt and pepper until zucchini is evenly coated. Pour into buttered 12-inch pie plate or an oblong dish (10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch). Bake until golden.

title: thomas & edna brunswick stew
directions: Cook pork and hens until tender, separately.
Then debone and chop to medium fine.
Reserve broth.
Use was pot to cook.
Pour 1 1/2 gallons of broth in pot.
Add ground chuck, chopped hens, and pork loin chopped up.
Cook until ground chuck is done.
Add corn and lima beans to the mixture, stirring constantly, until mixture begins to thicken.
Add tomatoes that have been crushed (may be canned or fresh).
Begin adding the other ingredients, adding salt to taste.
Cook slowly for several hours until thick.
Usually around 5 hours to cook.
This may be canned or frozen.
Lots of tasting to get to the right stage.
If mixture becomes too thick, add more reserved broth.
Must be cooked very slow to prevent sticking.

title: linguine with fresh tomato sauce
directions: Chop tomatoes.
Add oil and basil.
Add garlic.
Toss with hot pasta.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: chicken-broccoli-pasta dish
directions: Heat olive oil; add garlic and chicken pieces.
Cook until chicken turns white.
Push chicken to one side of skillet.
Add fresh broccoli flowerets and cook a few minutes, stirring.
Add basil, salt, pepper, dried tomatoes, red pepper flakes, wine and chicken broth.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Thicken juices with 1 tablespoon cornstarch in a little cold water.
Cook 5 minutes, until juices thicken, stirring.
Meanwhile, cook 2 cups bowtie pasta noodles in boiling salted water for 10 to 12 minutes; drain. Add cooked pasta to chicken and stir to combine.
Serves 4.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Place tomatoes in casserole dish.
Toast bread; crumble to crouton size.
Put all remaining ingredients in dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 4 bean dish
directions: Add to ingredients.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: fresno fritters
directions: Blend egg and milk.
Add pancake mix, stirring just enough to blend.
Fold in corn and raisins.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil. Cook until golden brown, about 4 minutes.
Drain on paper towels. Serve warm with butter and syrup for breakfast or as a side dish. Makes 24-30.

title: gift-wrapped ham
directions: Cut out corners of pie crust to form a cross.
Brush with egg and sprinkle with parsley, mustard and sage.
Set ham on cross and fold up sides to cover ham.
Pinch to seal edges.
Brush with egg. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Put each item in layers, starting with lettuce and ending with the cheese.
Cook peas, drain and cool.
Cook bacon.
Cool and crumble.
Do not toss.
Let set 12 hours.
Will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: mayonnaise chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Bake in 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Frost with your favorite icing.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla until creamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Add all dry ingredients and nuts.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pans.

title: microwave baked beans
directions: Microwave meat on High along with the onion and pepper for 10 minutes; drain meat.
Add beans, catsup, mustard and brown sugar. Microwave 20 to 30 minutes on Roast setting, stirring 2 or 3 times.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add baking powder and baking soda to flour and sift together.
Alternate dry ingredients and buttermilk; stir mixture until blended.
Chill, covered, for 30 minutes or longer.

title: cranberry mold(if you don't have fresh cranberries)
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve syrup; add water to make 1/2 cup. Dissolve gelatin and sugar in 1 cup boiling water.
Add lemon juice and syrup.
Chill until partially set.
Add fruit, celery and nuts.
Chill in 5 cup ring overnight.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: jessica's meat loaf
directions: Mix together and add 2 eggs, crackers, etc.
(anything you like in meat loaf).
Place into a 12 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: carrot surprise
directions: Wash and cut carrots into small pieces.
Place cut carrots into large pan.
Cover with water.
Boil slowly until carrots become soft.
Place cooked carrots into blender, a little at a time, and blend until mixture looks like pudding.
If blender is full, pour out about half into a casserole dish.
To the amount left in blender, add all other ingredients, except sugar, into blender.
Blend until all ingredients are well mixed.
Pour mixture out of blender into casserole dish with other mix.
Stir all together and add sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or firm in middle.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt margarine, add sugar, vanilla and milk. Bring to a boil and cook for 4 minutes. Leave on heat.
Add marshmallow cream and peanut butter until melted.
Remove from heat and beat by hand until thick.
Pour into a buttered platter.
Cool, cut and serve.

title: glaze for pecans
directions: Boil together 1 minute.
Remove from fire.
Add 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar, 1 teaspoon vanilla.
To this, add 4 cups pecan halves.
Pour out on wax paper and separate.

title: chile rellenos casserole
directions: Layer chiles, then cheese in oblong pan or baking dish. Blend eggs, milk, Bisquick and seasonings together.
Pour over chiles.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Bake at 375° (400° at higher altitudes).

title: punch
directions: Mix water, jello and lemon juice up ahead, but don't refrigerate
because it will jell.
For ice mold, use water and a red food coloring with piece of holly in it.
Makes 11 quarts.

title: flan
directions: Bake sugar in the bottom of a 6-cup mold until caramelized. Coat bottom and sides; set aside.

title: chicken 'n' dumplings
directions: In covered pot fill halfway with water, let boil.
Add chicken (parboil), don't overcook.
Put chicken aside to cool (debone). Should have 1/2 pot hot water.
Add onion, pepper, celery, poultry seasoning, packages and cubes of broth.
Cook until celery is done. Add cornstarch (mix with water to make paste).
Cook 5 to 10 minutes to a gravy-like state.
Add potatoes.
Cook 10 minutes. Add chicken.
Cook approximately 15 minutes.
Add carrots, 5 minutes.
Shut off.
Add peas.
Place in oven (large casserole dish or lasagne pan).

title: salami stacks
directions: Spread one slice of salami with cream cheese and top with another salami slice.
Spread with cream cheese and continue layering in this manner, ending with a salami slice.
Refrigerate until firm, then cut through all layers in thin pie-shaped wedges. Top each wedge with a toothpick which has been speared with an olive or a bite-size piece of cheese.
Easy for kids to do as long as you help small ones with the slicing.

title: cordon bleu(german)
directions: Flatten steaks to 1/4-inch thickness.
On each of 6 steaks, place 1 slice ham, 1 slice cheese, then another slice ham, trimming ham and cheese to make smaller than pork steak.
Cover with remaining steak.
Press edges together to seal.
Season both sides of pork.
In shallow bowl, beat eggs and milk together.
Dip pork with egg mixture, then coat completely with bread crumbs. Heat 1/2-inch oil in skillet.
Cook coated pork in hot oil until golden brown.
Put in large baking pan.
Finish cooking in 325° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve with tossed salad.

title: white bean and tuna salad
directions: Cook bacon; reserve 1/4 cup bacon drippings (drain bacon on paper towel).
Process reserve bacon drippings, salt, pepper, cider vinegar, onion, honey and mustard in processor.
Heat in pan, stirring or in microwave.
Line salad plates with greens and arrange items over greens.
Drizzle with dressing.
Serve immediately.

title: christmas spice cake
directions: Boil water, Crisco and raisins 5 minutes; set aside to cool. Mix together in a large bowl the flour, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, allspice, baking soda and salt.
When water, Crisco and raisins mix have cooled, add to flour mixture; stir in 3 eggs, one at a time, then add 1 cup chopped nuts.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°. Use a greased tube cake pan.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Place cooked macaroni or noodles in greased casserole dish. Add tuna, vegetables and half of the cheese.
Then add soup and mix lightly.
Put remaining cheese on top.
Bake in buttered casserole 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Soften jello in 1/2 cup water.
Combine other ingredients and blend all together with electric mixer at least four minutes. Bake, in three nine-inch layers, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: devil burgers
directions: Make patties from mixture.
Wrap a bacon strip around each patty.
Broil 15 minutes each side.

title: three-day yeast rolls
directions: Roll out package of crescent rolls (Grands preferred). Take marshmallows and roll in melted butter.
Then roll marshmallows in cinnamon and sugar.
Place a marshmallow in each crescent roll. Seal along seam.
Bake in moderate oven until brown.

title: cabbage baked with sausage
directions: Add salt, caraway seed and some water to finely shredded cabbage and simmer briefly.
Cut bacon into cubes and melt; add finely chopped onion.
Allow to become golden, then add strained cabbage, diced sausage, pickles and crushed garlic.
Finally, add slices of peeled potatoes.
Add some oil and place into a greased dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Put the sugar and flour in a bowl.
Put the oleo, Crisco, cocoa and 1 cup water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add to flour and sugar; mix well.
Add the buttermilk, soda, vanilla, eggs and cinnamon.
Mix and bake for 20 minutes.
Five minutes before cake is done, start icing.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: salmon teriyaki
directions: Blend well together all ingredients, except salmon.
Put salmon in large plastic storage bag or container with a cover; pour marinade over salmon.
Marinate in refrigerator for about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Turn over bag or container every 45 minutes. Drain and broil on each side until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Serves 4.

title: wisconsin cheese and sausage fondue
directions: Melt butter in heavy chafing dish or in skillet on stove and press garlic clove in it.
Remove garlic and slowly add white wine, alternating with the grated cheese.
As cheese melts, add more cheese and wine until all is dissolved.
Add cornstarch and white pepper, stirring constantly, until ready to serve.
Cut French bread and sausage so that each bite size piece has crust casing on it.
Dip and eat.

title: crab cakes
directions: Pick over crab and discard any pieces of cartilage.
Combine the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Add crab and mix well. Form into 4 cakes and put on a baking sheet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Cover and refrigerate for at least1 hour.
Cook 6 inches below a preheated broiler until hot and tops are golden brown.

title: peanut brittle
directions: First, grease 2 cookie sheets and set aside.

title: crazy slaw
directions: Mix slaw mix, Ramen noodles and chopped green onions.
Toast butter, sunflower seeds and slivered almonds.
Add 30 minutes before serving the sugar, oil and vinegar.

title: tri-tip marinade
directions: Place onion and beef tip in resealable plastic bag or glass dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour marinade over tri-tip beef mixture and place in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Turn beef occasionally.
Barbecue on medium heat until tri-tip is medium rare.

title: aunt mame's rhubarb relish
directions: Cook rhubarb and onions in vinegar until soft.
Add remaining ingredients; boil until thickened.
Seal in hot jars.
Very tasty accompaniment for cold meats and cheese.

title: chilled berry soup
directions: Place berries and 1/4 cup water in blender; puree until smooth.
In large saucepan, combine pureed fruit, remaining 1 1/4 cups water, cranberry juice, sugar, cinnamon stick and cloves. Cook over medium heat until mixture begins to boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool.

title: red beet jelly
directions: Mix juices and Sure-Jell and bring to a boil.
Add sugar and raspberry jello.
Boil for several more minutes.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: *baked stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Remove bones from chicken breasts; place breasts, skin side down, and pound until thin.
Prepare stuffing mix according to directions on package.
Put about 2 tablespoons of stuffing on each piece of chicken and fold sides and ends over.
Place, seam side down, in baking dish.
Spread soup over the top of the chicken.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
(No salt is needed in this recipe.) Serves 4 to 6.

title: hurry up meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, 1/2 cup tomato sauce, bread crumbs, egg, onion flakes, salt and pepper; mix well.
Shape meat mixture into 4 individual loaves; place in a lightly greased baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients (tomato sauce, brown sugar, parsley flakes and Worcestershire sauce).
Mix well and pour over loaves.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: snow peas
directions: In a heavy skillet, melt the butter.
Add the potatoes and fry over medium heat until golden and crisp.
Add the snow peas, onion and salt and fry for 5 to 7 minutes, until the peas are crisp and tender.

title: louisiana fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Yields 12 servings.

title: microwave candy
directions: In microwave bowl, combine chocolate chips and peanut butter chips.
Microwave for 2 1/2 minutes on High.
Stir until smooth. Add pecan pieces.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Let cool and enjoy.

title: monkey bread
directions: You will need 1 greased Bundt pan.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine egg, oil and milk.
Add dry ingredients all at once. Stir quickly just to moisten.
Gently fold in fresh or frozen blueberries.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° about 25 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1 cup of cracker crumbs to sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook and drain squash and onion.
Beat eggs.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream together sugar and oil.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift together flour, baking soda and baking powder. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, alternating with zucchini.
Stir in vanilla and cinnamon.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Use 1 to 3 tablespoons to taste, mixed with warm milk.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix soups and water. Add rice, green peppers and onions. Season chicken with salt, pepper and paprika. Roll in melted butter.
Pour soup mixture in large casserole dish and arrange chicken on top. Do not cover. Bake at 325° for about 2 hours.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: In a large saucepan, brown sausage and drain. Remove half and set aside. Stir tomato sauce, paste, water and brown sugar into sausage in saucepan. Simmer 15 minutes.

title: do ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Beat in remaining ingredients. Adjust seasonings.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Cool, cover and refrigerate.
Make at least 24 hours ahead.
Keeps up to 2 weeks.

title: swedish pecans
directions: Heat pecans thoroughly.
Whip egg whites and salt. Add sugar gradually.
Mix nuts and egg whites.
Drop into pan which butter has been melted.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: one crust chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Heat 1/3 cup butter in a 2-quart saucepan over low heat until melted.
Stir in 1/2 cup Bisquick, onion and pepper.
Cook over low heat until bubbly.
Stir in broth and milk. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute. Stir in chicken and frozen vegetables and heat through.
Keep warm over low heat.

title: lemon-almond wafers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Use ungreased cookie sheets.
Beat margarine and sugar with electric mixer until fluffy.
Beat in egg, then vanilla.
Gradually stir in flour until blended.
Stir in lemon peel.
Drop heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Gently press a few sliced almonds into center of each. Bake 8 to 10 minutes until edges are golden brown.
Cool on sheet 1 to 2 minutes, then remove to wire rack to cool completely.

title: pistachio cheese cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add oleo on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Mix occasionally to get oleo and rest of ingredients mixed thoroughly.
Press in pie plate.
Save 1/2 cup for topping.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Wash and place chicken in large shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle rice over the chicken (uncooked).
Add soups and water and bake 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.
Serves 5 to 6 people.

title: easy fruit cake
directions: Boil together raisins or currants, apple, rind and juice of lemon or orange and cranberry juice 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add butter or margarine, eggs, glazed fruit and walnuts.
Sift together flour, sugar, salt, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and allspice.
In large bowl, mix all ingredients well.
Put in greased and floured deep baking pan.
Bake at 325° for about 2 hours or test with toothpick.
(Will keep a long time stored in a sealed tin.)

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni by directions and cool.
Chop onion, celery, bell pepper, sweet pickle and parsley in food processor.
Add shredded Cheddar cheese and ham, cut in small pieces.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a 2-quart casserole.
Spread croutons on top and dot with butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: crocked swiss steak
directions: Cut round steak in half and season with salt and pepper. Place onion slices in crock-ette.
Place meat on top of onion. Pour tomato sauce over all.
Cover and cook for 8 to 10 hours.

title: hot pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers; add vinegar and sugar.
Boil slowly 10 minutes. Add liquid pectin.
Boil hard 1 minute.
Put in half pint jars.

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mix with pistachio pudding mix.
Add Cool Whip, marshmallows and pecans.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: homemade potato soup
directions: Put all ingredients in a 4-quart pan, except milk.
Bring to a boil, then turn heat down and simmer until vegetables are done. Add milk last.

title: lemon carrots
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place carrots in ungreased baking pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Mix butter, lemon juice and salt; drizzle over carrots.
Cover; bake 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole dish and put cracker crumbs with melted butter on top.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes or until it starts to bubble at 350°.

title: french fried mushrooms
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Combine eggs, oil and water, mixing well.
Dredge mushrooms in flour mixture and dip in egg mixture; roll in bread crumbs.
Refrigerate at least 1 1/2 hours. Deep fry mushrooms in hot oil (375°) until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: holly farm taters
directions: Place all ingredients and potatoes in brown bag.
Shake to coat potatoes.
Place in dish or on a cookie sheet.
Pour melted butter over and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco into dry ingredients until it's mealy; add water, vinegar and beaten egg.
Roll out on floured board.
Makes enough for four 2-crust pies (depending on size).

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour butter into a shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Set aside and drain peaches, reserving 1/4 cup juice in a saucepan.
Bring the peaches and juice to a boil.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Put all ingredients in saucepan and place over low heat until oleo is melted.
Do not boil.

Put 1 cut-up fryer in baking dish and place in oven at 350° to 400° until chicken begins to dry out. Spoon hot sauce over meat; continue baking, turning chicken and coating each piece several times until meat is done.
Serve with rice; leftover sauce may be used for gravy.

title: dilled onions
directions: Slice onions in rings and separate each one.
Place in large neck jar or bowl that can be covered.
Make brine of sugar, salt, vinegar and water.
Bring to rolling boil for 2 to 3 minutes. Cool and pour over onion rings.
Cover and let stand overnight or longer in refrigerator.
Stir or shake them every once in a while.

title: black forest cake
directions: Combine pie filling and almond extract; stir well and set aside.
Combine sugar and oil in a large bowl, beating at medium speed.
Add melted chocolate; beat well.
Add egg whites and beat well.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Mix well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Reserve 2 cups of batter and set aside.
Pour remaining batter into 12-cup Bundt pan coated with cooking spray. Spoon pie filling into center of batter to form a ring.
Top with reserved batter.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Toothpick should come out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then remove.
Cool on wire rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate mint cookies
directions: Melt butter, sugar and water over low heat.
Add chocolate chips and stir until partly melted.
Remove from heat and stir until completely melted.
Pour into large bowl.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Beat eggs at high speed.
Reduce speed and add dry ingredients.
Chill 1 hour.

title: chicken and noodles casserole
directions: Cut chicken in small pieces.
Place in a buttered casserole with cooked noodles.
Mix broth (which may be slightly thickened) with chicken soup and cheese.
Pour over chicken and noodles. Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: round steak casserole
directions: Tenderize and pound the steak.
Cut up in individual pieces. Cut up garlic; salt and pepper.
Put soups on top of meat.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
(Makes delicious gravy for mashed potatoes or pasta.)

title: brown sugar banana bread
directions: Beat margarine, applesauce, eggs, milk, and brown sugar in large bowl until smooth.
Add bananas and blend at low speed; beat on high speed 1-2 minutes.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt mix into batter.
Mix in nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55-60 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into baked pie shell. Place in refrigerator and chill 2 hours.
May sprinkle additional pecans on top; food coloring can also be added for more color in filling.

title: asparagus roll-ups
directions: *There are 7 pieces in each package; this should equal 1 slice of ham for every 2 pieces of asparagus.

title: best-ever pecan pie
directions: Line pastry shell with pecans. Set aside. Blend sugar, salt, corn syrup and vanilla. Beat in eggs, one at a time, mixing well. Pour mixture over pecans and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted in center of pie comes out clean. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Flour nuts with 1/2 cup flour mixture. Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes or until done.

title: six fruit crisp
directions: Pour applesauce into greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish. Layer with pineapple, peaches, pears and oranges.
Spread with pie filling.

title: hawaiian meatballs
directions: Mix together ground beef, onions, salt, crackers and milk. Roll into small balls.
Roll in flour and brown in skillet with hot oil.
As they finish browning, remove and place in baking dish. Drain pineapple, reserving the liquid and add water to make 1 cup.

title: fruit slush mix
directions: Combine sugar and water in a medium saucepan.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add orange juice concentrate, lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Stir.
Fill 6 or 7 ice cube trays with mixture. Freeze until firm.
Remove cubes from trays and store in plastic bags in freezer.
Use within 6 months.
Makes about 100 small cubes.

title: broccoli rotini
directions: Cook rotini pasta according to directions on package; drain. Saute garlic and basil in oil in a nonstick skillet for 1 minute. Add parsley, broccoli, chicken broth, pepper and Parmesan cheese. Cook and stir until mixture is heated.
Remove from heat, stir in low-fat cottage cheese; add rotini to broccoli mixture, toss together.
Makes 4 servings.

title: party sloppy joes
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef, onion, celery and green pepper; drain fat.
Add all remaining ingredients, except cheese and buns; cook for 10 minutes.
Stir in cheese; cook until melted. Serve on buns.
Yields 50.

title: my own dressing
directions: Shake ingredients together in a bottle.
Just use enough to moisten any kind of macaroni, vegetable or green salad; refrigerate the rest.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter, sugars (white and brown), eggs and vanilla.
Sift all dry ingredients together and add to mixture. Roll in log.
Put in refrigerator.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Remove. Cut into slices.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water; bring undiluted soup to a boil and combine with gelatin.
Chop celery and onion in blender or food processor.
Add all ingredients, except shrimp, and blend.
Stir in shrimp.
Pour into 1-quart mold.
Chill. Unmold and serve with crackers.

title: cream cheese dainties
directions: Cream oleo, cream cheese, sugar and flavoring.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to cream mixture.
Roll in balls and roll in cereal.
Bake for 12 minutes.

title: beef rolls
directions: Will also need toothpicks.

title: lemon cheese cake dessert
directions: In a bowl, cut butter into flour until crumbly. Press into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 18 to 22 minutes or until set. Cool.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Combine the cream cheese, sugar, egg and lemon juice.
Beat well.
Line a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan with 1 package crescent rolls still intact.
Pour cream cheese mixture over rolls and then cover with second package of crescent rolls.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.
Cool overnight and cut into squares.

title: danny's mother's "original fruitcake"
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add unbeaten eggs slowly, mixing well.
Add candied fruits, nuts and orange juice.
Sift together flour, baking powder, spices and salt.
Fold into first mixture. Mix thoroughly.
Bake in well-greased, paper-lined 10 x 6 x 4-inch loaf pan or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in 275° oven for 3 hours or until done.
This recipe makes 2 or 3 loaf pans; bake 2 hours.

title: mom-mom's beef stew
directions: Salt and pepper beef cubes; dip in flour.
Heat a small amount of oil in frypan.
Add floured beef cubes to heated oil.
Brown all over.
Add chopped onion and simmer a few minutes, then add a small amount of water to cover meat.
Simmer about an hour or an hour and a half, then add carrots.
Let cook about 1/2 hour, then add potatoes.
Cook until vegetables are done.
Add peas.
Cook another 5 minutes or until all vegetables are tender.

title: 5 day coconut cake
directions: Combine coconut, sour cream and sugar in bowl.
Mix well and set aside.
Prepare cake mix using package directions for 9-inch layers.
Cool.
Split layers with string.
Spread coconut mixture between layers and over top and sides of cake.
Place in airtight containers for over 24 hours before you open.
This cake is better and better everyday that it is in the refrigerator.

title: layered cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberry sauce with hot water in a blender until smooth. In another bowl mix 2 jello packs and 1 cup boiling water until dissolved.
Add cranberry mixture and nuts.
Pour 1/2 mixture in 8-inch square pans and chill until firm in the freezer (30 to 35 minutes).
Spread sour cream on top of firm jello mixture.
Add remaining jello mixture by pouring slowly into the corner of the pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
This can be doubled for a 13 x 9-inch dish.

title: microwave tapioca pudding
directions: Mix tapioca, 3 tablespoons sugar, salt, milk and egg yolk in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cook in microwave about 3 minutes; stir, then cook about 2 1/2 to 3 minutes, until mixture comes to a full boil.
Stir in vanilla.
Let stand at room temperature while beating egg white until foamy.
Gradually add 2 tablespoons sugar; whip to soft peaks.
Fold egg white into hot mixture.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Mix in pan sugar and cinnamon.
Stir in milk.
Boil to 236°, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add nuts and vanilla. Stir until mixture can no longer be stirred.
Turn out onto wax paper.
Separate into small pieces with fork.
Do quickly.
Makes less than 1 pound.

title: jello salad
directions: Make jello
as	directed on box.
Mix all together with other ingredients.
Place in refrigerator until jelled.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: eggs fondue
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Break bread into cubes.
Place bread into buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese over bread.
Beat eggs and mix with milk.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Pour butter over mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
To bake, place casserole dish in a pan of water.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve warm.

title: sweet potato burrito spirals
directions: Spread warm refried beans on tortilla, layer remaining ingredients and roll up tightly.

title: marshmallow crispy treats(microwave cooking time:  2 minutes and 15 seconds)
directions: Microwave margarine in large microwave-safe bowl on High 45 seconds or until melted.
Add marshmallows; toss to coat with margarine.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth when stirred, stirring after 45 seconds.
Immediately add cereal; mix lightly until well coated.
Press into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Cool; cut into squares.
Makes about 24.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Stir all ingredients, then boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from stove immediately.
Pour onto wax paper into cookie shapes, then let cool.

title: skillet zucchini
directions: Crumble sausage in large skillet.
Add zucchini, green pepper and onion.
Cook until almost done.
Add tomatoes.
Cook until juice is almost gone.
Put in serving dish and sprinkle on cheese and let melt.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine, sugar, peanut butter, vanilla and eggs in a large bowl until creamy and well blended. Mix in flour and oats.
Stir in chocolate chips.
