Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Yields 4 dozen.

title: salsa (sid's dip)
directions: Mix all together and serve with tortilla chips.

title: quick monkey bread
directions: Sprinkle pecans in bottom of a well-greased Bundt pan.
Set aside.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Cut biscuits into fourths. Roll each piece in sugar mixture and layer in pan.
Combine brown sugar and butter.
Pour over dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Invert onto serving platter.
Serve.

title: chocolate chip peanut butter cake
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, peanut butter and margarine.
Mix with fork until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup crumb mixture.
Combine the remaining mixture with baking powder, milk, eggs and vanilla.

title: pizza pasta
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Add dry soup mix.
Then add water and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil; add mini shells, oregano and Parmesan cheese.
Simmer until shells are cooked, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Then sprinkle Mozzarella cheese all over top and remove from heat until cheese melts.
Serve hot!

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Cook onion, bell pepper and garlic in oleo over low heat until tender.
Pour in celery soup, cornstarch, paprika and water.
Mix well and let come to a boil.
Pour in crawfish tails and cook for 30 minutes over low heat.
Add onion tops the last 5 minutes of cooking.
I add 3 or 4 chicken bouillon cubes to enhance the flavor.

title: 60 minute dinner rolls
directions: Mix together milk, sugar and yeast. Let yeast dissolve.
Add salt, oil and 1/2 the flour. Beat until smooth.

title: hot mexican dip
directions: Brown beef, sausage and onion; drain well.
Combine meat mixture and remaining ingredients and heat on low, stirring constantly,
until cheese is melted.
Serve in chafing dish to keep warm with tortilla chips.

title: south of the border dip
directions: Mix taco seasoning with refried beans and spread in bottom of an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Cover with sour cream and finish off with enough Cheddar cheese to make a layer.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and everything is hot. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: corn chowder
directions: Place potatoes in large pot covered with water.
Boil until tender and add corn.
In large skillet, fry bacon until done. Place on paper towel to drain.
Saute onion in drippings until tender.
Remove from heat; add flour, stir over medium heat until bubbly.
Remove from heat, add milk, heat to boiling for one minute.
Add to potatoes in pot.
Cook until all heated thoroughly.
Serve in bowl and sprinkle with bacon.

title: debbie's fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Set pineapple aside.
Pour juice into small saucepan.
Add sugar and flour; bring to a boil. Quickly stir in egg; cook until thickened.
Remove from heat. Cool; refrigerate.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Place chilled spinach in a large salad bowl.
Add chilled bean sprouts, drained water chestnuts, eggs, onion and bacon.
Mix sugar, oil, salt, vinegar, catsup and Worcestershire sauce in a small bowl; mix well.
Pour over spinach mixture; toss to mix well.
Serve immediately.

title: martha goldstrohm's swiss cheese meat loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. (Cover meat loaf with foil while baking).
Bakes faster in 2 small loaves.
Great leftover for sandwiches.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix butter and cracker crumbs.
Layer the beans, corn, soup and cheese in order given.
Sprinkle cracker crumb/butter mixture over it and bake at 350° until bubbly and crisp on top.
Serves 6.

title: party mix
directions: Melt butter in shallow pan. Stir in Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder. Add Chex, nuts and pretzels and mix until all pieces are coated. Heat in oven at 250° for about an hour. Stir every 15 minutes.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Mix 1 tablespoon oil, 4 teaspoons soy sauce and 2 teaspoons cornstarch in small bowl. Stir in chicken to coat.
Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: cowboy biscuits
directions: *Buttermilk may be used instead of sweet milk.
If used, add 1 teaspoon soda.

title: festive fruit salad
directions: Combine yogurt, sherbet and wheat germ; mix well. Add fruit; mix lightly. Chill 1 hour before serving. Makes 8 servings.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together thoroughly shortening, eggs and sugar.
Sift together and stir in flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt. Chill dough.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Then roll in mixture of 2 teaspoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 12 minutes, until lightly browned, but still soft. (These cookies puff up, then flatten out with crinkled tops.) Makes about 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Place crackers on microwave plate. Spread pizza sauce on top of crackers. Place pepperoni on top of sauce. Spread cheese on top of pepperoni. Microwave until cheese is melted. Enjoy!

title: cowboy coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and shortening until crumbly; reserve 1/2 cup.
To remaining crumbs, add baking powder, soda and spices. Mix well.
Add milk and eggs.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8-inch round pans.
Top with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: pilgrim's progress
directions: Mix juices in large pitcher.
Pour over crushed ice.
Garnish with lemon slices.
Yields 3 servings.

title: dessert cups
directions: Cut crust off edges of bread.
Butter both sides of bread. Put bread into cinnamon and sugar.
Place into cupcake pan; bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool completely until hard.
Add favorite pie filling.
Place whipped topping on when ready to serve.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Sift together flour and salt; set aside.
Combine the orange slices, dates, pecans and coconut.
Add to the candy mixture 1/2 cup of flour mixture.
Mix well and set aside.

title: vinegar cole slaw
directions: Toss with equal parts of oil, sugar and vinegar, about 1/2 cup or more of each.
Add salt and pepper.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Prick crust several times with fork. Line with aluminum foil.
Bake until lightly browned, 10 to 12 minutes.
Place crust on rack to cool completely.
Reduce oven heat to 375°.
Place half the cheese in the baked pie shell.
Top evenly with sausage, mushroom, onion and green pepper.
Sprinkle evenly with remaining cheese.

title: slushy punch
directions: Heat 2 cups water with sugar until sugar dissolves.
Cool. With mixer, mix bananas until smooth.
Add to cooled sugar mixture.
Add all of the other ingredients including remaining water.
Place mixture in plastic container and freeze.
When ready to serve, thaw for 15 minutes and add 1/2 large 7-Up or ginger ale until right consistency.
The punch should be slushy.
Add cut up strawberries.
Delicious on a hot day.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in order.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: new potatoes with garlic
directions: Cook the potatoes in boiling salted water until tender, 20 to 25 minutes. Drain and set aside. In a large saucepan or skillet, heat the butter and oil. Add the potatoes and saut for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring frequently. Add the garlic, salt, pepper, lemon juice and Tabasco sauce; lower the heat and cook for 3 to 4 minutes or until the garlic turns a golden color. Be careful not to burn the garlic. Serves 6. Probably can't be frozen. Can make ahead.

title: pig pickin barbecue sauce
directions: Mix well.
Baste on pig the last 2 hours of cooking the pig on the grill.

title: lemon custard cake
directions: Tear cake into bite size pieces.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix in bowl the pudding, milk and sour cream; beat until thickened.
Spread over cake.
Spoon pie filling over cake. Chill.

title: chicken artichoke casserole
directions: Salt,
pepper
and
paprika
the chicken pieces.
Brown them in 4 tablespoons butter.
Place in large casserole.
Put 2 tablespoons butter into frying pan and saute mushrooms in it for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle the flour over the mushrooms and stir in
the chicken
consomme and the sherry.
While this cooks 5 minutes, open
the artichokes and arrange between the chicken pieces.
Pour the
sauce
over the chicken and artichokes and bake
at
375° for
minutes.
You can prepare this in the morning or even the day
before.
Do
not
bake until at room temperature.

title: party punch
directions: Prepare lemon juice according to directions.
Stir in thawed strawberries; stir in sugar.
Mix until sugar dissolves.
Chill. Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Partly boil broccoli and drain.
Mix broccoli, mushroom soup, mayo, eggs and shredded cheese.
In saucepan, melt butter and mix with breadcrumbs.
Put broccoli mixture in baking dish and breadcrumb mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: grilled chicken kabobs
directions: In 12 x 8-inch (2-quart) baking dish or plastic bag, combine dressing, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice; blend well.
Add chicken strips; turn to coat.
Cover dish or seal bag; refrigerate 2 to 3 hours, turning once.

title: elegant steak and gravy
directions: Cut round steak into strips.
Put 3 tablespoons oil into a pot.
Brown round steak and onion (ring the onion).
Put soup, cooking sherry, garlic salt and liquid from the mushrooms into the blender (do not put mushrooms in the blender).
Blend these together.
Put the liquid and mushrooms in with the steak. Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, mayonnaise and chili powder.
Layer 1/2 each of the meat mixture, chips and cheese in 2-quart casserole dish.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until heated.
Top with shredded lettuce, tomato and sour cream if desired.

title: betty's chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, vanilla and chocolate. Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture and alternately add 1 cup boiling water.
Bake in 8-inch square greased pan for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sicilian meat roll
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Add beef.
Mix well.
On waxed paper or foil, pat meat to a 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Arrange ham and cheese on top, leaving a small margin around edges.
Starting from short end, roll up meat.
Seal edges and ends.
Place seam down in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: butternut layer cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs for 10 minutes.
Add 1 cup flour; beat on medium speed.
Add rest of flour and milk; beat 1 minute. Add flavoring last.
Pour into 3 greased and floured cake pans; bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: banana raisin bread(for bread machines)
directions: Add all ingredients, except raisins and nuts, to bread machine pan. Add ingredients in order listed or as directed by your machine's general instructions. Select "mix bread" or "raisin bread" function and push "start."
At "beep" (about 25 to 30 minutes into the cycle), add raisins and nuts.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Combine milk with water. Add pudding and mix well. Refrigerate 5 minutes. Fold in Cool Whip. Spoon approximately 1 cup of pudding into 2 1/2 qt. bowl. Layer wafers, then bananas, then half of remaining pudding. Add another layer of wafers, remaining bananas and remaining pudding. Top with wafer crumbs. Refrigerate till set, approximately 4 hours.
Do not make too far in advance as wafers get soggy and bananas turn brown.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger; drain and add spaghetti sauce.
Simmer.
Boil mostaccioli noodles for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Mix hamburger/spaghetti sauce with noodles.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Beat egg whites to stiff peaks. Add sugar gradually.
Fold in nuts and nibs.
Drop cookies on well-buttered cookie sheet.
Place in oven.
TURN OFF OVEN.
Do not open oven door for at least eight hours.
It is nice to make these in the evening and leave overnight in the oven.

title: grandma's swedish pancakes
directions: Put ingredients in blender (except oil); blend until smooth. (You may blend in mixing bowl if preferred.)
Heat skillet that has a handle.
Add small amount of oil to grease skillet after skillet has warmed up.
Add small amount of batter, tipping skillet so pancake runs out and becomes thin.
After pancake has become golden brown in spots, flip and cook other side same way.
Roll into tube shape and serve with maple syrup and butter or fresh cut fruit and powdered sugar.
Recipe can be halved.

title: rommegrot
directions: Melt butter in large, stainless or heavy pan.
Add flour and salt, stirring to mix, then add half and half very slowly, stirring constantly.
Heat and stir until it thickens.
Remove from heat and add sugar.
Melt 1/4 cup butter and pour over Rommegrot in serving bowl.
Also, sprinkle top with sugar and cinnamon.
Makes 5 cups.
Freezes nicely.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done, until meat falls from bone.
Let cool, discard bone and shred meat.
In large bowl, mix soup concentrates and tomatoes.
In buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, layer 1/3 of tortilla chips, 1/3 cooked chicken, 1/3 grated cheese and 1/3 soup mixture.
Repeat layers, reserving a little cheese and crushed chips for the top.
Bake for 1 hour, until hot and bubbly.
Serve with olives, tomatoes and lettuce.

title: seashore dip
directions: Crumble cream cheese into blender.
Add remaining ingredients, reserving liquid from clams.
Blend well.
If a softer mixture is desired, add small amount of liquid from clams.
Yield: 1 cup.

title: microwave chocolate fudge
directions: Microwave on Medium for 2 minutes.
Stir.
Microwave for 1 more minute.
Pour in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: squash chili verde
directions: Saute onion and chopped chili pepper in oil until tender.
Add squash, milk, salt and black pepper.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove from burner; top with grated cheese and cover until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: rich tomato beef sauce served over pasta
directions: Saute onions, celery, mushrooms and garlic in oil in large saucepan.
Add beef and continue cooking until meat begins to brown.
Drain excess fat.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Reduce heat and simmer slowly 1 hour. Serve over favorite pasta.

title: easy time party squares
directions: Cream oleo well. Gradually add sugar and beat well. Add eggs, one at a time, flour and lemon extract. Grease jelly roll pan, 15 x 10 x 1-inch. Spread batter in pan. Lightly score into 20 pieces. Place 1 heaping tablespoon of pie filling on each square. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. While still warm, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: zesty italian crescent casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown beef and onions.
Drain grease. Stir in sauce mix and tomato sauce.
Heat until hot and bubbly. Combine cheese and sour cream.
Pour hot meat mixture into a 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Spread cheese mixture over meat mixture. Separate crescent dough into rectangles.
Place over cheese mixture.
Spread margarine over dough and sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 25 minutes or until browned.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In heavy saucepan, dissolve cornstarch in water; stir in sweetened condensed milk and egg yolks.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat; add margarine and vanilla.
Cool slightly.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a baking dish with foil (shiny side towards the meat).
Place a chuck roast in the foil and sprinkle with pepper and thyme.
(Important!!
No salt!!)

title: lemon custard(healthful eating)
directions: In a bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; set aside. In another bowl, lightly beat egg yolks.
Beat in milk, lemon juice and lemon zest.
Add salt, sugar and flour and beat until smooth.
Fold yolk mixture into egg whites.
Pour into 6 individual 1 cup custard cups.
Place the cups in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour boiling water into baking pan to a depth of about 1-inch.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden and top springs back.
Serve warm.

title: five flavor cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time and beat until thick and smooth.
Combine flour and baking powder. Sift together and add to creamed mixture alternating with milk.
Stir in flavors.
Beat until blended. Spoon into tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add beaten eggs, mashed bananas and sifted flour.
Pour in greased loaf pan.
(Optional: Pour 1 cup of chopped pecans in mixture.) Bake in loaf pan in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine eggs, soup, cheese and mayonnaise.
Fold into broccoli. Pour into greased casserole dish.
Cover with Ritz cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until tender.
Drain. Allow to cool. Peel and slice. Place in a buttered casserole dish. Dot with butter and cinnamon. Mix all other ingredients together and pour over sweet potatoes.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hidden treasure cake
directions: Sift flour, 3/4 cup sugar and salt together.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar in large mixing bowl until soft mounds form. Gradually add 3/4 cup sugar, beating constantly until very straight peaks form.
Mix egg yolks, apricot nectar, rum flavoring and orange rind.
Add dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Beat 1 minute with mixer on medium speed.
Add 1/3 at a time to egg whites, folding gently but thoroughly.
Put in ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Invert and cool. Slice into 3 layers and spread Apricot-Orange filling between layers, then frost top and sides with Snowy White Frosting.

title: ham loaf
directions: Make loaf or balls.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Stir-fry meat until brown and heated through.
Add vegetables and heat through.
Add pineapple chunks and sweet and sour sauce. Heat and pour all over prepared rice.

title: easy doozits
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs with sugar, cinnamon, peanut butter and Karo syrup.
Mix and shape into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Yields 18 to 20 balls.

title: texas torte
directions: To eggs, add flour, salt and milk (beat well).
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a flat well-greased 8 x 12-inch Pyrex baking dish and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cut into tiny squares and serve as a hot hors d'oeuvre.
Makes 96 squares.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Tear up 4 slices rye bread into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. In layers over bread, spread kraut, corned beef, sour cream and onion.
Add Mozzarella and Swiss cheeses.
Tear other 4 slices bread on top of cheese, then pour melted oleo over bread.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until browned.

title: pink stuff
directions: Combine pie filling and milk.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Add a drop or two of red food coloring.
Refrigerate and serve chilled.

title: super sand tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 285°. Roll in balls. Bake and roll in powdered sugar while hot.

title: easy hot fudge
directions: Melt Chocolate in Microwave until soft. Stir. Then add milk and heat.
Stir again.
Pour over vanilla ice cream and add chopped nuts.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all but cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Add cheese on top last 15 minutes.
You may use Mexican cornbread mix for a different spicy taste treat.

title: no bake oat cookies
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, milk and oleo and bring to a boil and boil 3 minutes only.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla. Mix well and stir into oatmeal.
Drop from spoon onto waxed paper.
Cool and serve.

title: fried rice
directions: Take wok or frying pan and warm on medium heat.
Use 3 tablespoons vegetable oil and heat in pan.
First put in pan the garlic; brown a little and add beef.
Cook thoroughly.
Add onions. Cook 2 minutes; add egg and scramble all together.
When egg is done, add salt and pepper, then add rice.
Stir until well blended. Finally, add soy sauce and cook for 3 more minutes until rice is lightly browned completely in soy sauce.

title: celery mushroom casserole
directions: Cook celery in small amount of salted water until tender. Saute mushrooms in butter about 5 minutes, then add mushroom soup and peas and heat well.
Put half the cooked celery in greased casserole.
Pour in half of soup mixture and sprinkle with half of cheese.
Repeat.
Top with bread crumbs and bake at 350° until brown and bubbly, about 20 minutes.

title: settler's beans
directions: Brown beef with onion.
Add cut up Polish kielbasa.
Fry bacon and break up.
Mix with other ingredients.
Bake one hour at 350°. Serves 8.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine eggs, soup, onion, chicken, rice, celery, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Stir to mix well.
Spoon mixture into shallow nonstick 2-quart casserole.
Combine bread crumbs and butter substitute; sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 40 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: oriental spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs into serving pieces; place in baking pan.
Saute onion and garlic in oil in saucepan; stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour over spareribs.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for about 1 hour or until done.
Baste frequently.

title: perfect pilaf(supper dish)
directions: Cook rice as directed on package, substituting soup for part of water and reducing salt to 1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon.
Good in place of potatoes for any dinner.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Mix well.
Pour into paper cups and freeze.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine all except 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese and onions.
Bake 5 minutes.

title: broccoli bacon quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook bacon until crisp. Set aside.
Beat eggs with cream and cheese.
Stir in broccoli, salt, garlic powder and lemon pepper. Crumble bacon. Stir 1/2 of the crumbled bacon into egg mixture. Pour into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Top with remaining bacon.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix 100% Bran and boiling water and let cool.
Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, salt, baking soda, buttermilk and 40% Bran.
Add this to the first mixture of 100% Bran and water.
Fill muffin tins 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. (Check with toothpick for doneness.)
Batter may be stored for up to 2 weeks in Tupperware container in the refrigerator.

title: low-fat orange delight
directions: Mix ingredients together; let chill overnight.
May substitute other flavors and fruits (blackberry, strawberry, etc.).

title: chappell's dip
directions: Layer equal amount of guacamole daily, sour cream and Pace picante sauce in a clear bowl.
Serve with tortilla chips or corn chips.
Combine all ingredients; mix well.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Melt the butter or margarine in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix the remaining ingredients in the order given, pouring the milk over all.
Spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pear salad
directions: Place enough lettuce leaves on platter to cover it. Put drained pear halves, with hole side up, on lettuce leaves. Fill hole with Miracle Whip. Sprinkle with cheese. Place 1/2 cherry on top of cheese. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine cereal, milk, oil and eggs.
Stir until moist.
Let set 5 minutes.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and spices. Add to cereal mix.
Stir until well blended.
Bake at 375° for 14 to 16 minutes in greased or lined muffin pan.

title: mounds candy bars
directions: Mix all ingredients.
It will be hard to mix but do not add any more liquid.
Chill for 2 hours.
Form into balls.
Melt 1 large package (12 ounce) chocolate chips and 1 bar of paraffin wax.
Keep over hot water while dipping candy.
Place on wax paper.
Can be frozen.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Spread chicken wings on baking pan.
Bake in 450° oven for 35 minutes if frozen or 25 minutes if thawed.
Combine ingredients to make sauce.
Cover cooked wings with sauce and bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
I put my sauce in a large Tupperware bowl and add cooked wings and shake vigorously to coat wings.

title: grandma's honey cookies
directions: Roll in balls. Dip top in water, then sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Put toast into greased 2-quart baking dish; sprinkle with raisins.
Pour over toast mixture of eggs, sugar, salt, milk, boiling water and vanilla.
Let stand for 10 minutes and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until a knife inserted into center comes out clean.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana delight
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, softened butter and pecans.
Press in pan and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: quick escalloped potatoes(no curdling)
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour and salt and add milk slowly, stirring constantly until sauce boils and thickens.
Add potatoes and heat, stirring occasionally until the sauce boils again.
Turn potatoes into a shallow greased casserole (6 1/2 x 10 x 1 3/4-inch).
Drizzle the tablespoon melted butter over top. Place on rack a little above middle of oven.
Bake in 350° preheated oven 35 minutes or until potatoes are tender, the liquid bubbles up almost over potatoes and they are slightly brown on top.

title: witch hat cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, soda and salt. In a mixer bowl, beat butter for 30 seconds. Add peanut butter and sugars.
Beat until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Combine eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add zucchini.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts. Pour into two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
(Should be about 1/2 full.)
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pans for 15 minutes. Pour out onto wax paper.
Yield: 2 loaves.

title: snack cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, combine butter and shortening.
Beat in sugar, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in cereal; mix well.
Drop by level tablespoons onto ungreased baking sheet 2-inches apart. Bake 9 to 11 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool at least 1 minute before removing from baking sheet.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: tennessee baked ham
directions: Soak ham overnight in cold water.
Drain and wipe dry.
Mix cornbread with brown sugar and pepper.
Add enough water to make a clay-like paste.
Put ham in a shallow baking pan.
Cover ham with cornmeal paste, making shell about 1-inch thick.
Roast in preheated moderate oven at 350° for 4 hours or until meat registers 170° on thermometer.
Add a little boiling water to pan but do not taste.
Remove from oven.
Strip off paste and skin. Sprinkle ham with dry bread crumbs.
Replace in oven and bake until brown.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Crumble sausage into large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat. Add onion; cook and stir until transparent.
Drain, discarding all but 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Stir in flour; cook over medium-low heat for about 6 minutes, or until mixture bubbles and turns golden.
Stir in milk.
Add seasonings; cook, stirring, until thickened.
To serve, slice biscuits and spoon gravy over halves.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: caramel chocolate squares
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: In a large glass bowl, blend together pudding and mix in pineapple.
Mix well.
Fold in marshmallows and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill.
Serve cold.
(Best when made a day ahead.)

title: zucchini muffins
directions: In a medium bowl, mix the flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and sugar.
Add the eggs, milk, oil, zucchini and walnuts or raisins.
Mix completely, but not too well, or else muffins will be tough.

title: macaroni and cheese supreme
directions: Cook macaroni with salt.
Drain.
Mix all together, except crushed parsley and cracker crumbs.
Pour into a large baking dish.
Sprinkle with crushed parsley and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: 3-cheese lasagna in half the time
directions: Mix tomatoes and juice with spaghetti sauce.
Mix Ricotta cheese and basil.
Spread 1/4 of the tomato mixture on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with 4 noodles, 1/3 Ricotta cheese and 1/3 Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers 2 more times, ending with tomato sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, covered.

title: german pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large mixing bowl, whip eggs until extremely light and airy.
Add milk, flour and salt and again mix until airy.
Heat butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour batter into pan of melted butter.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot with maple syrup.

title: super supper dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and stir beef and onions in large skillet until beef is brown; drain.
Spoon half of beans into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with half each of beef mixture, chilies, salsa and cheese.
Repeat with remaining beans, beef mixture, chilies, salsa and cheese.
Bake 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and mixture is heated through.
Top with sour cream, green onions and olives.
Serve with chips.

title: creamy curry dip(chutney accents the curry and adds sweetness)
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine tomato sauce, instant minced onion, Worcestershire sauce and curry powder.
Let mixture stand 10 minutes.
Add softened Neufchatel cheese.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until cheese mixture is creamy.
Turn into serving bowl.
Garnish dip with a ring of chutney.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Makes about 1 cup dip.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger in large skillet.
Drain excess fat.
Mix in dry taco mix, follow direction on package.
Set aside.
Spread cream cheese in bottom of a 8x10 baking dish.
Add hamburger to dish and cover cream cheese.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over the top.
Bake at 350 until cheese is melted and meat is hot.
Remove from oven, enjoy by dipping taco chips.

title: thank god for fellowship
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Put in chicken, cover with cheese.
Mix wine and soup and pour over.
Mix stuffing with melted margarine and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Serves 10 for lunch and 8 for dinner.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Blend well. Shape round tablespoonfuls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 9 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix together and roll into balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 325° until golden brown or done.

title: pineapple barbecued ham steak
directions: In small bowl, stir together barbecue sauce, pineapple and dry mustard until well blended.
Grill ham steak 6 inches from source of heat, brushing with sauce and turning frequently, 25 to 30 minutes.
Heat remaining sauce and serve with ham.
Makes 4 servings.

title: divinity candy
directions: Bring sugar, syrup and water to boil and boil until small amount cracks on edge of cup.
Then slowly pour over egg whites, which have been beaten.
Add chopped nuts and vanilla.
Beat until small dabbles can be dipped out and will not run.

title: chelou kabab(chelou is rice and kabab is broiled meats and vegetables)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Flatten the beef mixture onto a baking sheet until about 1-inch thickness.
Cut crosswise into 2-inch wide strips for individual portions.
Cook for 30 minutes (325°).
May need to turn oven to broil for the last 3 to 4 minutes to get the desired brownness.
Serve kabab over rice (chelou).
Sprinkle with sumac.

title: healthy garden quiche(makes 6 servings, 152 cal., 5 g. fat, 14 mg cholesterol per
directions: In saucepan, cook onion and garlic in margarine.
In bowl, toss Lite-line pieces with flour.
Add onion mixture and remaining ingredients.
Pour into lightly oiled 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until set.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: easy brown sugar cobbler(serves 8)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and place in oven to melt.
Mix together the flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, brown sugar and milk to make a batter. Remove the hot dish with the melted butter from the oven and pour in the batter.
Evenly spoon the fruit with its juices over the batter.
Place the dish back in oven and bake until batter is browned and has risen up and around the fruit, about 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream, if desired.

title: italian zucchini and sausage
directions: Pan-fry sausage until browned and crumbled. Add onion, zucchini and garlic; cook 5 minutes. Add tomato sauce and seasonings; cover and simmer 25 minutes or until zucchini is tender. Sprinkle with cheeses. Serves 6.

title: stuffed round steak
directions: You will need a roasting pan and string to tie roast.

title: rice and shrimp salad
directions: Mix rice, celery, olives and green peppers.
Mix shrimp, mayonnaise, French dressing, salt and pepper.
Chill.
Just before serving, toss together and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Save 1 cup of flour to coat
fruit and nuts in.
Mix rest of ingredients.	Bake at 250° for 5 hours with pan of water under cake.

title: spice coolers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 3 ingredients in large bowl by hand.
Drop by teaspoon into sugar and cinnamon mixture to coat.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Let cool on cookie sheet for 5 minutes.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 9-inch square pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Beat well and pour over melted butter.
Spoon fruit over batter using all of the juice.
Bake at 375° about 30 minutes or until it browns on top.

title: garden vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 10-inch pie pan.
Cook broccoli until almost tender (5 minutes) and drain.
Mix broccoli, onion, peppers and cheese into pie pan.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth and pour into pie pan.
Bake until golden brown and inserted knife comes out clean, about 35 to 40 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat slowly in crock pot about 8 hours. Stir a few times while cooking if possible.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain and place in a large mixing bowl.
Combine soup, mayo, eggs, onion, salt and pepper with broccoli.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Cover with cheese and
bread	crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and potato chips.
Place in a greased casserole.	Top with cheese, then with a layer of potato chips.
Bake at 400 degrees for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: tuna cakes
directions: Mix well and fry in butter until golden brown.
Drain and serve plain or with tartar sauce.

title: vitamin candy
directions: Blend first four ingredients.
Add wheat germ and nuts.
Shape into small balls.
Roll them in confectioners sugar.
Store in refrigerator or freeze.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Heat sugar, butter and milk until boiling.
When mixture comes to boil, boil for 5 minutes or until foamy.
Take off stove and add marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Spread mixture into glass dish or 9 x 13-inch baking pan and cool.
Cut and serve.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix and pour over bread.
Put cinnamon on top.
Add more milk to make soft.
Add raisins.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place blueberries and lemon juice in small saucepan.
Place over low heat until warm; set aside. Combine flour, noncaloric sweetener, fructose and baking powder in large bowl.
Add milk and margarine; stir until blended.
Pour into an 8-inch square baking pan.
Drain and rinse blueberries; spoon blueberries over batter.
Do not stir.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes, until golden brown.

title: swedish rye bread
directions: Bring to boil 1 1/2 cups water, sugar and dark brown sugar. Remove from heat and add molasses or Karo syrup, oleo and shortening. Cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in warm water. Let stand several minutes before adding to mixture. Add 3 cups rye flour. Let rise until doubled in size. Knead in white flour and salt. Let rise again. Form into 2 loaves and let rise. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Brush tops with butter. Makes 2 loaves.

title: eloise's pound cake
directions: Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Cover bottom of a 9 x 13 inch pan with a single layer of graham crackers.
Mix together 2 small packages of instant vanilla pudding and milk, stir well and add Cool Whip.
Spread half of pudding mixture over graham crackers in pan.
Add another layer of graham crackers, then remaining pudding.
Add another layer of graham crackers.
Prepare frosting by mixing together powdered sugar, butter, milk, Karo syrup, melted chocolate, and vanilla. Frost cake and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: poor man's fruit cake
directions: Dissolve sugar and oil.
Add vegetables and fruit.
Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Add one egg at a time and beat well.
Pour into Bundt pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Put all ingredients into plastic bag. Close and shake until potatoes are coated evenly.
Empty into shallow baking pan.
Bake, stirring occasionally, for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Garnish with fresh parsley.
Serves 8.

title: bacon-wrapped scallops with lemon-chive sauce
directions: Cut bacon in half crosswise.
Wrap each scallop in a piece of bacon and secure with a wooden toothpick.
Place scallop on a rack in a broiler pan.
Brush with Lemon and Chive Sauce.
Broil 6 inches from heat, 10 to 15 minutes or until scallops are opaque and bacon is done, turning occasionally.
Serve immediately. Yield:
6 servings.

title: jello punch
directions: *Mixed fruit flavor works best, but you can use any flavor you wish.
Try mixing flavors (i.e. strawberry and peach) or use flavor(s) to match a certain color scheme (i.e. grape for purple color or lime for green color).

title: sausage muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix cornmeal, eggs, and milk; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into muffin pan.
Bake 25 minutes or until brown.
Makes 24.

title: zwiebach
directions: Let the yeast melt in the warm water.
Mix all the ingredients.
Save about 4 cups of the flour for later.
With electric beater, beat eggs, sugar and salt.
Add milk and lard. Add flour until it makes a nice dough.
Let rise in a warm place until double in size.
Punch down with floured hands and let rise again.
Flour hands and form into small loaves in pan (15 x 15-inch).
Let rise again, then bake at 350° until light brown. Take out and let cool and then pull or cut loaves apart, then put back into pan to dry in a 300° oven; do not burn.
Can be frozen or stored in a closed container.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Place beef in a large pot and fill with water just to top of beef.
Do not cover. Add 1 teaspoon salt. Bring to a boil.
Reduce to a simmer for 3 to 4 hours. Remove scum as it appears on top. Pour juice into bowl. Shred beef.
Add juice and 1 large bottle Open Pit sauce.
Simmer 1 hour, uncovered.

title: monterey spinach melt
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut cheese into 20 thin slices; cover and set aside.
In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, sour cream, salt and garlic; mix until well blended.
Stir in spinach, carrot onion.
Spread rounded tablespoonful spinach mixture into each bread slice.
Place on baking sheet; top with cheese.
Bake 10-12 minutes or until cheese is melted and bread is crisp.
Serve warm.

title: pineapple whipped cream cake
directions: Add sugar to pineapple.
Cook until thick.
Stir to keep from burning.
Add to whipped cream.
Mix good and spread on cake.
Be sure pineapple is cold before adding to whipped cream.
Have cake cool before putting the whipped cream mixture on it.
Use 2 1/2 pints whipping cream.

title: banana split cake
directions: Make strawberry/banana Jell-O, using juice from peaches and pineapple.
Make vanilla instant pudding according to directions.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Saute bacon in large pan.
Remove bacon and saute onions in drippings.
Stir in flour, salt, sugar, mustard, water and vinegar.
Stir until thickened, add cut up potatoes and bacon pieces.
Serve immediately. (This dish can all be done in the microwave too.)

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Melt the butter in iron skillet.
Heat berries with 1 cup sugar until they boil.
Make batter of 1 cup sugar, the flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour batter in skillet on butter.
Pour berries on batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pineapple raspberry mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add enough water to make 1 cup.
Bring to boil.
Add gelatin and dissolve.
Break up cranberry sauce and add to gelatin.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add pineapple and chopped nuts.
Pour into 1-quart mold.
Chill for about 4 hours.
Unmold onto serving plate. Yields 6 servings.

title: oatsies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease baking pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
In medium bowl, mix oats and brown sugar.
Stir together butter, syrup, salt and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly into oats mixture.
Press dough evenly in bottom of pan.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until top bubbles.
Cool, spread chocolate on top.
Sprinkle nuts on chocolate.
Chill for 1 hour.
Cut into about 2 x 1-inch bars.

title: sandra's hot apple cider
directions: Dissolve candy in apple juice and add cinnamon sticks.

title: onion soup meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 375°.

title: chicken and asparagus casserole
directions: Boil chicken and cut into bite-size pieces.
Stir together soup, pimiento strips, water chestnuts, almonds, salt, pepper and chicken.
Put into buttered casserole.
Carefully fold in drained asparagus.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes, or until it bubbles.
Add onion rings to cover top for the last 8 to 10 minutes. Preparation time:
45 minutes.
Can be prepared in advance. Serves 6.

title: comida mexicana
directions: Brown meats, onion and green pepper in a large skillet.
Add tomatoes, sour cream or buttermilk, vermicelli, chili powder comino and salt.
Cover and simmer 3 to 5 minutes or until done.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in baking dish or sheet cake pan.
In saucepan, heat sugar and water until sugar dissolves.
Cut shortening into flour until particles are like fine crumbs.
Add milk and stir with fork until dough leaves the side of bowl.
Knead just until smooth on floured cutting board. Roll dough out into large rectangle, about 1/4-inch thick. Sprinkle cinnamon over apples, then sprinkle apples evenly over dough.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Dampen edge of dough with water and seal.
Slice dough into 16 slices (1/2-inch thick). Place in pan with margarine.
Pour syrup over roll.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes.

title: brown rice
directions: Place all ingredients in casserole dish; cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: turkey tacos
directions: Put all ingredients in saucepan
Cover; simmer gently 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Drain; fill prepared taco shells with mixture.
Add chopped lettuce, grated cheese and hot sauce as desired.

title: coconut pie
directions: Place all ingredients in blender at one time and blend well. Pour into buttered 10-inch pie pan.
Bake in 350° oven for an hour.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Melt butter in skillet (or large pan).
Saute vegetables until tender.
Add rest of sauce ingredients and cook until thick.
Mix with chicken and cooked spaghetti.
Mix in or top with cheese. Cook at 350° until cheese melts.
Can be frozen or stretched with more cheese and spaghetti.
Some people add sliced green olives.

title: honey whole wheat bread
directions: With mixer, beat the first 8 ingredients on medium speed.
Add 1 cup flour.
Beat on high speed 1 minute. Add the oats, whole wheat flour, apple, wheat germ and flour to stiffen. Hand mix. Turn out on floured board.
Knead 5 or 10 minutes.
Let rest on board, covered with wax paper, 20 minutes.
Punch down and shape into 3 loaves.
Put into greased pans.
Grease with butter or margarine.
Brush tops of loaves with oil.
Let rise in oven over pan of hot water until double in bulk.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°. Cool on racks on side.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling, salted water.
When soft, drain potatoes.
Mix milk, butter, flour and pepper. Cook all ingredients 1 minute.
Serve with soda crackers or cornbread.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine margarine with flour and confectioners sugar.
Pat into oblong glass baking dish (approximately 9 x 12-inch) for crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Beat eggs and mix with 2 cups sugar, baking powder, flour and lemon juice.
Pour over baked crust right away.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with sifted powdered sugar.

title: lemon-lime punch
directions: Mix Kool-aid, sugar, and pineapple juice in gallon jug.
Add enough water to fill jug.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.
May use some of mixture for ice ring.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: friendship sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add egg and blend well.
Sift flour with dry ingredients.
Add vanilla to milk.
Alternate adding flour mixture and milk to creamed mixture, starting and ending with flour.
Mix well and chill.
Drop by teaspoon into powdered sugar coating.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375° on center rack.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter in top of double boiler.
Fold in noodles, then marshmallows.
Drop by teaspoon on greased wax paper.
Cool.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: taco dip
directions: Soften cream cheese, mix with sour cream until smooth.
Spread in glass baking dish.
Top with taco sauce, lettuce, onion, black olives, tomatoes and Cheddar cheese.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients and then mix other ingredients together. Combine and cook in microwave until thick, stirring occasionally.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with Cool Whip on top.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring margarine, cocoa, water and salt to a boil. Remove from heat. Add flour, soda and sugar. Beat eggs into sour cream and add to mixture along with vanilla.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.
Frost immediately.

title: sour cream pineapple pie
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, flour, crushed pineapple (with syrup), sour cream, lemon juice and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Mix well.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Stir a small amount of the pineapple mixture into the egg yolks.
Return to the hot mixture and cook, stirring until yolks are heated, about 2 minutes.
Cool, stirring often during cooling.
Pour filling in pie shell.

title: ham and swiss buns
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
On floured surface, separate dough from the crescent dinner rolls into 4 rectangles.
Gently pinch diagonal perforations together on each rectangle.
With lightly floured rolling pin, roll each rectangle into 7 x 5-inch rectangle.
Arrange ham and cheese slices on dough rectangles, cutting ham and cheese to fit and leaving 1/2-inch rim of dough all around.
Spread filling with mustard.
Brush rim of dough with some egg.
Fold dough and filling over so 5-inch sides meet.
With fork, firmly press edges together to seal.
Place on cookie sheet; brush with remaining egg.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes until browned. Makes 4 servings.

title: beer cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs together.
Sift or stir together flour, baking soda, salt, cloves, cinnamon and allspice.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with beer.
Roll cherries and dates in powdered sugar.
Fold in dates, cherries, and nuts.
Turn into greased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.
Cool on rack completely before removing from pan.

title: pineapple punch
directions: You need 1 punch bowl.

title: apple raisin cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla; beat until well blended. Stir in flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Fold in apples, raisins and nuts.

title: christmas rolls
directions: Place rolls in 2 Bundt pans.
Sprinkle dry pudding over rolls.
Melt together the butter, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over rolls.
Sprinkle nuts and raisins over rolls.
Bake according to package directions on rolls.

title: great grandma's pandowdy
directions: Beat up the egg.
Add the sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Put in the chopped apple.
Throw in a handful of currants and some walnut meats, if you wish.
Turn into a greased pie pan; bake 1/2 hour.

title: shiny dough
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour mixture into plastic squeeze bottles like the kinds used for ketchup or mustard.
You and your child can make 3-D pictures by squeezing this dough onto cardboard.
The salt makes it sparkle when it dries.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add well beaten eggs.
Mix dry ingredients and add to mixture and mix well.
Add bananas and water then nuts.
Bake in two or three 8-inch pans at 350 for 30 minutes OR in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350 until done.
Frost when cooled and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: bread pudding
directions: Place buns crust side up in 8-inch pan.
Stick holes in top of buns.
Melt butter and pour over buns.
Mix eggs, sugar, milk and nutmeg.
Pour over buns.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mash buns down one time while cooking.

title: dave and kurt's birthday cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine chocolate, 3/4 cup sugar and water in a small saucepan.
Stir until chocolate is melted.
Cook 10 minutes.
Cool and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Set aside.

title: beer bread
directions: In large bowl, mix flour, sugar and beer.
Mix well.
Put in greased bread pan.
Brush top lightly with melted butter or oleo. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Mix together and spoon into ungreased muffin pan.
Cook at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate pie(easy)
directions: Mix all in blender.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked apples - lo-fat
directions: Core apples.
Mix remaining ingredients; put filling in apples.
Add 1/4-inch water to baking pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: zucchini chili cheese bake
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Cook zucchini in small amount of salted water until crisp-tender.
Set aside. In a 3-quart buttered casserole, place cooked rice; cover with chopped chilies.
Sprinkle on half of cheese; arrange zucchini slices over cheese.
Add tomato slices.
Sprinkle with salt.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix 3 cups milk with pudding then fold in Cool Whip.
Put a layer of graham crackers in bottom of large pan.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over graham crackers.
Add another layer then put rest of mixture over it and add another layer of graham crackers.
Mix cocoa, 1/4 cup milk and sugar together.
Boil 1 minute then add margarine and vanilla.
Pour over mixture.	Better if you fix night before.

title: whole wheat muffins
directions: Combine butter and eggs, beating well.
Stir in honey. Combine dry ingredients; add to butter mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating well after each addition.
Spoon into well-greased muffin pans.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: hungry ram's punch
directions: Boil sugar and 2 quarts water until sugar is dissolved.
Mix to taste.
Serves 50.

title: almond rice
directions: Heat butter in saucepan; add almonds and saute a few minutes just until golden.
Add rice and stir until it is thoroughly coated.
Add water and salt.
Bring to lively boil.
Stir briefly. Boil until water barely disappears from surface.
Lower heat immediately.
Cover tightly and cook until rice is done and fluffy, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: boston baked beans(microwave)
directions: Slice bacon into 1/2-inch pieces.
Combine bacon, onion and garlic in microsafe dish.
Microwave at High for 5 minutes or unti onion is soft.
Drain beans.
Add beans and remaining ingredients to onion mixture.
Microwave covered with wax paper, at High for 7 minutes, stirring once during cooking time.
Serves 4.

title: mother's best fudge recipe
directions: Put chocolate chips, nutmeats, oleo and vanilla into a large bowl; set aside.
In heavy saucepan or skillet, combine sugar and milk; heat and stir until sugar is melted.
Add 10 large or 30 small marshmallows.
Bring to a boil and boil 6 minutes.
If raining or damp, boil 2 minutes longer.
Pour this mixture over mixture in bowl.
Stir until it starts to set.
Turn into greased pan or platter.
When firm, cut into squares.

title: suicide soup
directions: Put all ingredients together and simmer.
This is a good soup if you are trying to shed a few pounds.
It has very few calories, hardly any nutrition, but it fills you up.
You can experiment with the spices and use all the low calorie vegetables you like, but no potatoes, corn or peas.

title: fruit and pudding dessert
directions: Mix milk, orange juice and pudding mix with rotary beater. Drain pineapple, oranges and peaches.
Fold into pudding mixture. Slice bananas and apples and add just before serving.
Chill before serving.

title: grits surprise
directions: Cook boiling water, grits and salt until done but not dry.
Add pepper, garlic cheese, Worcestershire sauce, butter, eggs and chili powder.
Mix together in a casserole.
Cover with grated cheese and paprika.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
You can mix this all together the day before and refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and chocolate thoroughly.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Stir together flour, soda and salt; blend in.
Mix in nuts.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Drop teaspoonfuls of dough about 2 inches apart on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until no imprint remains when touched lightly.
Frost cooled cookies.

title: kim's potato soup
directions: In large pan, cook carrots, celery and onions in margarine until onions are transparent.
In a separate bowl, add chicken broth to mashed potatoes until smooth.
Add to vegetable mixture, then add milk and potatoes, cubed and shredded.
Salt, pepper and cheese.
Cook over low heat to prevent scorching and stir frequently.
Cook until potatoes are tender.

title: harvard beets
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and pepper.
Add beet juice and vinegar.
Simmer, uncovered, over low heat; stir until clear and thickened, about 5 minutes.
Add beets and heat until hot. Yield: 4 servings.

title: stromboli
directions: Thaw dough at room temperature; let rise a little.
Roll out dough into 12 x 14-inch rectangle.
Cover with ham, Mozzarella cheese, hard salami and pepperoni.
Starting at the 14-inch side, roll dough, tucking stuffing inside.
Pinch ends together.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into pie crust.
Chill.

title: pineapple cranberry sauce
directions: Slice cranberry sauce, reserving 3 slices.
Puree remaining cranberry sauce and pineapple together in food processor or blender.
Put in serving dish. Place reserved slices of cranberry sauce on top.
Chill 2 hours.
Serve as a side dish or dessert.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand (no mixer) and pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: betty's corn casserole
directions: Saute margarine, onion and bell pepper.
Add corn, egg, salt, pepper, rice and sugar.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken breasts with asparagus and mushrooms
directions: Pound the chicken breasts until thin.
In a skillet, saute the chicken in 2 tablespoons of butter until lightly browned on both sides.
Season the chicken and remove it from the pan.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix together.
Sprinkle over cake before baking.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: potato buttermilk soup
directions: Cover cubed potatoes with broth and cook until tender.
Remove from heat, do not drain.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain.
Saute shallots (onions) in bacon fat until golden, then remove.
Melt butter in saucepan over medium-high heat.
Add flour and stir for 2 minutes.
Slowly stir in buttermilk.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Add shallots, potatoes and liquid, and thyme; heat to near boil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Garnish with bacon and thyme sprigs.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and 1/2 carton Cool Whip.
Cover crust.
Mix pudding and milk.
Spread over. Cover with 1/2 carton Cool Whip.
Garnish with nuts and cherries. (Any flavor pudding mix may be used.)

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Cook carrots for 5 minutes or until tender.
Rinse under cold water.
Separate onions into rings and alternate layers of carrots, onions, peas, etc.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix until smooth.
Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight. (Keeps well up to 2 weeks.)

title: strawberry pecan bread
directions: Sift flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt together; combine with sugar in large bowl.
Make well in center; put strawberries, eggs, oil and pecans in well and stir until moistened.
Pour batter in 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 2 loaves.
Batter is sufficient for use with 4 (6 x 3-inch) loaf pans.
Reduce baking time to 35 to 45 minutes. Freezes nicely.

title: baked dried beef dip
directions: Cream together all ingredients except dried beef.
Add dried beef which has been rinsed well and cut into small pieces.
Place into a baking dish and cover with 1/2 cup pecans, chopped and sauteed in 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: orange and lemon jello cake
directions: Beat
egg
yolks,
cake mix, dry Jell-O, Mazola oil, orange juice
and	vanilla
until	smooth.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Bake in
tube
pan, greased and floured, oven 325° to 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Let cool 5 minutes, remove from pan and drizzle
over
cake
the orange juice and sugar. This is a delicious and moist cake.

title: very good baked beans
directions: Wash and soak beans overnight.
Cook in the water soaked in for 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, 2 hours. Cover and bake 1 hour longer.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Add cocoa and sugar.
Mix well.
Add milk. Bring to boil.
Boil hard for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and oats.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt Milky Way candy bars and 1 stick of butter together. Beat until smooth and set aside.
Cream 1 stick butter with sugar and eggs.
Mix in flour, buttermilk, soda, vanilla, salt and nuts. Fold in Milky Way mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and ice.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice 15 minutes in chicken broth.
Let set 15 minutes (may cook in microwave according to instructions).
Add chicken, beans, soup, chestnuts, almonds and mayonnaise.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: pistachio torte
directions: Mix the butter, flour and walnuts together.
Knead and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Let cool. (May be placed in refrigerator to cool.)

title: vegetable salad dressing
directions: Mix thoroughly and shake before using.
May be stored indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend and shape into ball or roll.
Roll in chili powder. Chill well.
Serve with crackers.

title: apple banana frosty
directions: Blend all the ingredients in a blender.
Serves 4 little kinders.

title: turkey impossible pie
directions: Sprinkle turkey, mushrooms, onions, salt and cheese in 10-inch pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake at 400° until center comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes after done.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: miss ellen's roast
directions: Place roast in the center of extra wide heavy foil in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Brush the meat with steak sauce; sprinkle with onion soup.
Mix and spread the mushroom soup over top.
Wrap loosely in foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Yields 6 servings.

title: stained glass cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and chill 1 hour.
Divide into thirds and form into rolls.
Wrap in foil.
Chill 3 hours.
Slice and put on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until brown on edges.

title: hot lettuce dressing
directions: Pour mix over bacon and cook until thickened.
Pour over lettuce and enjoy.

title: cheese crackers
directions: Mix all together until it forms into dough. Roll in small balls and flatten with fork. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: ham and potatoes
directions: Cut luncheon meat into 8 slices; place in an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.

Top with potatoes from 1 package dry au gratin potato mix, mushrooms and cheese sauce mix from potato mix. Continue as directed on box, adding 1 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce to butter and boiling water called for.
Cover; bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Cut the eggplant in half lengthwise and scoop out.
Chop pulp very fine.
Add butter, onion and green pepper; cook slowly until very tender.
Remove from stove.
Beat the cup of bread crumbs and seasoning into it, then the well beaten egg.
Add milk (enough to make a thin batter); put back into the hulls.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and brown in oven for about 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a bowl stir together mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese and onion.	Stir into the mixture the artichoke hearts, lemon juice and black pepper.
Scrape into a small ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle on top the bread crumbs and olive oil. Bake until top is brown, about 20 minutes.	Serve with crackers or toast.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Cover meat with cold
water
and
simmer for 3 to 3 1/2 hours over medium
fire.
After
3 hours, add cabbage and cook until tender.
Serves 7 to 9.

title: mushroom soup and rice
directions: Heat mushroom soup and water.
Add Minute rice and heat with soup, until boiling.
Cover and let stand until moisture is gone.

title: grandma's pie crust
directions: Mix until well blended.
Put 1/3 of mixture in another bowl; add 1/3 cup of water.
Mix together, then add the other 2/3 and mix.
Makes 1 double crust pie.

title: apple muffins
directions: Beat the honey, oil and eggs.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Add to honey mixture; stir well.
Add and fold together the apple and vanilla and the raisins and nuts.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from tins to cool.
Makes 24 large muffins.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and cocoa.
Add eggs, vanilla, nuts and flour.
Beat 1 to 2 minutes.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan with butter and flour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spread one large Marshmallow Creme over cake and let cook.

title: white bean dip
directions: In food processor or blender, puree cannellini beans, lemon juice, olive oil and cumin until smooth.
In small serving bowl, stir bean puree, picante sauce and thinly sliced green onions. Garnish and serve with veggies.
Makes 10 servings.

title: savory crawfish (or shrimp) casserole
directions: Melt butter and saute onion and rest of vegetables.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes. Stew 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook rice according to package directions. Add to onion. Add mushroom soup, parsley and crawfish or shrimp to mixture. Spray casserole dish with Pam. Pour mixture into casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Precook and slice carrots and set aside.
In 3-quart saucepan, melt 1/4 cup of the margarine, stir in the flour.
Stir in broth, continue to stir until thick.
Lower heat, add cheese.
Stir and remove from heat. Stir in chicken, carrots and pimento.
Spread in 2-quart casserole dish.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt remaining margarine, add stuffing, spread over chicken mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: virginia stew
directions: Boil the first 5 ingredients in 3 quarts of water for 1 hour. Add corn, sugar, butter and salt and pepper to taste.
Boil 20 minutes and then add 1 cup milk before serving.

title: vegi-soup(low calorie)
directions: Cook for 2 hours, adding water as it cooks.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in the order they appear.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 325°.
Do not overbake.

title: pork chop and potato casserole
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in paper bag.
Cut pork chops into bite-size pieces.
Shake in flour mixture.
Heat bacon fat and brown chops.
Place in greased baking dish.
Blend soup, milk, onion, Tabasco and sugar.
Cover chops with layers of potatoes and then 1/2 of sauce.
Add another layer of potatoes and the rest of sauce.
Dot with margarine and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: raisin cake
directions: Boil raisins and water down to 1 cup of juice.
Pour juice in a bowl; add soda.
Cool slightly and add shortening and sugar to the warm liquid.
Then add flour, baking powder and raisins. (Nuts can be added.)
Bake in well-greased loaf pan at 350° for 40 minutes.
Can be served plain or with a brown sauce.

title: lemon torte with strawberries
directions: Spray bottom only of 8-inch spring-form pan with nonstick spray.
Set aside.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
(If you intend to freeze, do not cook before freezing.)
Top with crushed Ritz crackers mixed with margarine.
Can freeze any leftovers.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan over low heat, melt butter.
Remove from heat and add sugar, flour, cocoa, baking powder, salt, eggs and vanilla.
Stir with spoon until batter is well blended and smooth.
Stir in 1/2 cup chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with remaining chocolate chips.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until set. Cool on wire rack.

title: oven barbecued steak
directions: Cut meat into 10 serving pieces.
In a large skillet, brown meat in oil.
Remove meat to Dutch oven.
Add remaining ingredients to skillet; simmer 5 minutes and pour catsup mixture over meat.
Cover and bake 2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in greased square pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: 3 lemon pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
In separate bowl, mix Crisco, sugar and egg yolks, well beaten.
Add extracts, juice from the three lemons, milk and flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold in beaten egg whites and bake in loaf pan 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: maria's breakfast dish
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with 8 slices of bread.
Cover with 8 slices of bacon and 8 slices of cheese.
Mix all remaining ingredients, except butter and chips.
Spread over cheese.
Let stand overnight in fridge.

title: quick-trick brazil nut fruit cake
directions: Butter 2 loaf pans (10 1/4 x 3 5/8 x 2 5/8-inch).
Line with 2 strips waxed paper, extending paper above rim.
Butter again; set aside.
Put Brazil nuts in a large mixing bowl with graham crackers, raisins, glazed fruit and glazed cherries.
Place marshmallows in top of double boiler with orange juice, vanilla, orange rind and spices.
Heat over boiling water, stirring occasionally, until marshmallows are melted.
Add Brazil nut-fruit mixture; blend thoroughly.
Turn into prepared pans, pressing with spoon.
Fold waxed paper over cake.
Press down with hands.
Chill in refrigerator 6 to 8 hours.

title: sweet and sour wieners
directions: Wrap each wiener with bacon and secure with a toothpick. Place on cookie sheet lined with foil.
Mix brown sugar with mustard.
Dribble 1/3 of this over wieners.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes, uncovered.
Take off of pan and put in crock-pot. Pour rest of the mustard sauce over the wieners and cook on low 5 to 6 hours.

title: microwave chex muddy buddies
directions: Pour cereal into large bowl; set aside.
In 1-quart microwave safe bowl, combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine. Microwave on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth, stirring after 1 minute.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereals, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated.
Pour cereal mixture into large resealable plastic bag with powdered sugar. Seal securely and shake until all pieces are well coated.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.

title: pineapple-orange ice
directions: In a small saucepan, combine water and sugar.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Cool slightly. Stir in juices.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cover pan with foil and freeze about 5 hours or until mixture is firm.

title: banana split pie
directions: Prepare graham cracker crust.
Mix pudding according to package directions; pour into crust.
Cook pineapple for 10 minutes over low heat.
Add thickening, if necessary (1 teaspoon cornstarch mixed with 1 to 2 tablespoons water).
Cool for 10 to 15 minutes. Pour over pudding.
Spread with whipped topping over top.
Garnish with pecans and cherries.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes and serve.

title: broccoli with rice
directions: In a large skillet, saute the onion and celery in butter until the vegetables are clear.
Cook broccoli according to the package directions; drain well.
Mix broccoli with soup and cheese; add to celery and onion.
Stir in rice; season and mix well.
Put into a greased casserole and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This can be mixed ahead and frozen.

title: christmas bread
directions: Mix yeast, sugar, salt, cardamon and 4 cups of flour in a large bowl.
Heat milk, water and butter to scalding (130°).
Add flour mixture and beat well for 10 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat thoroughly after each one.
Add fruit and remaining flour; mix well.
Knead for 10 minutes.
Grease bowl, turn bread into the bowl, cover with a damp cloth and let rise until doubled. Punch down, knead and let rise until doubled again.
Punch down and shape into 4 loaves.
Put into greased pans.
Brush top with egg white and let rise until doubled in the pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Slice and serve toasted with butter.

title: peanut butter paisley brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a large bowl, beat butter and peanut butter.
Add sugar and brown sugar, beating well after each.
Blend in vanilla.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix into peanut butter mixture, blending well.
Spread half of batter into prepared pan.
Spoon syrup over top.
Carefully spread with remaining batter.
Swirl with metal spatula for marbled effect.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool in pan.
Cut into squares.

title: beef chunks in sour cream
directions: Roll beef cubes in flour; brown in shortening.
Add onions and brown.
Add mushrooms, water and spices.
Cover and simmer over low heat about 1 3/4 hours, or until meat is tender.
Stir occasionally during cooking.
Stir in sour cream and heat through. Serve over noodles.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into a large bowl; sprinkle in yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in lukewarm milk mixture.
Add 3 cups of flour; beat until smooth.
Add enough additional flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto floured board.
Knead 2 minutes. Place in greased bowl.
Cover; let rise until doubled.
Punch down.
Divide in half.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Roll each loaf in cornmeal.
Place in 2 greased loaf pans. Cover; let rise until doubled.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until done.
Remove from baking pans; cook on wire racks.
Slice and toast.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch glass dish with bread.
Fry sausage and spread on top of bread, then top with cheese.
Beat eggs, salt and dry mustard together.
Add half and half.
Pour mixture over bread, meat and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: chicken salsa
directions: Line bottom and sides of lightly greased 9 x 13-inch dish with flour tortillas.
Mix together in mixing bowl the cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup and salsa.
Mix well.
Pour 1/2 mixture into dish lined with flour tortillas.
Add a layer of chicken nuggets.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers until dish is filled.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan dainties
directions: Let cheese and margarine come to room temperature.
Work together with hand and put a small amount in 24 miniature muffin cups and then work out with your finger.
Combine other ingredients and fill cups.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. Remove from pans as soon as they come from oven.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken in pressure cooker.
Save broth; debone and deskin chicken.
Cut into small pieces.
Lightly grease 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
In another bowl, combine margarine, pepper, salt, flour and buttermilk.
Mix this to form batter.
Layer chicken, broth mix and spoon batter on top.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix well the sugar, oil and eggs. Add sifted flour and vanilla. Add apples and nuts by hand. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.

title: pineapple-sour cream pie
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, flour and salt in a saucepan.
Add pineapple, sour cream and juice.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Beat egg yolks until thick and pale. Gradually stir about 1/4 of hot mixture into yolks; add to remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook, stirring constantly, 2 minutes.
Cool.
Spoon into shell.

title: quick butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan.
Remove from heat; blend in sugar.
Cool slightly.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together; add to brown sugar mixture with remaining ingredients. Stir until mixed.
Pour into greased and floured rectangular baking pan (about 11 x 7 inches).
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes until done.
Cool in pan; cut in bars.

title: sugar starch for doilies
directions: Boil together 2 minutes.
Stir well, then boil 2 minutes more. Let cool before using.

title: meat filled shells
directions: Cook shells as directed; drain and cool shells. Brown hamburger in pan; drain off fat. Combine meat, eggs and everything else. Mix well. Fill shells with filling. Put a thin layer of sauce, then your stuffed shells face down.
Cover with remaining sauce; add a little more cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chips.
Spoon into greased casserole dish, 9 x 13-inch.
Top with chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: greek ham pie
directions: Cut phyllo to size of dish.
Melt butter.
Brush bottom of dish.
Spread 1 sheet on bottom; brush with butter.
Do this 6 times.
Layer ham, then cheese.
Layer 3 of phyllo; brush each with butter.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Put 3 more layers and sprinkle with crumbs.
Cut through layers to make 8 triangles. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 2 Pyrex rectangular dishes.
Yield:
16 large or 64 appetizers.

title: easy italian casserole
directions: In a large skillet sprayed with vegetable cooking spray, brown beef with onion and garlic.
Drain well.
Stir in tomatoes, oregano, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in zucchini.
Cook for additional 10 minutes. Stir in noodles.

title: cafe au lait
directions: Use 4 tablespoons coffee to 1 cup water.
Use any method desired.
Have ready an equal quantity of freshly scalded milk. At the same time pour equal amounts of coffee and milk into heated cups.
For a richer drink, add 1 tablespoon butter to each cup of milk or top each cup with 1 tablespoon whipped cream.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli by directions on box.
Cook rice by directions on box.
Cook onion in butter until tender.
Then add soup and Cheez Whiz.
When cheese is melted, mix all ingredients.
Put in casserole dish and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apricot whip
directions: Soak apricots in boiling water; then cook until tender. Mix sugar, cloves and ginger; add this to fruit.
Cool partly, then add
marshmallows
and
stir
well into partially cooled fruit and let
stand
overnight
to	absorb	juice.	Whip the whipping cream and fold into fruit mixture.	Chill, but do not freeze. Serves
Good
with
thin
nut	bread sandwiches. (Can add a few crushed macaroons.)

title: sugar-free pudding cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until very soft.
Gradually add 1/2 cup milk and blend until smooth.
Add remaining milk and pudding mix. Blend at low speed until smooth.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix and let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in greased casserole dish at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mayhaws
directions: Sort mayhaws, removing decayed fruit and trash.
You can leave the tiny stems and dark blossom end on the fruit.
Wash thoroughly.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to package directions; mix in Cool Whip. In a large bowl, layer pudding, wafers, strawberries, pudding, wafers and strawberries, beginning and ending with pudding.
Chill.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Mix together milk and lemonade. When thoroughly combined, fold in Cool Whip and food coloring.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: corned beef sandwich spread
directions: Break corned beef apart with fork.
Add mayonnaise, mustard and relish.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: Brown and drain ground beef and onion.
Add brown sugar, ketchup, mustard, barbecue sauce, molasses and pinto beans.
Put all into crock-pot and cook on high for 2 hours.

title: easy alfredo
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil.
If using fresh mushrooms these may be sauteed along with garlic, about 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin ice cream pie
directions: Mix pumpkin and ice cream in large mixing bowl.
Cream until well mixed.
Spoon into pie shell.
Freeze 1 hour.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef; drain
well.
Add
