onions and garlic and cook until onions are clear.
Add pepper and chili powder. Mix well.
Add tomato puree and water.	Bring to boil.	Reduce heat and simmer 3 hours.

title: apple pie
directions: Put apples in pan and add all ingredients.
Cook over low heat to let butter and sugar melt.
Pour into unbaked pie shell (deep). Strip the top with pastry and bake first 10 minutes at 400°, then reduce heat to 275° and cook for 50 to 60 minutes until good and brown.

title: a.b.c.  peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Sprinkle flour on your hands and begin to roll the cookie dough into 1-inch balls.
Put balls on a greased cookie sheet.
Dip a fork in sugar and press cookie ball out flat.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: 4 layer chocolate pie
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, oleo and chopped nuts.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: frozen rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate to rise.
When doubled in size, punch down.
Shape in rolls.
Freeze on cookie sheet or in bag or in pan ready to cook. Let rise again.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Drain and cut up artichoke hearts.
Mix with cut up green chilies, cheese and mayonnaise.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with chips while hot.

title: hummus
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread in a blender or a food processor until smooth, adding water until a desirable consistency is reached.
Makes hors d'oeuvres for 10 to 12.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Bring to boil fruit cocktail, crushed pineapple and sugar. Add jello; stir until dissolved.
Add cold water.
Set until it quivers; add whipped cream and shredded cheese.
Set in refrigerator.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients. Put into a 13 x 9 pan and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Filling: In medium mixing bowl, blend together Eagle Brand milk, lemon juice, lemon peel and yolks until thickened. Turn into pie shell.

title: capellini pomodoro
directions: *I often use Polaner ready to use chopped garlic and basil when fresh is not available.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Melt the stick of butter in a casserole dish. Add the broccoli, cheese, soup, water, rice, onions, and peppers; mix in casserole with the butter. (Some stores only carry the large jar of Cheez Whiz--in this case use only half of the jar). Add the crumbled Ritz crackers on top. Bake for 1 hour.

title: mandarin shrimp
directions: Heat oil in a frying pan and saute shrimp about 3 minutes, until pink.
Remove from the pan and set aside.
Add garlic to the pan and saute a minute or two.
Add mushrooms, sauteing 2 minutes longer.
Add water chestnuts, bouillon cube, 1 cup water and ginger.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Make a paste of cornstarch and water. Add soy sauce and pour into the pan.
Return the shrimp to the pan and heat until nicely thickened.
Serve over rice.
Sprinkle with green onion.
Serves 4.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Grease bowl.
Cook sausage; drain.
Lightly butter 1/2 bread and break into small pieces.
Add 1/2 cheese.
Add sausage.
Add last 1/2 bread.
Add last 1/2 cheese.
Lightly beat eggs with milk; add to casserole.
Let set overnight.
Add chiles.
Cook at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: beef and broccoli stir-fry
directions: Cut beef across the grain into thin slices.
Combine 1 tablespoon each cornstarch and soy sauce with sugar, ginger and garlic; stir in beef.
Let stand for 15 minutes.

title: cheesy hash brown casserole
directions: Combine hash browns and next 4 ingredients in a large bowl.

title: five flavor cake
directions: Cake:
Cream margarine, butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs (unbeaten), one at a time, beating after each. Measure all-purpose flour (sifted).
Add baking powder and salt to flour mixture and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk. Stir in flavorings.

title: soft chicken tacos
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring stock to a boil. Add chicken. Reduce heat to medium-high and cook 20 to 25 minutes or until chicken is tender. Cool.
Tear into strings.
In a covered vegetable steamer basket or bamboo steamer basket over boiling water, steam tortillas 3 to 5 minutes or until steaming hot.
Lay each tortilla flat. Fill center with chicken, tomatoes, onions, lettuce, sprouts and cheese.
Drizzle with salsa.
Fold sides of tortilla over center.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Combine in saucepan the cream of mushroom soup, 1 can Ro-Tel, 1 cup chicken broth and onion.
Layer in casserole dish 1/2 bag Doritos (crushed), slices of Velveeta cheese, chicken, 2/3 sauce, remaining Doritos and remaining sauce.
Sprinkle 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix, adding ingredients one at a time, with mixer. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Cool completely before removing from pan.

title: penne pasta with vegetables
directions: Saut carrots, onions, basil, parsley, oregano and garlic in olive oil for about 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes, zucchini, bell pepper, wine, salt and hot pepper flakes and simmer (uncovered) for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In separate pan, melt 1 tablespoon butter; add flour.
Cook roux over very low heat; whisk in heated cream.
Add tomato paste; whisk until mixture is very smooth.
Stir into vegetables along with Parmesan cheese.
Toss mixture with cooked pasta.

title: fruit dip for blackberries
directions: Combine and blend cream cheese with powdered sugar.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Fold Cool Whip into cheese and sugar mixture. Also beat until smooth.
Chill.

title: cherry cheesecake tart
directions: Mix all; pour on top of pie.
Chill well.

title: lime cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of boiling water and chill until slightly thickened.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into a 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill.

title: miniature chocolate cupcakes
directions: Melt chocolate and water together.
Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs; beat.
Add chocolate mixture, then dry ingredients and rum flavoring.
Line small cupcake tins.
Pour dough into pans and drop 6 to 8 chocolate bits on top of each before baking.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Yield: 48.
Freezes well.

title: cabbage for a king
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Blend in flour.
Add tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce, salt, sugar and pepper.
Cook finely shredded cabbage in boiling, salted water for 5 minutes.
Lightly brown bread cubes in one tablespoon butter.
Cube cheese.
Layer cabbage, tomato mix, bread and cheese in a 2-quart casserole. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chile con carne for 2
directions: Brown onions and meat in fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add a little water if mixture becomes dry.
Serves 2.

title: lazy day cobbler
directions: In a baking dish, mix flour, sugar, salt, milk and baking powder.
Do not stir anymore.
Pour peaches with juice over batter.
Melt margarine and pour on top.
Bake 50 minutes in 400° oven.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat; combine all ingredients in a 2 quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 1 hour. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine the margarine, buttermilk, sugar, nuts, eggs and flour.
Add vanilla and salt last.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chocolate bits and paraffin; mix thoroughly.
Let set in refrigerator approximately 30 minutes; then roll into balls.
Melt chocolate bits and paraffin slowly in a double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate mixture and place on waxed paper to cool.

title: twice baked cottage style potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes; prick several times with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Let cool to touch.
Slice skin away from top of each potato.
Carefully scoop out pulp, leaving shells intact.
Set aside shells.
Mash pulp.
Combine cottage cheese and milk in container of electric blender or food processor, process until smooth.
Add cottage cheese mixture, green onions, salt and pepper to potato pulp; stir well.
Stuff shells with potato mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: pennsylvania dutch potato filling
directions: With a fork, mix the eggs and potatoes.
Break the bread into pieces and mix with potatoes.
Pour milk over mixture to soak. Brown the onions in melted butter.
Stir onions and seasoning into filling.

title: cowboy jerky
directions: Cut beef strips about 1/4-inch thick. Make brine, combining all ingredients. Soak meat in brine approximately 6 hours or longer. Remove meat from brine and hang up or lay out flat to dry.

title: chili willie dip
directions: Brown meat; drain off fat.
Add taco seasoning and water. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add chili and cheese.
Heat 10 minutes. Serve with chips.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Arrange spareribs in large baking pan.
Add onions and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over spareribs.
Cover and bake in moderate oven (350°) about 1 1/2 hours, basting frequently.
Remove cover and continue to cook about 20 to 30 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: aunt tootsie ash's fruit and nut bars
directions: In a 9 x 14-inch well-greased pan, arrange pecan halves. Cover with a mixture of eggs, margarine, vanilla, brown sugar and flour.
Top with cherries and pineapple.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Cool and cut into squares.
Store in airtight container.
Freezes well.

title: poor man's lobster
directions: Put fish in pan frozen.
Cook without lid for 20 minutes. Lift gently out of pan; put on broiler pan.
Smooth on butter; broil for 2 or 3 minutes.

title: cheesy spinach bake
directions: Drain spinach.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 1-quart greased baking dish.
Cover and bake at 375°, 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: red velvet punch
directions: Heat 1 cup cranberry juice.
Dissolve gelatin.
Add the rest of cranberry juice and lemon juice; cool.
Add lemon-lime drink. Pour over ice and serve.

title: potato rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Mix together potatoes, Crisco, salt and sugar.
Add hot milk and let cool.
Add yeast mixture and eggs.
Beat well.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Add 5 1/2 cups of flour.
Mix and shape into rolls.
Let rise and bake at 375°.

title: sliced strawberry jam
directions: Slice strawberries in halves lengthwise.
Measure sugar and prepared fruit into large saucepan, packing fruit into cup when measuring; mix well.
Bring to a full rolling boil over high heat. Stir constantly.
Boil hard 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in pectin.
Then stir and skim by turns for just 5 minutes to cool slightly to prevent floating fruits.
Pour quickly into clean, sterilized jars.
Cover at once.

title: avocado dip
directions: Peel and crush avocados until smooth; add lemon juice and mix well.
Spread avocado mixture in bottom of serving dish.
Spread sour cream over first layer.
Pour picante sauce over sour cream layer.
Top off with shredded cheese.
Serve with chips.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
For variety, cover with cream cheese (optional).

title: doritos salad
directions: Brown meat.
Drain.
Add drained beans and heat.
Mix salad together and add meat and beans.

title: corn special cheese casserole
directions: Pour in 1/3 corn batter, then layer of cheese.
Alternate. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Very good!

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Top with topping.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Alternate, mixing eggs and milk with flour mixture.
Add butter, shortening and sugar.
Add flavoring.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: copper coin salad
directions: Marinate 12 to 24 hours.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Heat margarine or butter in small saucepan until melted; stir in brown sugar and brandy.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer until sauce is thickened to the consistency of honey, 5 to 8 minutes.
Makes about 2/3 cup.

title: broccoli nut salad
directions: Break and cut broccoli; place pieces in large serving bowl. Add pecans, raisins, red onion and bacon.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Add eggs and margarine.
Sift flour and pinch of salt.
Then add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: lye soap
directions: Heat the grease and strain.
Measure and set aside to cool. Combine lye and water and stir slowly into cooled, but not congealed, grease.
Use a granite dishpan, no other ware will do. Stir all the time, while pouring lye and water mixture into grease.
Use a wooden stick.
When the mixture is about the color and consistency of honey, pour into paper-lined carton boxes and allow to stand overnight or until hard enough to cut in squares. Age a month to six months.
Keep from intense cold or intense heat, the closet is the best.

title: diabetic lentil soup
directions: Mix all in a pot.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes.
Add fresh spinach juice or 1/2 lemon juice.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Simmer canned tomatoes and chicken stock until the liquid is reduced by one-half.
Season with parsley, onion quarters, garlic, Worcestershire sauce, salt, basil and thyme.
Slice and saute fresh or canned mushrooms in a little butter until golden; drain. Add to sauce, along with chicken meat.
Stir flour into mushroom drippings.
Add light cream.
Heat and stir until thickened. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add to tomato-chicken mixture.
Cool and freeze.

title: chocolate nut icing
directions: Cook the sugar with the butter and milk until they reach the soft ball stage.
(To test, drop a few drops of the mixture into a cup of cold water and roll them between the thumb and first finger.)
Add the chocolate chips and beat until the icing reaches a consistency for spreading.
Just before icing the cake, fold in the nuts.

title: shoulder lamb chop dinner
directions: Place chops in bottom of greased baking pan. Peel and quarter potatoes and fill in around chops.
In a bowl, mix salt, pepper, parsley, grated cheese, garlic and chopped onion.
Sprinkle mixture on top of chops.
Add crushed tomatoes.
Bake in covered casserole dish at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 4 or 6 servings.

title: kelly's hash browns
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Mix chopped onions, melted butter, cream of chicken soup, sour cream, salt and pepper; add to potatoes and mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grandma mcmillen's three bean salad
directions: Drain the green and yellow beans.
Rinse off the kidney beans.
Add the diced sweet onion, green and red peppers and diced celery.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Thaw lemonade completely and blend with milk and Cool Whip. Pour mixture into pie crust and top with additional Cool Whip. Chill and serve.

title: not-so-quick banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir in sour cream.
Combine dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with mashed bananas.
Pour into loaf pan and bake at 350° until done.

title: cornell bread
directions: Put water, yeast and honey in large bowl.
Stir and let stand 5 minutes in warm place.
Sift flour, soy flour and dry milk solids.
Stir in wheat germ.
Add salt to yeast mixture.
Add half of flour mixture and beat for 2 minutes.
Add oil and rest of flour mixture (add extra flour if needed).
To form dough, knead on floured area 10 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
Put in greased bowl.
Grease top.
Cover and let rise 45 minutes or until double.
Punch down.
Fold over edges and turn upside down in bowl.
Cover and let rise 20 minutes.
Divide in three and form 3 balls.

title: baked pork chops and stuffing
directions: Melt shortening in 10-inch skillet.
Brown pork chops.
In medium mixing bowl, combine bread crumbs, celery, onion, butter, eggs, salt and pepper (as desired) together.
Remove chops from skillet and pour 2 cups of water in skillet.
Pour over stuffing. Place pork chops in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with stuffing. Bake at 350° uncovered for 1 hour or until chops are tender.

title: "pecan pie"
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add remaining ingredients.
The melted butter should be added last.
Pour into unbaked 9 or 10-inch pie shell over the pecans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: raisin cake
directions: Beat margarine in bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour, salt and sugar.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir into dough with vanilla and lemon extract. Stir in raisins.
Butter a 10-inch tube pan.
Sprinkle the bottom with almonds.
Turn dough into pan and let rise to almost the top of the pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan for 20 minutes.
Invert onto cake plate and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Also good if drizzled with rum flavored confectioners glaze.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and mix in all but 1 tablespoon of taco seasoning mix.
Shred lettuce into one large bowl with kidney beans, onion and tomatoes.
Add cooled ground beef.
Just before serving, mix dressing, sugar, taco sauce and 1 tablespoon taco seasoning.
Pour over other ingredients and mix.
Add shredded cheese and crushed taco chips.
Stir and serve.
Makes a large bowl.

title: brochetta with cheese
directions: Slice bread on angle thinly.
Mix roasted garlic, cream cheese and squeezed tomatoes.
Spread on bread and sprinkle with Romano cheese and basil.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Sift together and stir in the next 3 ingredients.
Roll in ball, size of a small walnut. Roll in a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until lightly browned, but still soft.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, margarine, cocoa and salt in a large saucepan.
Bring to rolling boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and quickly mix in peanut butter until melted.
Add vanilla and oats.
Beat until thick.
Drop on greased cookie sheet by teaspoon or place in 2 greased 8 x 8-inch pans and cut in squares after cooling.

title: harvest potatoes
directions: Melt butter in large bowl. Add spices and mix. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mountain high cake
directions: Mix above ingredients well and cook in 3 layers at 350°. Cool and frost.

title: baked yams or sweet potatoes
directions: Place Italian bread crumbs in a shallow dish.
Set aside. Peel each zucchini and cut into slices about 1/2 inch thick.
Salt and pepper all slices.

title: southern stuffed dressing
directions: Melt butter, onion and celery in skillet until just tender. Add broth; heat.
Bake in 350° oven uncovered 1 hour.
Pour broth from chicken or turkey.

title: delicious baked beans
directions: Pour beans in mixing bowl; have onions sauteed. Add ketchup and brown sugar to taste. Stir well; pour into baking dish. Add bacon to top. Place in oven and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat together in large mixing bowl the oil, applesauce and sugar. Add beaten eggs and mashed bananas. Beat well. Sift together all dry ingredients and add to first mixture. Add milk and vanilla, mixing well. Stir in nuts.
Pour into large loaf pan that has been greased and floured. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then on rack out of pan for at least 1 hour before cutting. (Freezes well when tightly wrapped.)

title: crunchy apple salsa with chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken and mix well; allow flavors to blend 30 minutes.
Serve with grilled chicken.

title: herb bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix first 9 ingredients together, then add yeast; add eggs and gradually add flour.
Knead until smooth and let rise until doubled.
Punch down and divide into 2 loaf pans.
Let rise and then bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: cowboy beans
directions: In skillet, cook beef, onion and garlic.
Add peppers.
Pick and wash beans.
Cook in large pot all together for about 6 hours.

title: piccalilli
directions: Wash and chop the tomatoes, onions, green peppers and red peppers (discarding liquid is optional).
Place in a large pot. Add the 1 quart vinegar.
Boil 30 minutes, stirring often.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer 3 minutes and keep simmering while packing one jar at a time, sealing immediately.
Makes 6 to 7 pints.

title: frozen pumpkin dessert(4 to 6 servings)
directions: In medium bowl, combine pumpkin, sugar, salt, ginger, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir in pecans.
In a large, chilled bowl, fold pumpkin mixture into softened ice cream.

title: heavenly hash pie
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into a graham cracker crust and refrigerate 3 hours.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: governor's salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add lemon juice and vinegar.
Making sure carrots, onions, cucumber and green pepper are grated and chopped fine, add to gelatin mixture.
Add cottage cheese, salad dressing and coffee cream.
Refrigerate until firm. Looks yucky, but is a delicious summer salad.

title: sherry's apple strudel
directions: Beat together oil, egg, water and salt; add flour, while beating, until a firm dough, which pulls away from the bowl, forms.
Knead several times, until smooth and elastic.
Cover; let stand 30 minutes.
Cut with a sharp knife into two equal parts. Roll out each piece to a 12 x 18-inch rectangle.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Simmer dates and pineapple.
Blend.
Return to saucepan and boil.
Add
arrowroot mixed with water to mixture in pan. Simmer until
thick.
Blend berries slightly.
Add to mixture and cool. Store in refrigerator.
Can be frozen.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Grease bottom of baking dish.
Line bottom and sides of dish with chipped, dried beef slices.
Wrap a slice of bacon around each chicken breast and place on top of chipped beef.
Cover with mixture of soup and sour cream.
Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 3 hours.

title: popovers
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease generously 6 (6 ounce) custard cups or 8 medium muffin cups.
Beat eggs slightly in medium bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients with fork or wire whisk just until smooth (do not overbeat).
Fill custard cups 1/2 full or muffin cups full.
Bake 25 minutes at 450°.
Decrease oven temperature to 350°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Remove immediately from cups and serve hot.
Makes 6 to 8 popovers.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Mix butter, flour and sour cream together.
Spoon into muffin pan.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies(flapjacks)
directions: Melt butter, syrup and sugar in heatproof bowl in microwave (or in a saucepan over low heat).
Stir in oats; mix well.
Line pan (approximately 8 x 12-inch) with greased foil.
Press oat mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until lightly browned.
Cool for 5 minutes, then cut into squares.

title: stromboli
directions: Cook Italian sausage; slice sausage, then brown sausage.
Take loaf bread, roll out.
Place olive oil down center and spread. Layer pepperoni, sausages and gold, green and red peppers (mixed together).
Slice Mozzarella cheese.
Layer on top.
Then fold. Place in baking pan with sesame seed on bottom of pan.
Take yolk of egg, spread on top of loaf bread.
Sprinkle sesame seed on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: asparagus-pea casserole
directions: Put drained peas in a greased casserole dish.
Place asparagus over peas; pour (or smooth) soup over asparagus.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Top with corn flake crumbs.
Bake until flakes are brown at 350°.

title: wild turkey gumbo
directions: Heat butter in a large kettle and saute the okra.
Add flour and cook until it begins to turn brown.
Stir celery, garlic and green pepper into the pot and cook, stirring, another minute or so. Add water, bay leaves, 1 teaspoon salt, cayenne and tomato paste. Bring to a boil and simmer 15 minutes.
Add turkey pieces to the pot and simmer gently for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender.

title: hedge hogs
directions: Grind dates and nuts in food chopper.
Add beaten eggs and sugar.
Add coconut and blend well. Shape with your hands into logs and roll in additional coconut.
(Use the stringy kind.) Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
These will be soft, but get chewy as they cool.

title: sausage and cheese party snack
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
(Add oregano to taste and a few dashes of Worcestershire sauce.)
Drain grease from sausage and mix Velveeta cheese in until completely melted.
Spread on party rye and bake at 350° until bread is toasted.

title: spicy chicken
directions: Bring the 4 cups of water to a boil, then add bouillon cubes, chicken tenders, rice and tomatoes.
Reduce heat and simmer until chicken is tender and rice is done, about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve.

title: homemade salsa
directions: In a small bowl, mix all ingredients, mashing tomatoes. Cover.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours to allow flavor to mellow.

title: shrimp and scallops au gratin
directions: Melt butter in large skillet over low heat.
Add shrimp, scallops and green onion.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes or until shrimp is pink and onion is tender.
Stir flour into shrimp mixture.
Add cream and half and half, cooking over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture starts to thicken.
Remove from heat. Add 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese and stir until smooth.
Add red pepper and brandy.
Serve over fettucine noodles or rice with extra cheeses, if desired.

title: rolls
directions: Pour 1 cup warm water over salt, sugar and shortening.
Stir until dissolved, then add 1 cup cold water.
Add yeast and eggs. Add 7 1/2 cups flour.
Cover and let rise in warm place 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Work down; cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: squash puppies
directions: Drain squash well.
Mash and drain again.
Combine with remaining
ingredients.
Drop by tablespoons into hot oil. Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: orange glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Peel; cut potatoes lengthwise in half.
Layer in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In saucepan, stir sugar, cornstarch, salt and orange peel.
Slowly stir in orange juice; add margarine.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Reserve 1 cup of broccoli's water.
Combine softened cream cheese with this water (a whisk works well).
In a casserole dish, layer as follows:
broccoli, cream cheese mixture, crushed crackers and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: grandma's yum yum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Whip egg whites separately and fold in batter.
Bake according to cake mix directions.

title: farmer's market squash casserole
directions: Peel squash; slice and boil in small amount of salted water for 10 minutes.
When soft, drain and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Put into one 2-quart of two 1-quart casserole dishes.
Top with remaining cornbread dressing crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: spanish fruit punch
directions: Pour the apple juice over the ice cubes in a large bowl and add the strips of lemon peel.
Add the fruit juices.
Stir in the sugar and add soda water to mixture.
Mix in fruit chunks.
Serve in glass or Spanish earthenware pitcher.
Serves 4.

title: lemon icebox dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients, except egg whites, whipping cream and crackers, until slightly thickened, stirring continuously over heat.
Let cool.
Fold in egg whites and cream.
Put half of crackers in bottom of ice tray.
Pour in mixture and top with remaining crackers.
Freeze.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Bake pie shells as directed.
Cool 15 minutes before placing filling inside.

title: old santa fe hamburger
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet.
Drain thoroughly.
Add elbow macaroni, precooked according to package directions.
Stir in green beans, stewed tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Simmer until thickened.
Serves 4.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Crush soda crackers; mix in butter and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Beat the egg whites until stiff, adding the sugar while beating. Put on top of cooled crust. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool. Spread pie filling over top of whites, then lastly spread with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: potato soup
directions: In 3
quart
saucepan,	cook onion in margarine about 5 minutes
or
until	tender.
Add
potatoes,
celery,
carrots, parsley, chicken
broth,
salt
and
pepper.
Cover and simmer about 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Reduce heat; add 3 1/2 cups milk and pimento.
Heat the soup until the milk is hot. (It
should not boil.) Blend flour with 1/2 cup milk; add to soup, stirring constantly.	Cook until soup is slightly thickened and bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grandma podmore's chocolate chip cake
directions: Grease a Bundt pan.
Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour. When cool, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: dill bread
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Combine in mixing bowl with all ingredients, except flour.
Stir in flour; knead well.
Let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk (about 60 minutes). Punch down and knead again.
Form into loaf; place in greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Let rise in warm place for 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 1 large loaf.

title: tuna fish roll
directions: Mix dough together using flour, baking powder, salt, oil and milk.
Roll out for size of jelly roll pan.
Mix filling together (tuna, eggs, soup and parsley).
Spread filling over all dough. Roll up dough and seal ends.
Make into circle or semi-circle on jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until brown.
Cut and serve hot.

title: hearty beef dip
directions: Place ground chuck, onion, Ro-Tel tomatoes, cubed Velveeta cheese, cilantro and hot sauce in crock-pot or heavy pan.
Stir well.
Heat slowly until ready to serve; stir often.
Serve with Fritos or other substantial "dippers."

title: carrot-coconut cookies
directions: Mix carrots, sugar, shortening and eggs.
Stir flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in coconut.
Drop by teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until almost no indentation remains when touched, about 8 minutes.

title: chinese chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Saute onion and celery until soft. Add soup, bouillon, soy sauce, Tabasco, pepper and chicken.
Cook, stirring often, for 5 minutes.
Place mixture in casserole and top with noodles and nuts.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop the popcorn, then melt butter; stir in sugar, syrup and salt. Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 15 minutes without stirring.	Stir in soda and pour over popcorn. Bake 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slightly cook carrots (should still be crisp).
Heat the next 6 ingredients together for 2 or 3 minutes.
Mix all together and chill overnight before serving.

title: strawberry delight pie
directions: Wash and stem strawberries.
If they are large, cut into halves.
Combine water, sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Cook until thickened.
Add a few drops of food coloring and vanilla.
Let cool, then stir berries gently into cornstarch mixture.
Put whipped topping on top.

title: layered dip
directions: Layer the ingredients and serve with your favorite tortilla chips.

title: ooey-gooey peanut butter chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine 1/4 cup condensed milk, melted margarine, milk, egg white and cake mix.
Batter will be very stiff.
Spray 13 x 9 baking dish.
Press 2/3 of batter into prepared baking dish, using floured hands (layer will be thin). Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
In another bowl combine 1/2 cup condensed milk and marshmallow cream.
Stir in peanut butter morsels.
Remove baked layer from oven and spread marshmallow mixture evenly over brownie layer.	Carefully drop remaining batter by spoonfuls over marshmallow mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool completely in pan.
Serves 24.
Delicious.

title: spinach delight
directions: Remove wrapper from spinach box; place box in a flat baking dish.
Pierce with a fork.
Microwave at High for 7 minutes. Combine remaining ingredients.
Add spinach and mix well.
Spoon mixture into a 1-quart casserole.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap.
Microwave at High for 3 or 4 minutes or until casserole is almost set, turning once.
Let stand 1 minute.
If not set, continue in microwave briefly.
Serves 4.

title: bouillabaisse
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
Cut lobster into 6 - 8 pieces.
Cut fish fillets into 2-inch pieces.
Cut large scallops in half.
Wash clams well.
In large saucepan, cook onion in oil till tender.
Add 6 cups fish stock or water, tomatoes, garlic, parsley, thyme, bay leaf, salt & pepper.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Strain seasoned stock into large kettle.
Discard vegetables.
Bring strained stock to boil.
Add lobster and fish.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add scallops and clams.
Boil till clams open, about 5 minutes.
Serve with French Bread.

title: cranberry-raisin pie
directions: Mix cornstarch with water. Add other ingredients and cook 10 minutes. Cool and place between 2 crusts, lattice top crust is nice.
Bake at 400° until crust is done. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together well and put in refrigerator for at least 12 hours for chilling.
Place this dough around cherries and again return to the refrigerator.
Melt the chocolate chips and paraffin in top of double boiler.
Dip candy with toothpick into the chocolate; shake off excess and cool. Makes about 5 dozen.
This is very rich.
May also use pecans or almonds instead of cherries.

title: peanut butter clusters
directions: Melt almond bark and chocolate chips in double boiler.
When completely melted, stir in peanuts and drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Keep cool.

title: mandarin orange-pineapple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except oranges.
Fold in oranges gently.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Snap off tough ends of asparagus. Remove scales with a vegetable peeler if desired. Cut asparagus diagonally into 1 1/2 inch pieces. Place asparagus and broccoli flowerets in a vegetable steamer over boiling water. Cover and steam 6 to 8 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender. Remove from heat; set aside.

title: graham cracker dessert
directions: Make instant pudding as directed.
Blend in Cool Whip. alternating, place 1 layer of graham crackers in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and top with pudding mixture.
Make several layers; top with milk chocolate icing.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chili sausage supper
directions: Cook pork, onion and pepper.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover; simmer 30 minutes until noodles are tender, adding more water if necessary.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix and bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Best cooked in iron skillet.

title: chocolate, stout and bourbon pie
directions: Stir together the brown sugar, flour and cornmeal.
Beat eggs with granulated sugar until thick and light in color.
Add vanilla, stout and bourbon to the brown sugar mixture, stirring to eliminate lumps.
Fold in the beaten egg mixture and chocolate chips.
Pour into crust and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until the center is set.
Cool just until warm and serve with just a dollop of whipped cream.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Mix in wafers and baking powder. Add nuts and coconut. Bake in greased tube pan for 1
hour or more at 355°.
Let cool thoroughly in pan.

title: cake decorating frosting
directions: Cream butter and shortening together.
Add vanilla flavoring and stir.
Add milk; add confectioners sugar gradually so that it will not be difficult to stir.
After all ingredients have been mixed well, the mixture is ready to be used for frosting.
You may use food coloring to change the color.

title: cheez-it chicken
directions: Fill casserole dish with boneless, skinless chicken breast tenders, salt and pepper.
Spread sour cream over chicken. Sprinkle crushed Cheez-Its crackers over sour cream.
Pour 1/2 cup melted butter over Cheez-Its crackers.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown at 350° in oven.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine. Add eggs, bananas and nuts. Add flour gradually. Pour into 2 loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Yield: 20 servings.

title: christmas fruit cake
directions: Set oven at 300° to preheat while you mix the cake.
In large mixing bowl, put butter, sugar and spices.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Then add applesauce, rum and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and soda together and gradually add to the mixture.
Beat until batter is smooth.
Fold in glaced fruit mix and nuts.
Mix well to distribute throughout batter.
Pour batter into a greased, lightly floured tube or angel food cake pan.
Bake in slow 300° oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours; in loaf pan about 2 hours.
Cake will pull away from pan when completely done. Cool in pan.
Turn out and allow to cool.

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine corn meal, flour and salt.
Add milk, egg and oil; mix well.
Insert wooden skewer in one end of each frankfurter.
Coat with additional flour.
Dip into corn meal mixture.
Fry a few at a time in deep, hot oil (375°) until golden brown.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Prepare the chicken breasts, then place each between sheets of plastic wrap and pound with the flat side of a wooden mallet or cleaver or with a metal meat pounder, until very thin and velvety. Heat oil and butter together in a large skillet until bubbling, keeping heat low enough so butter doesn't burn.

Place chicken breasts in skillet and brown; turn and brown the other side, then reduce heat and cook just until tender, another couple of minutes. Season chicken to taste with salt and pepper and remove to heated serving plates or platter.
Add lemon juice and capers to skillet and stir to get up any brown bits.
Heat through and spoon over chicken.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 to 8 servings.

title: hickory b~b~q sauce
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan over low heat. Add onion and cook until tender. Add all other ingredients. Cook on low for 30 minutes.

title: spice cake (eggless)
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, water, raisins, spices and boil for 3 minutes.
Add flour, soda and baking powder, with nuts.
Bake 45 minutes at 300° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: potato-egg bake
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes and bacon.
Add potatoes and bacon.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: play doh
directions: Mix all ingredients; cook over high heat, stirring constantly. In 2 to 3 minutes, consistency changes (balls up or pulls away from sides).
Dump out immediately on plastic or formica surface. Knead.
Put in airtight container.

title: hidden valley ranch chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces in melted butter.
Dredge in bowl of dressing mix, cheese and crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, in a well-greased baking dish at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes; mix all together and place in large dish sprayed with Pam (8 1/2 x 13-inches).
Spread 2 cups crushed Ritz crackers on top.
Pour 1 melted stick margarine over crackers. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream the sugar and Crisco well.
Add salt and eggs and beat well.
Add buttermilk alternately with flour.
Add soda, hot water and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into two 8-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost with favorite frosting.

title: barbecue hamburgers
directions: Fry onion and beef in oil in large skillet.
Season with salt and pepper.
